1
00:00:52,219 --> 00:00:55,097 
[Vintage Malayalam song playing]

2
00:01:24,877 --> 00:01:27,504 
[Vintage Malayalam song continues]

3
00:01:29,548 --> 00:01:32,509 
[Musical Night
by Cochin Kalamela]

4
00:01:39,892 --> 00:01:41,560 
- Hey, son... Psst!
- Huh?

5
00:01:41,894 --> 00:01:43,061 
Here's the orchestra list.

6
00:01:43,645 --> 00:01:44,980 
This is the final song.

7
00:01:45,022 --> 00:01:47,024 
Don't forget to add my name
at the end of the announcement.

8
00:01:47,107 --> 00:01:48,775 
Saji Pattambi, Troupe Manager.
Got it?

9
00:01:48,942 --> 00:01:50,152 
- What was that?
- Saji Pattambi!

10
00:01:50,194 --> 00:01:51,486 
- Right, right.
- Okay.

11
00:02:01,455 --> 00:02:02,623 
- Hey, Razak...
- Yeah?

12
00:02:02,623 --> 00:02:03,957 
The visas for the Europe trip arrived.

13
00:02:05,125 --> 00:02:07,127 
Good for you, Saji Chetta.

14
00:02:08,045 --> 00:02:09,254 
Oh no!

15
00:02:10,255 --> 00:02:11,256 
What's wrong?

16
00:02:11,757 --> 00:02:14,009 
We submitted 15 passports
for the trip.

17
00:02:14,384 --> 00:02:16,261 
But we got visas
for only 14 people.

18
00:02:16,553 --> 00:02:17,763 
One person's visa is missing.

19
00:02:18,055 --> 00:02:19,181 
Whose visa is it?

20
00:02:31,985 --> 00:02:33,987 
[Announcement] Keyboard: Francis.

21
00:02:35,531 --> 00:02:36,823 
Francis Chettan is cleared.

22
00:02:36,949 --> 00:02:39,326 
Violin: Xavier,

23
00:02:39,952 --> 00:02:40,994 
Linto,

24
00:02:41,411 --> 00:02:42,704 
Kundara Das.

25
00:02:42,955 --> 00:02:44,498 
The entire violin team
has received visas.

26
00:02:44,790 --> 00:02:46,792 
Tumba: Joy.

27
00:02:48,502 --> 00:02:49,545 
Tumba Joy made it too.

28
00:02:49,545 --> 00:02:53,048 
Tabla: Surendran, Chacko.

29
00:02:55,008 --> 00:02:56,677 
Even Chacko, the troublemaker,
got through.

30
00:02:56,718 --> 00:02:59,471 
Prabhendu on electric guitar.

31
00:03:14,778 --> 00:03:15,946 
- Hey, Razak...
- Yeah?

32
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:17,865 
It's Prabhendu who didn't
get the visa.

33
00:03:55,986 --> 00:03:57,154 
- And then?
- Huh?!

34
00:03:57,863 --> 00:03:58,947 
Okay, okay.

35
00:03:59,781 --> 00:04:01,116 
Let me sleep for a bit.

36
00:04:04,536 --> 00:04:05,537 
Prabha...

37
00:04:05,787 --> 00:04:06,788 
What's going on?

38
00:04:06,997 --> 00:04:09,208 
I'm searching for a jacket
to handle the cold in Europe.

39
00:04:09,917 --> 00:04:12,586 
My jacket from the US tour
has turned all mouldy.

40
00:04:13,253 --> 00:04:15,631 
I have to place the order today
to get it before we leave.

41
00:04:15,839 --> 00:04:17,216 
Ah, true, true.

42
00:04:17,424 --> 00:04:20,177 
Hey, that room behind
our rehearsal space...

43
00:04:20,219 --> 00:04:21,929 
I'm going to use it
for two months, okay?

44
00:04:22,054 --> 00:04:23,347 
I'm vacating my current apartment.

45
00:04:23,388 --> 00:04:25,140 
So, to store my stuff...

46
00:04:25,307 --> 00:04:26,725 
So you already vacated your flat?

47
00:04:26,767 --> 00:04:28,727 
What is this? You could've
at least asked me first!

48
00:04:28,769 --> 00:04:30,812 
Just a second.
Let me just enter this OTP.

49
00:04:30,896 --> 00:04:32,814 
- Wait, wait! Don't enter it!
- 4--

50
00:04:33,065 --> 00:04:34,441 
They've cut the electric guitar, man.

51
00:04:34,441 --> 00:04:36,235 
You're the only one
who's not coming on the trip!

52
00:04:36,485 --> 00:04:37,486 
What?!

53
00:04:39,196 --> 00:04:40,239 
And then?

54
00:04:44,201 --> 00:04:46,161 
- Who's having the omelette?
- Just keep it here.

55
00:04:46,328 --> 00:04:47,704 
How about some
chicken fry for you, sir?

56
00:04:47,746 --> 00:04:48,747 
It's our speciality.

57
00:04:49,456 --> 00:04:50,457 
We've also got quail fry.

58
00:04:50,958 --> 00:04:52,584 
- No need.
- We have pork with Chinese potatoes.

59
00:04:52,709 --> 00:04:54,336 
- It's amazing.
- Get going, will you?

60
00:04:54,503 --> 00:04:56,046 
He's a Namboothiri (Brahmin).
Pure veg.

61
00:04:56,630 --> 00:04:58,382 
Then I'll remove the pork
and get him the Chinese potatoes.

62
00:04:58,423 --> 00:05:00,968 
Hey, this isn't some wedding spread
where food keeps coming.

63
00:05:01,009 --> 00:05:02,052 
I still have to pay you, right?

64
00:05:04,763 --> 00:05:06,849 
Will this idiot go around
asking everyone the same thing?

65
00:05:07,641 --> 00:05:09,810 
We don't even have enough budget
for everyone's omelettes.

66
00:05:10,143 --> 00:05:11,812 
If budget was a problem,
you should've said it earlier.

67
00:05:11,812 --> 00:05:15,482 
You know, adding an omelette to
the dosa gives it a touch of luxury.

68
00:05:15,899 --> 00:05:17,484 
I mean the electric guitar here,
not the omelette!

69
00:05:17,526 --> 00:05:19,903 
Yeah, I asked them
the exact same thing.

70
00:05:20,153 --> 00:05:22,281 
Then, that sponsor guy
sent a message.

71
00:05:22,281 --> 00:05:23,282 
Let me find it.

72
00:05:24,741 --> 00:05:27,077 
Chetta, one of the investors
pulled out at the last minute.

73
00:05:27,244 --> 00:05:28,745 
We can pull through only
if we remove one person.

74
00:05:28,829 --> 00:05:29,955 
- So I...
- And also...

75
00:05:29,997 --> 00:05:31,915 
Please convey my special apologies
to Prabhendu Ma'am.

76
00:05:32,916 --> 00:05:34,209 
Prabhendu "Ma'am"?
Idiot!

77
00:05:35,127 --> 00:05:36,128 
Look, Prabha...

78
00:05:36,587 --> 00:05:38,338 
Don't think I'm just trying
to make you feel better.

79
00:05:39,006 --> 00:05:40,507 
What if this is actually
for the best?

80
00:05:40,674 --> 00:05:44,094 
What? Being broke,
homeless for two months, and starving?!

81
00:05:44,136 --> 00:05:45,262 
Oh, give me a break!

82
00:05:45,304 --> 00:05:47,055 
It's not like you come from
some poor household!

83
00:05:47,514 --> 00:05:51,560 
Wouldn't even a tiny bit of
your dad's and brother's puja income

84
00:05:51,685 --> 00:05:54,021 
be enough for you
to manage a full Europe tour?

85
00:05:54,146 --> 00:05:56,148 
Wasn't it your ego that made you
snap your sacred thread

86
00:05:56,231 --> 00:05:57,566 
and choose to live by cutting costs?

87
00:05:57,900 --> 00:06:00,360 
If someone loses faith
and becomes an atheist,

88
00:06:00,402 --> 00:06:01,820 
that's their personal choice.

89
00:06:02,196 --> 00:06:04,698 
That is not ego.
That's confidence.

90
00:06:05,157 --> 00:06:07,659 
- No, Prabha... I didn't mean--
- I'm not finished.

91
00:06:07,826 --> 00:06:09,661 
To become a truly
passionate musician,

92
00:06:09,703 --> 00:06:11,455 
you have to sacrifice
a lot of things.

93
00:06:11,496 --> 00:06:13,665 
Just imagine if A.R. Rahman
had played it safe,

94
00:06:13,665 --> 00:06:15,834 
packed his lunch every day
and gone to a bank job,

95
00:06:15,876 --> 00:06:18,378 
would we have even half the songs
we performed on stage today?

96
00:06:18,754 --> 00:06:21,089 
Prabha, I wasn't trying
to argue with you.

97
00:06:21,548 --> 00:06:24,676 
What I actually wanted to talk about
was the passion you have.

98
00:06:25,928 --> 00:06:28,680 
You're the most talented person
in our troupe.

99
00:06:29,014 --> 00:06:31,016 
Have any of these guys
ever played for a movie?

100
00:06:31,225 --> 00:06:34,269 
You're the only one they call
for studio recordings, right?

101
00:06:35,229 --> 00:06:36,980 
But that only happens
once in a while, right?

102
00:06:37,231 --> 00:06:39,107 
Anyway, since your trip is cancelled,

103
00:06:39,149 --> 00:06:41,485 
you should attend your father's
70th birthday celebration.

104
00:06:41,527 --> 00:06:43,487 
Your elder brother called you
so many times, right?

105
00:06:43,529 --> 00:06:44,655 
No, that's not a good idea.

106
00:06:44,738 --> 00:06:45,739 
Look...

107
00:06:46,073 --> 00:06:48,992 
There's a proven trend of grumpy dads
becoming warm and loving

108
00:06:49,034 --> 00:06:50,827 
once they hit 70.

109
00:06:51,203 --> 00:06:53,205 
This is your chance to slip in
and stay there for some time.

110
00:06:53,580 --> 00:06:56,083 
You can save money
on food and rent, right?

111
00:06:56,458 --> 00:06:58,794 
Plus, free WiFi, free laundry!
How great is that?

112
00:06:58,836 --> 00:07:00,254 
Hey, son!
Got any quail eggs?

113
00:07:00,337 --> 00:07:01,588 
Him and his damn eggs!

114
00:07:01,713 --> 00:07:03,423 
Eggs! Eggs! Eggs!

115
00:07:03,549 --> 00:07:05,300 
Where do you keep
shoving all these eggs?

116
00:07:05,425 --> 00:07:07,219 
So now it's quail eggs
instead of chicken eggs?

117
00:07:07,302 --> 00:07:08,637 
Can't you eat a meal
without eggs, huh?

118
00:07:08,679 --> 00:07:11,265 
[Radiant at 70
- Neelakandan Namboothiri]

119
00:07:16,645 --> 00:07:17,604 
Indu...

120
00:07:17,896 --> 00:07:19,189 
I know you won't come.

121
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:21,650 
But still, whenever you're
free, if you come home,

122
00:07:21,692 --> 00:07:23,944 
it would make Dad very happy,

123
00:07:24,695 --> 00:07:26,321 
even if he doesn't express it.

124
00:07:27,072 --> 00:07:29,491 
Even uncle keeps talking
about wanting to see you.

125
00:07:37,833 --> 00:07:38,959 
I'm busy.

126
00:07:39,418 --> 00:07:40,419 
I'll try.

127
00:08:00,022 --> 00:08:02,024 
Passengers getting down at this stop,
please step out.

128
00:08:09,448 --> 00:08:11,366 
[Radiant at 70
- Neelakandan Namboothiri]

129
00:08:11,450 --> 00:08:12,492 
Hello...

130
00:08:12,784 --> 00:08:13,827 
Huh?

131
00:08:13,869 --> 00:08:15,287 
Aadi, no.
You'll get hurt.

132
00:08:16,246 --> 00:08:17,289 
When was this?

133
00:08:17,331 --> 00:08:18,373 
What?

134
00:08:18,749 --> 00:08:20,042 
What did you see while passing?

135
00:08:21,502 --> 00:08:22,920 
You must stay for lunch, okay?

136
00:08:23,545 --> 00:08:25,255 
There's nothing wrong with Dad.

137
00:08:25,506 --> 00:08:27,716 
Just stop the car
and read that flex board properly.

138
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:30,219 
Flex boards aren't
just for funerals, you know!

139
00:08:30,427 --> 00:08:31,428 
Okay.

140
00:08:31,929 --> 00:08:32,930 
What is it, Thulasi?

141
00:08:33,222 --> 00:08:36,600 
Your Dad had asked me to let him know
once the water filter service is done.

142
00:08:36,683 --> 00:08:38,101 
Ask them to wait for a bit.

143
00:08:38,143 --> 00:08:39,978 
I'll tell Dad right after
the Minister leaves.

144
00:08:43,941 --> 00:08:46,026 
This is my eldest son, Deepankuran.

145
00:08:46,109 --> 00:08:47,486 
He was with me at Sabarimala.

146
00:08:47,528 --> 00:08:48,779 
Then I must have seen him.

147
00:08:48,987 --> 00:08:50,781 
Do you work with your Dad
at the temple here?

148
00:08:50,822 --> 00:08:51,949 
Oh no.

149
00:08:51,990 --> 00:08:53,325 
He's always abroad.

150
00:08:53,325 --> 00:08:54,993 
He handles only VIP pujas.

151
00:08:55,160 --> 00:08:56,453 
He's flying to Kenya tonight.

152
00:08:56,495 --> 00:08:57,496 
And from there, to Dubai.

153
00:08:57,788 --> 00:09:00,040 
He even moved closer
to the airport for convenience.

154
00:09:00,624 --> 00:09:01,834 
And this is his wife.

155
00:09:03,126 --> 00:09:04,503 
Where is your younger son?

156
00:09:05,420 --> 00:09:06,588 
He'll be late.

157
00:09:06,630 --> 00:09:08,131 
- Let's click the photo.
- Alright.

158
00:09:10,342 --> 00:09:11,343 
Sir, over here!

159
00:09:20,978 --> 00:09:22,938 
Hey, Pappu!

160
00:09:25,399 --> 00:09:26,900 
Why are you coming in
from the back, Indu?

161
00:09:26,900 --> 00:09:28,944 
There were too many people
at the front, Thulasi Chechi.

162
00:09:28,944 --> 00:09:30,112 
Dad was there too.

163
00:09:30,445 --> 00:09:31,780 
I just wanted to avoid
creating a scene.

164
00:09:32,364 --> 00:09:34,241 
And this way,
I could see Pappu too.

165
00:09:34,658 --> 00:09:37,494 
Not Pappu.
You have to call him "Uncle Pappu" now.

166
00:09:38,287 --> 00:09:41,123 
When your mother brought him here
from behind the temple,

167
00:09:41,248 --> 00:09:43,250 
my child
was only four days old then.

168
00:09:43,458 --> 00:09:44,877 
She's studying in fifth grade now.

169
00:09:45,043 --> 00:09:48,046 
He really lost all his cheer
after Mom passed away, didn't he?

170
00:09:48,881 --> 00:09:50,174 
Not just him...

171
00:09:50,174 --> 00:09:51,383 
You did too.

172
00:09:58,765 --> 00:10:01,643 
[Sanskrit news plays on radio]

173
00:10:05,939 --> 00:10:08,358 
Sigh! How many times do I have to tell him?

174
00:10:12,738 --> 00:10:13,739 
Ugh!

175
00:10:20,537 --> 00:10:21,997 
Welcome back, Indu!

176
00:10:23,415 --> 00:10:26,835 
You know, if you press that
like this after peeing, it sprays water.

177
00:10:27,252 --> 00:10:28,504 
It doesn't even take a second.

178
00:10:28,504 --> 00:10:30,005 
Why do you have to make
the whole room stink?

179
00:10:30,130 --> 00:10:33,175 
We're already peeing
into water, aren't we?

180
00:10:33,175 --> 00:10:35,135 
So why flush more water in?

181
00:10:36,178 --> 00:10:38,347 
Aha! So uncle's favourite is here!

182
00:10:38,805 --> 00:10:41,475 
Indu, I need to leave right away
to catch my flight.

183
00:10:41,975 --> 00:10:44,228 
Go take a quick shower,
wear a nice mundu,

184
00:10:44,269 --> 00:10:45,646 
and go take care
of things downstairs.

185
00:10:46,438 --> 00:10:47,940 
I have a doubt, Uncle.

186
00:10:47,981 --> 00:10:51,401 
For the puja in Kenya, ebony twigs
are required for the sacred fire.

187
00:10:51,568 --> 00:10:53,195 
That's not easy
to get at the moment.

188
00:10:53,237 --> 00:10:55,072 
And we also need
to check in early.

189
00:10:55,155 --> 00:10:56,490 
Is there an alternative I can use?

190
00:10:56,532 --> 00:10:58,784 
- Isn't it for an auspicious occasion?
- Yes.

191
00:10:58,867 --> 00:11:01,870 
Then just use small twigs
from the Bael tree.

192
00:11:02,079 --> 00:11:03,705 
That's a relief!
We have Bael in stock.

193
00:11:03,747 --> 00:11:04,998 
Okay, so that's sorted.

194
00:11:05,207 --> 00:11:06,959 
Want me to bring you anything
from Kenya?

195
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:09,628 
Bring back a Kenyan beauty
for our chronic bachelor here.

196
00:11:09,711 --> 00:11:12,339 
Sounds good. Just make sure
she belongs to the Namboothiri clan!

197
00:11:12,381 --> 00:11:14,049 
Yeah, right!
High hopes you have!

198
00:11:14,383 --> 00:11:15,801 
- Okay. I'll call you, Indu.
- Okay.

199
00:11:16,051 --> 00:11:18,011 
- I'll come see you when I'm back.
- Alright, alright.

200
00:11:21,181 --> 00:11:23,684 
Deepu Chettan bought
his assistant a car.

201
00:11:24,142 --> 00:11:25,686 
I heard he pays him very well, too.

202
00:11:25,894 --> 00:11:28,730 
If you still had your sacred thread on,
Deepu would've taken you along.

203
00:11:28,772 --> 00:11:30,482 
Had you stayed with Neelakandan,

204
00:11:30,482 --> 00:11:33,402 
you would've been the chief priest
of our family temple by now.

205
00:11:33,610 --> 00:11:35,904 
Well, it's all because
of the path you chose, isn't it?

206
00:11:37,614 --> 00:11:38,699 
At least what I chose...

207
00:11:38,824 --> 00:11:40,659 
is something I can feel and hear.

208
00:11:41,034 --> 00:11:42,327 
All you have is hype, right?

209
00:11:42,327 --> 00:11:43,620 
There's nothing to see or hear.

210
00:11:43,620 --> 00:11:44,621 
That's enough.

211
00:11:44,913 --> 00:11:46,456 
He's just ignorant!

212
00:11:46,456 --> 00:11:49,376 
Forgive this ignorant fool,
O Lord!

213
00:11:50,919 --> 00:11:54,506 
And please remind him to flush
after he urinates, O Lord!

214
00:11:56,925 --> 00:11:58,635 
Please don't mind!

215
00:12:37,216 --> 00:12:38,884 
Rupesh, the owner of the
shop is this madam here.

216
00:12:39,259 --> 00:12:40,260 
Oh!

217
00:12:44,515 --> 00:12:46,850 
I'm not saying this just because I did it,
but the puja was a big success.

218
00:12:46,892 --> 00:12:48,143 
It's all the Lord's blessing.

219
00:12:48,143 --> 00:12:49,186 
Correct.

220
00:12:49,937 --> 00:12:51,230 
- Sreekutta...
- Yes.

221
00:12:55,108 --> 00:12:57,611 
Hare Krishna, Hare Krishna,
Krishna Krishna Hare Hare.

222
00:12:57,653 --> 00:12:58,654 
Hmm!

223
00:12:58,654 --> 00:13:01,114 
Hare Rama, Hare Rama,
Rama Rama Hare Hare.

224
00:13:01,156 --> 00:13:03,408 
Hare Krishna, Hare Krishna,
Krishna Krishna Hare Hare.

225
00:13:03,450 --> 00:13:05,869 
Hare Rama, Hare Rama,
Rama Rama Hare Hare.

226
00:13:05,869 --> 00:13:07,079 
Hare Krishna, Hare Krishna...

227
00:13:08,622 --> 00:13:09,623 
Sreekutta...

228
00:13:09,832 --> 00:13:11,124 
You can take it yourself, sir.

229
00:13:13,710 --> 00:13:15,128 
I'm not saying this
just because I did it,

230
00:13:15,879 --> 00:13:17,130 
but the puja was a big success.

231
00:13:17,214 --> 00:13:18,757 
- So?
- So, well...

232
00:13:31,353 --> 00:13:32,813 
- Sreekutta...
- Yes.

233
00:13:32,855 --> 00:13:34,398 
Just check whether
that broom works.

234
00:13:34,565 --> 00:13:36,275 
The broom is in
excellent working condition.

235
00:13:36,316 --> 00:13:37,818 
But you'll need to pay me extra
for cleaning.

236
00:13:37,943 --> 00:13:39,695 
Don't be so greedy, Sreekutta.

237
00:13:39,736 --> 00:13:41,613 
Why shouldn't I be?

238
00:13:41,738 --> 00:13:44,616 
Don't I take on
these low-budget pujas for you too?

239
00:13:44,825 --> 00:13:45,659 
- Is that so?
- Yes.

240
00:13:45,701 --> 00:13:47,744 
Then why were you trying to find
a new assistant instead of me?

241
00:13:47,744 --> 00:13:49,246 
No way!
Would I ever do that?

242
00:13:49,246 --> 00:13:50,455 
Oh, really?

243
00:13:50,747 --> 00:13:51,748 
Just a minute.

244
00:13:54,710 --> 00:13:56,795 
Bhasi, that Sreekuttan
is a complete fraud.

245
00:13:56,920 --> 00:13:58,297 
Do you know anyone else
who can assist me?

246
00:13:59,173 --> 00:14:01,633 
Even if I say all this,
I'm really fond of you.

247
00:14:01,967 --> 00:14:03,844 
Of course, I know that,
Rupeshetta!

248
00:14:04,344 --> 00:14:06,346 
And that? 500
the madam gave...

249
00:14:06,346 --> 00:14:07,389 
I'm keeping it.

250
00:14:07,389 --> 00:14:08,765 
Just consider it
my travel expense.

251
00:14:08,807 --> 00:14:09,808 
- Huh?
- Yeah.

252
00:14:11,310 --> 00:14:13,061 
- Aren't you happy, Rupeshetta?
- Yes.

253
00:14:13,645 --> 00:14:14,813 
I'll get going.
I've got work.

254
00:14:17,357 --> 00:14:18,483 
- Pavithran...
- Yes?

255
00:14:18,483 --> 00:14:19,776 
We need to leave at
4:30 AM tomorrow.

256
00:14:19,776 --> 00:14:20,777 
Okay.

257
00:14:20,819 --> 00:14:22,821 
Unni, start cutting vegetables
for the Sambar at 3:30 AM.

258
00:14:23,071 --> 00:14:24,072 
So where's the feast, Aunty?

259
00:14:24,114 --> 00:14:25,115 
In Thrissur.

260
00:14:25,157 --> 00:14:27,451 
Oh! You got your bike fixed?

261
00:14:27,492 --> 00:14:28,493 
That's great.

262
00:14:28,535 --> 00:14:30,245 
- I'll be here for a couple of months.
- Okay.

263
00:14:30,287 --> 00:14:32,748 
The 70th birthday feast
was fantastic, Uncle.

264
00:14:32,789 --> 00:14:34,583 
I couldn't eat on a banana leaf
because I arrived late.

265
00:14:34,625 --> 00:14:37,878 
Come on! Subramanyan Namboothiri's
feast must be eaten on a banana leaf!

266
00:14:38,086 --> 00:14:40,881 
It's really embarrassing when you talk
about yourself in the third person, Dad!

267
00:14:42,382 --> 00:14:43,383 
Hello!

268
00:14:43,425 --> 00:14:44,760 
Give me your phone, Mom.

269
00:14:44,760 --> 00:14:46,345 
How's your uncle keeping, Indu?

270
00:14:46,345 --> 00:14:48,555 
He's doing well overall.
Only his leg is giving him some trouble.

271
00:14:48,847 --> 00:14:50,098 
Hey, do you need a towel?

272
00:14:50,140 --> 00:14:51,517 
No need. I showered
before I came.

273
00:14:51,558 --> 00:14:53,268 
- I'm heading to the temple pond.
- Okay.

274
00:14:53,936 --> 00:14:54,978 
Looking handsome!

275
00:14:56,063 --> 00:14:57,189 
What's on Aunty's mobile phone?

276
00:14:57,648 --> 00:14:59,399 
I just checked Anagha's WhatsApp status.

277
00:14:59,983 --> 00:15:01,151 
I can't see it.

278
00:15:01,276 --> 00:15:02,694 
She blocked me
after we broke up.

279
00:15:02,778 --> 00:15:04,571 
- Aren't you ashamed?
- Why should I be?

280
00:15:04,947 --> 00:15:06,740 
It's not like I'm bothering her.

281
00:15:07,157 --> 00:15:08,450 
Even if we're out
in the semifinals,

282
00:15:08,700 --> 00:15:10,202 
we still need to know
who wins the cup, right?

283
00:15:10,202 --> 00:15:11,370 
And don't step on the snake.

284
00:15:12,412 --> 00:15:13,539 
- What?
- What?

285
00:15:13,580 --> 00:15:14,832 
Ugh! Aren't you ashamed?

286
00:15:21,213 --> 00:15:22,464 
- Rupe...
- Yeah?

287
00:15:22,673 --> 00:15:23,882 
Do you know of any jobs

288
00:15:23,966 --> 00:15:26,718 
that could help me get by
for the next couple of months?

289
00:15:28,679 --> 00:15:30,472 
There are many options
in my dad's line of work.

290
00:15:30,931 --> 00:15:32,391 
Would you be willing
to serve at feasts?

291
00:15:32,641 --> 00:15:34,893 
No, that won't suit me.
Too many people, too much noise...

292
00:15:35,394 --> 00:15:36,770 
Do you know
how to grate coconuts?

293
00:15:36,895 --> 00:15:38,272 
How about chopping vegetables?

294
00:15:38,480 --> 00:15:40,816 
No way! If I hurt my hand,
I won't be able to play the guitar.

295
00:15:42,526 --> 00:15:44,194 
Why don't you just
work as my assistant?

296
00:15:44,903 --> 00:15:45,904 
As a priest's assistant?

297
00:15:45,946 --> 00:15:46,947 
That's not happening.

298
00:15:46,989 --> 00:15:50,075 
Didn't you and your brother Deepu
study the Vedas properly together?

299
00:15:50,534 --> 00:15:52,911 
Even after all this time,
I haven't learned as much as you.

300
00:15:53,203 --> 00:15:54,705 
But I'm still able
to keep it going, right?

301
00:15:54,997 --> 00:15:56,248 
But that was ages ago.

302
00:15:56,748 --> 00:15:59,501 
I'm not really convinced about
this whole "God" concept anymore.

303
00:15:59,918 --> 00:16:02,504 
In that case, are you certain
we'll even be alive tomorrow?

304
00:16:02,921 --> 00:16:04,631 
That just comes down to luck.

305
00:16:05,215 --> 00:16:06,967 
So why not treat
that luck as God?

306
00:16:08,635 --> 00:16:10,512 
Hey, tell them to buy it
only if they really need it!

307
00:16:13,307 --> 00:16:15,100 
[in Hindi]
Bhai, this is quality stuff.

308
00:16:15,684 --> 00:16:16,894 
Hey, where are
those guys headed?

309
00:16:17,394 --> 00:16:18,770 
This has been going on
for a week.

310
00:16:18,770 --> 00:16:20,439 
No fire, no smoke.

311
00:16:20,981 --> 00:16:22,524 
Must be hardcore stuff!

312
00:16:22,649 --> 00:16:24,359 
Here? With me around?

313
00:16:24,359 --> 00:16:25,402 
How dare they!

314
00:16:25,444 --> 00:16:27,946 
- Rupe...
- I'm not the same Rupa anymore. Move!

315
00:16:27,946 --> 00:16:30,032 
Rupe, drop it!
You'll land in trouble!

316
00:16:30,199 --> 00:16:31,366 
This is common everywhere!

317
00:16:31,408 --> 00:16:32,451 
Just zip it!

318
00:16:32,451 --> 00:16:33,452 
Hey! Hey!

319
00:16:34,536 --> 00:16:35,954 
Who are you guys? Huh?

320
00:16:36,538 --> 00:16:37,539 
What's going on here?

321
00:16:37,998 --> 00:16:39,291 
Go on! Go home!

322
00:16:39,291 --> 00:16:40,292 
Clear out!

323
00:16:40,334 --> 00:16:41,502 
Want me to call the cops?

324
00:16:42,002 --> 00:16:43,295 
[In Hindi]
Go, go! Go home!

325
00:16:43,670 --> 00:16:45,005 
Say something, man.

326
00:16:46,215 --> 00:16:47,382 
Who the hell are you guys?

327
00:16:47,591 --> 00:16:50,385 
Look at those jeans,
that bag, that chain!

328
00:16:50,636 --> 00:16:52,804 
You better cut that hair
and beard tomorrow!

329
00:16:54,723 --> 00:16:56,266 
Just chase this pest away.

330
00:16:59,102 --> 00:17:00,103 
Scared?

331
00:17:00,854 --> 00:17:02,439 
Me? What for?

332
00:17:04,233 --> 00:17:05,234 
Oh no!

333
00:17:06,568 --> 00:17:07,653 
No, child!
Don't do that!

334
00:17:07,653 --> 00:17:08,654 
I said don't!

335
00:17:09,404 --> 00:17:10,405 
Oh, Goddess!

336
00:17:10,531 --> 00:17:11,949 
Don't! Oh, Goddess!

337
00:17:11,949 --> 00:17:13,534 
- Run!
- I am running!

338
00:17:14,243 --> 00:17:15,369 
That child has such perfect aim!

339
00:17:17,079 --> 00:17:18,956 
Indu, I am coming!

340
00:17:19,039 --> 00:17:20,666 
Take the soap and towel with you.

341
00:17:23,252 --> 00:17:24,253 
Okay.

342
00:17:38,934 --> 00:17:40,853 
Chetta, that was awesome!

343
00:17:41,019 --> 00:17:42,771 
You elevated the song
to the next level.

344
00:17:42,771 --> 00:17:44,106 
It's all because of
the Goddess's grace!

345
00:17:44,147 --> 00:17:45,566 
- Right, chetta?
- Yes, yes.

346
00:17:45,774 --> 00:17:47,734 
Can I just GPay you?

347
00:17:51,947 --> 00:17:53,198 
You don't have cash?

348
00:17:53,824 --> 00:17:55,200 
Err... Sanaletta...

349
00:17:55,242 --> 00:17:57,327 
We don't have cash.
It'll be credited to your account.

350
00:17:57,411 --> 00:17:58,453 
Don't worry.

351
00:17:58,495 --> 00:17:59,496 
Nice work.

352
00:18:00,747 --> 00:18:01,832 
Psst... Psst!

353
00:18:05,294 --> 00:18:06,795 
I've told you so many times

354
00:18:06,795 --> 00:18:08,839 
not to call me for these
low-budget music albums.

355
00:18:09,256 --> 00:18:10,257 
Oh, I see!

356
00:18:10,299 --> 00:18:12,050 
You said I should call you
even for a Rs.1000 job.

357
00:18:12,092 --> 00:18:13,385 
This one pays Rs.2500.

358
00:18:13,510 --> 00:18:15,470 
- Then where is it?
- It'll come when it comes.

359
00:18:16,221 --> 00:18:18,640 
I barely have money
to get home, Faizal.

360
00:18:19,016 --> 00:18:20,392 
Don't get stressed, Prabha.

361
00:18:20,392 --> 00:18:22,311 
Money comes today,
goes tomorrow.

362
00:18:22,936 --> 00:18:24,605 
How can it go tomorrow
if it hasn't come today?!

363
00:18:25,439 --> 00:18:26,899 
You know the composer
Viraj Trivedi, right?

364
00:18:26,940 --> 00:18:29,568 
He's looking for new
electric guitarists from Kerala.

365
00:18:29,860 --> 00:18:31,695 
There's a new Malayali girl
in his management team.

366
00:18:31,737 --> 00:18:32,821 
That's where this came from.

367
00:18:33,363 --> 00:18:35,657 
Remember the session
you did for Justin?

368
00:18:35,991 --> 00:18:37,367 
I've already sent it to them!

369
00:18:37,826 --> 00:18:40,329 
All his movie and stage-show teams
are from Mumbai.

370
00:18:40,370 --> 00:18:41,371 
Photo! Photo!

371
00:18:41,914 --> 00:18:43,624 
But it's worth a shot, right?

372
00:18:43,874 --> 00:18:46,168 
- What?
- I said, we can try!

373
00:18:46,335 --> 00:18:47,336 
Okay.

374
00:18:49,004 --> 00:18:50,797 
Is this to check your oxygen level?

375
00:18:50,923 --> 00:18:52,841 
It's for credit card verification.

376
00:18:53,509 --> 00:18:55,385 
- Want one?
- No, no! It's too stressful!

377
00:18:55,427 --> 00:18:57,721 
You can withdraw up to
Rs.60,000 per month, sir.

378
00:18:58,096 --> 00:18:59,139 
- Really?
- Yes.

379
00:18:59,181 --> 00:19:00,641 
Hell yeah!
Bro, get him one.

380
00:19:01,350 --> 00:19:02,518 
What do you do for a living, sir?

381
00:19:02,559 --> 00:19:03,560 
I'm a musician.

382
00:19:03,602 --> 00:19:05,145 
Oh, then you'll definitely be rejected.

383
00:19:05,354 --> 00:19:06,396 
- Huh?!
- Sign here.

384
00:19:07,940 --> 00:19:08,982 
Sir, one photo.

385
00:19:09,942 --> 00:19:10,943 
Don't smile so much.

386
00:19:16,990 --> 00:19:18,116 
Bro!

387
00:19:18,367 --> 00:19:19,660 
You got Rs.200?

388
00:19:19,993 --> 00:19:21,787 
I went to Ernakulam yesterday
and came back with nothing.

389
00:19:21,829 --> 00:19:22,996 
There's zero stock!

390
00:19:23,038 --> 00:19:24,456 
How would I have money?!

391
00:19:24,706 --> 00:19:26,333 
Why don't you just ask your dad?

392
00:19:26,458 --> 00:19:28,126 
Me? Ask him?

393
00:19:28,585 --> 00:19:29,962 
Not in this lifetime!

394
00:19:35,926 --> 00:19:36,927 
What is it?

395
00:19:38,345 --> 00:19:39,346 
Never mind, it's fine.

396
00:19:39,763 --> 00:19:40,764 
Who is fine? Me?

397
00:19:41,640 --> 00:19:42,641 
Well, not that...

398
00:19:43,725 --> 00:19:45,477 
If you have something to say,
just say it.

399
00:19:46,061 --> 00:19:47,020 
Do you have change?

400
00:19:47,271 --> 00:19:48,230 
How much for?

401
00:19:49,523 --> 00:19:51,775 
For... errr... two hundred.

402
00:19:51,775 --> 00:19:53,110 
Will two hundreds work?

403
00:19:53,944 --> 00:19:55,529 
A single 200 rupee note
is also fine.

404
00:19:55,737 --> 00:19:57,656 
Then that isn't really
"change," is it?

405
00:20:00,826 --> 00:20:01,869 
Why do you need it?

406
00:20:02,911 --> 00:20:04,246 
Just to step out for a while.

407
00:20:04,413 --> 00:20:06,165 
Then why don't you just...
step out?

408
00:20:07,749 --> 00:20:09,209 
I was thinking
I'd get a tea as well.

409
00:20:09,293 --> 00:20:10,294 
Oh...

410
00:20:11,044 --> 00:20:12,296 
- One minute.
- Okay.

411
00:20:17,885 --> 00:20:19,386 
You recognise us, don't you?

412
00:20:20,429 --> 00:20:21,471 
Of course!

413
00:20:22,306 --> 00:20:23,974 
I remember seeing your daughter
when she was very young.

414
00:20:23,974 --> 00:20:24,975 
She's grown up so much!

415
00:20:25,475 --> 00:20:27,394 
Oh no, she's just my neighbour.

416
00:20:27,394 --> 00:20:28,729 
When I told her
we were coming here,

417
00:20:28,770 --> 00:20:30,272 
she came along
to see your ancestral house.

418
00:20:30,772 --> 00:20:31,773 
Yeah, yeah.

419
00:20:33,108 --> 00:20:34,109 
Oh, sorry!

420
00:20:34,443 --> 00:20:35,736 
You both have a son, right?

421
00:20:36,236 --> 00:20:37,487 
This is my brother.

422
00:20:37,487 --> 00:20:38,864 
My husband is in Qatar.

423
00:20:42,534 --> 00:20:43,660 
It's okay.
Don't worry.

424
00:20:46,371 --> 00:20:47,372 
Here you go.

425
00:20:47,915 --> 00:20:49,458 
There's enough tea
for three cups.

426
00:20:49,791 --> 00:20:51,877 
Help yourself
whenever you want.

427
00:20:52,461 --> 00:20:53,462 
Okay?

428
00:20:55,339 --> 00:20:58,091 
Back in our day, if Father knew
I drank tea from outside,

429
00:20:58,133 --> 00:20:59,510 
I'd get beaten instantly.

430
00:20:59,801 --> 00:21:02,137 
Kids these days...

431
00:21:02,387 --> 00:21:03,430 
they are just different.

432
00:21:05,432 --> 00:21:06,642 
That was funny!

433
00:21:06,808 --> 00:21:09,394 
Weren't you the first one
to gain fame here, Prahladan Namboothiri?

434
00:21:09,394 --> 00:21:11,522 
Even my father
started off as your assistant, right?

435
00:21:11,605 --> 00:21:12,606 
So what?

436
00:21:12,898 --> 00:21:15,234 
How do you put up with Dad's
attitude and still stay here?

437
00:21:15,275 --> 00:21:17,486 
Because I'm very fond of myself.

438
00:21:18,111 --> 00:21:19,112 
Huh?!

439
00:21:19,196 --> 00:21:20,697 
What do we really want in life?

440
00:21:20,989 --> 00:21:24,993 
Someone who loves us dearly,
and takes good care of us.

441
00:21:25,244 --> 00:21:26,245 
Right?

442
00:21:26,954 --> 00:21:27,955 
Yes.

443
00:21:27,996 --> 00:21:29,581 
Why can't I be that person?

444
00:21:29,915 --> 00:21:31,834 
I love myself dearly.

445
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:33,627 
And I take very good care of myself.

446
00:21:33,836 --> 00:21:35,379 
You don't care about anyone but yourself!

447
00:21:35,462 --> 00:21:36,922 
You have no idea what
I'm going through!

448
00:21:39,591 --> 00:21:42,594 
[quotes a sloka from the Mahabharata]

449
00:21:45,264 --> 00:21:46,265 
What comes next?

450
00:21:46,765 --> 00:21:48,767 
Say it out loud.
Don't you know this sloka?

451
00:21:54,940 --> 00:21:56,191 
What does it mean?

452
00:21:59,194 --> 00:22:00,904 
No crisis can take away
your ability to think.

453
00:22:01,905 --> 00:22:04,199 
If you apply that ability,
wealth can be earned again.

454
00:22:04,324 --> 00:22:05,325 
Simple.

455
00:22:05,576 --> 00:22:06,785 
That's it.

456
00:22:06,910 --> 00:22:08,453 
Now go on, earn.

457
00:22:18,839 --> 00:22:19,840 
Aunty, where's Rupesh?

458
00:22:19,840 --> 00:22:21,175 
He's bathing in our pond.

459
00:22:21,383 --> 00:22:23,677 
I don't know why...
He's stopped going to the temple pond.

460
00:22:27,764 --> 00:22:28,765 
Rupe...

461
00:22:29,183 --> 00:22:30,225 
Yeah?

462
00:22:31,393 --> 00:22:32,394 
I'm ready.

463
00:22:32,519 --> 00:22:33,520 
Ready for what?

464
00:22:33,812 --> 00:22:36,231 
I'm ready to put on
the sacred thread

465
00:22:37,065 --> 00:22:38,233 
and perform pujas.

466
00:23:02,174 --> 00:23:04,259 
~ The crystal-clear star
in the heavens so bright ~

467
00:23:04,301 --> 00:23:06,678 
~ It's holding its solemn vigil
in worshipful light ~

468
00:23:06,970 --> 00:23:09,014 
~ To the tune of the soft chant
in gentle sway ~

469
00:23:09,056 --> 00:23:11,475 
~ That blooms on the tongue's tip
in a blossoming way ~

470
00:23:11,808 --> 00:23:13,894 
~ Within the realm of fading memories
that drift like shade ~

471
00:23:13,894 --> 00:23:16,230 
~ The Vedas endure,
refusing to fade ~

472
00:23:16,522 --> 00:23:18,565 
~ Counting them one by one
as patterns shift ~

473
00:23:18,607 --> 00:23:20,984 
~ Habits change,
letting the unwanted drift ~

474
00:23:21,318 --> 00:23:25,781 
~ Not seeing with the outer eyes,
perceiving where the inner soul lies ~

475
00:23:26,156 --> 00:23:30,577 
~ Without seeking the safety
of faith's embrace ~

476
00:23:30,994 --> 00:23:35,707 
~ On the stylus tip where thought arises,
what counts as truth, what slips as lies ~

477
00:23:35,749 --> 00:23:40,212 
~ Don't worry about any of that today,
Just turn to yourself, be yourself your way ~

478
00:23:49,847 --> 00:23:53,851 
[Everything is a Delusion]

479
00:23:59,773 --> 00:24:01,817 
~ The crystal-clear star
in the heavens so bright ~

480
00:24:01,859 --> 00:24:04,236 
~ It's holding its solemn vigil
in worshipful light ~

481
00:24:04,528 --> 00:24:06,613 
~ To the tune of the soft chant
in gentle sway ~

482
00:24:06,655 --> 00:24:09,074 
~ That blooms on the tongue's tip
in a blossoming way ~

483
00:24:09,366 --> 00:24:11,451 
~ Within the realm of fading memories
that drift like shade ~

484
00:24:11,451 --> 00:24:13,537 
~ The Vedas endure,
refusing to fade ~

485
00:24:14,163 --> 00:24:16,206 
~ Counting them one by one
as patterns shift ~

486
00:24:16,248 --> 00:24:18,625 
~ Habits change,
letting the unwanted drift ~

487
00:24:33,473 --> 00:24:37,853 
~ In some distant sanctuary
set high in the sky ~

488
00:24:38,270 --> 00:24:42,649 
~ Who is there above us
to whom we must bow or comply? ~

489
00:24:43,066 --> 00:24:47,321 
~ Is any light greater,
any radiance akin ~

490
00:24:47,696 --> 00:24:50,240 
~ Than the fire that blazes brightly,
fiercely within? ~

491
00:24:50,240 --> 00:24:51,950 
Seriously? Lighting a match
in a fireworks shop?

492
00:24:52,201 --> 00:24:54,495 
~ This is the start,
the time to prepare with heart... ~

493
00:24:54,536 --> 00:24:56,705 
~ We must seize the battlefield,
whatever it costs ~

494
00:24:57,080 --> 00:24:59,208 
~ We must loosen the tangles,
undo all the knots... ~

495
00:24:59,249 --> 00:25:01,502 
~ We must chant the mantra fearlessly,
and must rise to our victory ~

496
00:25:02,169 --> 00:25:06,298 
~ Let us move forward,
ahead of the rest ~

497
00:25:06,632 --> 00:25:11,053 
~ By your own true being,
Blaze forth as lightning at its best ~

498
00:25:11,762 --> 00:25:16,308 
~ As time's own phases onward glide,
as your rituals flow in a faithful tide ~

499
00:25:16,558 --> 00:25:21,021 
~ As your deeds take form on life's broad shelf,
discover yourself within your self ~

500
00:25:30,948 --> 00:25:33,033 
~ The crystal-clear star
in the heavens so bright ~

501
00:25:33,075 --> 00:25:35,452 
~ It's holding its solemn vigil
in worshipful light ~

502
00:25:35,744 --> 00:25:37,788 
~ To the tune of the soft chant
in gentle sway ~

503
00:25:37,830 --> 00:25:40,249 
~ That blooms on the tongue's tip
in a blossoming way ~

504
00:25:44,127 --> 00:25:45,420 
- Indu...
- Yeah?

505
00:25:45,587 --> 00:25:46,880 
I just noticed something.

506
00:25:46,880 --> 00:25:48,507 
Has your accent changed slightly?

507
00:25:48,632 --> 00:25:50,092 
- Is that what has come to pass?
- Yes!

508
00:25:50,175 --> 00:25:51,593 
Exactly!
That's our traditional accent.

509
00:25:51,593 --> 00:25:53,053 
Does that really matter?

510
00:25:54,137 --> 00:25:55,973 
Priest, breakfast is ready.

511
00:25:56,098 --> 00:25:57,933 
- Please have it before you leave.
- Is that so?

512
00:25:58,392 --> 00:26:00,477 
- Can't we just eat at home later?
- There's only Upma at home.

513
00:26:01,019 --> 00:26:02,729 
It's masala dosa here.
I'll be right back.

514
00:26:03,021 --> 00:26:04,022 
Oh dear...

515
00:26:04,815 --> 00:26:05,858 
Five, six...

516
00:26:05,899 --> 00:26:07,568 
6 x 5 = 36...
It's okay.

517
00:26:07,985 --> 00:26:08,861 
Move.

518
00:26:08,902 --> 00:26:10,112 
This looks good!

519
00:26:10,112 --> 00:26:11,697 
- Did you make this, Paulose?
- Yes.

520
00:26:11,905 --> 00:26:12,948 
- Is it made of teak?
- Yes.

521
00:26:12,948 --> 00:26:14,616 
Paulose insists it's teak.

522
00:26:14,741 --> 00:26:16,076 
Then it must've cost a lot.

523
00:26:16,118 --> 00:26:18,287 
Anything Paulose builds
never comes cheap, right?

524
00:26:18,495 --> 00:26:19,746 
I just hope it's sturdy enough.

525
00:26:19,788 --> 00:26:21,748 
It's sturdier than
the wig on your head.

526
00:26:21,832 --> 00:26:23,959 
Better hold on to it.
Don't let it fly away.

527
00:26:24,334 --> 00:26:26,545 
How many people can
sit on this, Paulose?

528
00:26:26,545 --> 00:26:29,715 
It won't move an inch
even if the whole village sits on it.

529
00:26:29,715 --> 00:26:31,466 
Stop exaggerating, Paulose!

530
00:26:31,592 --> 00:26:32,968 
Me? Exaggerating?

531
00:26:33,218 --> 00:26:34,219 
Please step aside, sir.

532
00:26:34,428 --> 00:26:35,596 
I'll prove it now!

533
00:26:35,679 --> 00:26:36,680 
All of you, move aside.

534
00:26:36,972 --> 00:26:38,015 
Come here, son.

535
00:26:38,182 --> 00:26:39,224 
You sit there.

536
00:26:39,391 --> 00:26:40,684 
All you kids,
go and sit.

537
00:26:40,767 --> 00:26:42,186 
Go sit, Chechi.
Go on.

538
00:26:42,561 --> 00:26:43,937 
Come on, everyone.
Come and sit.

539
00:26:44,605 --> 00:26:46,315 
- What? You want to sit, Priest?
- No, no.

540
00:26:46,440 --> 00:26:47,858 
Please sit.
It'll be an honour.

541
00:26:47,941 --> 00:26:49,151 
Move aside.
Let the priest sit.

542
00:26:49,193 --> 00:26:50,527 
- No, really...
- Go on, sit.

543
00:26:50,944 --> 00:26:51,987 
How about now?

544
00:26:52,029 --> 00:26:53,947 
Call your dad or mom,
whoever's around.

545
00:26:54,198 --> 00:26:55,407 
Let them try swinging on it.

546
00:26:57,534 --> 00:26:58,535 
Psst...

547
00:26:58,660 --> 00:26:59,661 
Coming?

548
00:27:03,832 --> 00:27:05,542 
Come here, big shot!

549
00:27:06,710 --> 00:27:07,669 
Give it a good push!

550
00:27:07,711 --> 00:27:08,504 
Oh my!

551
00:27:08,504 --> 00:27:09,421 
Oh no!

552
00:27:12,758 --> 00:27:14,343 
Nothing to worry!

553
00:27:14,343 --> 00:27:15,511 
The swing is perfectly fine.

554
00:27:18,138 --> 00:27:19,181 
Go on, cry again.

555
00:27:20,641 --> 00:27:21,683 
Shush!

556
00:27:25,395 --> 00:27:26,355 
Move, move!

557
00:27:32,694 --> 00:27:33,695 
Rupe!

558
00:27:37,741 --> 00:27:38,826 
Does it hurt, son?

559
00:27:38,992 --> 00:27:39,993 
Not at all.

560
00:27:40,285 --> 00:27:43,205 
The doctor said the MRI scan showed
nothing wrong with his head.

561
00:27:43,497 --> 00:27:45,249 
Such a waste of money!

562
00:27:45,666 --> 00:27:46,792 
At least the X-ray
was worth it.

563
00:27:46,792 --> 00:27:48,544 
It shows swelling at two spots
on his spine.

564
00:27:49,294 --> 00:27:52,214 
Luckily, with Indu around, all the
pujas you agreed to won't be cancelled.

565
00:27:52,297 --> 00:27:53,298 
- Yes.
- Hmm.

566
00:27:54,258 --> 00:27:55,884 
Now, if you both could step outside.

567
00:27:56,426 --> 00:27:58,428 
I need to talk to Indu in private.

568
00:27:58,679 --> 00:27:59,680 
Go on.

569
00:28:01,014 --> 00:28:02,015 
Go on, Mom!

570
00:28:02,599 --> 00:28:03,600 
Let's go.

571
00:28:09,481 --> 00:28:10,482 
- Indu...
- Yeah?

572
00:28:10,816 --> 00:28:12,568 
Yes, I'm your cousin.

573
00:28:13,151 --> 00:28:14,194 
But now...

574
00:28:14,820 --> 00:28:15,863 
Now what?

575
00:28:15,904 --> 00:28:18,157 
Now I'm your employer too.

576
00:28:18,407 --> 00:28:19,408 
So what?

577
00:28:20,284 --> 00:28:23,078 
You're fully capable
of doing pujas on your own now,

578
00:28:23,704 --> 00:28:25,080 
and making your own money.

579
00:28:25,622 --> 00:28:26,957 
That makes me proud.

580
00:28:27,416 --> 00:28:29,543 
Look, I'm not planning
to do this forever.

581
00:28:29,793 --> 00:28:31,670 
I'll leave once
I'm financially stable.

582
00:28:31,753 --> 00:28:32,880 
Sure, you can leave.

583
00:28:32,921 --> 00:28:34,381 
That's not my point.

584
00:28:34,923 --> 00:28:37,426 
From tomorrow, we split
whatever you earn from the pujas,

585
00:28:37,467 --> 00:28:38,844 
fifty-fifty.

586
00:28:39,094 --> 00:28:40,012 
Huh?!

587
00:28:40,012 --> 00:28:41,054 
But I'm the one
doing the puja!

588
00:28:41,096 --> 00:28:42,931 
And I'm the one
bringing in the clients, right?

589
00:28:42,973 --> 00:28:44,266 
- Rupe!
- Listen, Indu...

590
00:28:44,433 --> 00:28:47,686 
When family and friends
turn into business partners,

591
00:28:47,686 --> 00:28:50,272 
having clarity about financial matters

592
00:28:50,355 --> 00:28:51,899 
can help prevent future conflicts.

593
00:28:52,482 --> 00:28:54,318 
There's no point
spoiling our relationship over it.

594
00:28:54,318 --> 00:28:55,319 
That's all I wanted to say.

595
00:28:58,030 --> 00:28:59,448 
- 60-40.
- Yeah, that's fine. Fine.

596
00:28:59,448 --> 00:29:00,491 
40 is fine, 40 is fine.

597
00:29:01,700 --> 00:29:02,784 
You are happy, right?

598
00:29:26,975 --> 00:29:31,230 
~ It clears up like the sky
in its vast renew ~

599
00:29:31,605 --> 00:29:35,901 
~ It fills like the ocean of milk
breaking through ~

600
00:29:36,401 --> 00:29:40,531 
~ Ascend the chariot of that wisdom
alive within you ~

601
00:29:41,365 --> 00:29:45,452 
~ And continue your journey,
steady and true ~

602
00:29:45,577 --> 00:29:50,082 
~ Every single battle
that comes our way ~

603
00:29:50,374 --> 00:29:54,378 
~ Let us face it with
blazing determination each day ~

604
00:29:55,504 --> 00:30:00,008 
~ On the stylus tip where thought arises,
what counts as truth, what slips as lies ~

605
00:30:00,300 --> 00:30:04,805 
~ Don't worry about any of that today,
Just turn to yourself, be yourself your way ~

606
00:30:14,648 --> 00:30:16,733 
~ The crystal-clear star
in the heavens so bright ~

607
00:30:16,775 --> 00:30:19,152 
~ It's holding its solemn vigil
in worshipful light ~

608
00:30:19,444 --> 00:30:21,530 
~ To the tune of the soft chant
in gentle sway ~

609
00:30:21,530 --> 00:30:23,949 
~ That blooms on the tongue's tip
in a blossoming way ~

610
00:30:24,283 --> 00:30:26,368 
~ Within the realm of fading memories
that drift like shade ~

611
00:30:26,368 --> 00:30:28,453 
~ The Vedas endure,
refusing to fade ~

612
00:30:29,079 --> 00:30:31,165 
~ Counting them one by one
as patterns shift ~

613
00:30:31,206 --> 00:30:33,792 
~ Habits change,
letting the unwanted drift ~

614
00:30:42,342 --> 00:30:43,385 
Prabha...
Just a minute.

615
00:30:43,385 --> 00:30:44,553 
- Almost done.
- Okay.

616
00:30:44,887 --> 00:30:45,888 
Hey, Prabha...

617
00:30:46,054 --> 00:30:47,055 
Faizal told me.

618
00:30:47,055 --> 00:30:48,098 
Congrats!

619
00:30:48,098 --> 00:30:49,892 
Don't forget us
when you make it big in Bombay!

620
00:30:49,933 --> 00:30:51,351 
Oh, come on!

621
00:30:54,813 --> 00:30:55,814 
Hey...

622
00:30:55,814 --> 00:30:58,483 
I've sent you a
request on Instagram.

623
00:30:59,568 --> 00:31:00,861 
I'm not very active on it.

624
00:31:01,028 --> 00:31:02,446 
Well, you can just accept it
right now.

625
00:31:05,282 --> 00:31:06,450 
Oh... just a minute.

626
00:31:09,620 --> 00:31:10,621 
Hey, Rupe...

627
00:31:10,621 --> 00:31:12,164 
Indu, where are you?

628
00:31:12,414 --> 00:31:15,542 
Remember I told you about
Viraj Trivedi, the Hindi music director?

629
00:31:15,751 --> 00:31:17,753 
He loved the track
I sent him.

630
00:31:18,086 --> 00:31:20,255 
He has called me to the studio
for a video call session.

631
00:31:20,506 --> 00:31:22,299 
Wow, congrats!
That's amazing!

632
00:31:22,633 --> 00:31:24,384 
What are you doing
tomorrow evening?

633
00:31:24,510 --> 00:31:26,803 
I've got a Ganesha Puja
at Kadampuzha at dawn.

634
00:31:26,970 --> 00:31:28,805 
I thought I'd watch a movie
later in the evening.

635
00:31:28,805 --> 00:31:30,682 
Ugh! That's a horrible movie!

636
00:31:30,807 --> 00:31:32,351 
But I never told you
which movie it was!

637
00:31:32,643 --> 00:31:33,644 
Oh, you didn't?

638
00:31:34,019 --> 00:31:35,854 
- He didn't!
- Yeah, you didn't.

639
00:31:36,021 --> 00:31:37,022 
Anyway, listen...

640
00:31:37,064 --> 00:31:39,066 
Can you handle
one more puja tomorrow?

641
00:31:39,358 --> 00:31:40,567 
You can go after 6:00 PM.

642
00:31:41,485 --> 00:31:42,486 
The pay is huge!

643
00:31:42,528 --> 00:31:45,489 
The biggest one our astrologer
Krishnanunni has ever given us!

644
00:31:45,614 --> 00:31:46,615 
What kind of puja?

645
00:31:47,115 --> 00:31:48,992 
A lawyer from Palakkad...

646
00:31:49,326 --> 00:31:51,662 
His son who's a 12th grade student,
is said to be possessed.

647
00:31:52,120 --> 00:31:53,914 
He's been seeing and hearing things.

648
00:31:54,373 --> 00:31:56,458 
Rupe, I honestly don't know
anything about exorcisms.

649
00:31:56,542 --> 00:31:58,085 
Hey, I'll walk you through it.

650
00:31:58,168 --> 00:32:02,297 
I'll send you a PDF on WhatsApp
with updated chants and procedures.

651
00:32:02,548 --> 00:32:04,842 
Otherwise, it's the same
Sudarshana Homam setup.

652
00:32:04,883 --> 00:32:07,135 
Just add more fire and flowers
for extra punch.

653
00:32:09,304 --> 00:32:11,765 
Sometimes I wonder why we named
you 'Rupe'. You're obsessed with money.

654
00:32:11,849 --> 00:32:13,225 
How is that my fault?

655
00:32:13,517 --> 00:32:14,518 
Hey... please!

656
00:32:15,102 --> 00:32:16,061 
Alright.

657
00:32:16,103 --> 00:32:17,479 
- And hey, don't forget... 60-40.

658
00:32:17,646 --> 00:32:18,647 
Yeah, okay.

659
00:32:19,606 --> 00:32:20,607 
Hey Prabha...

660
00:32:20,858 --> 00:32:22,276 
Sorry, man. Not today.

661
00:32:22,609 --> 00:32:23,944 
Viraj sir's manager just called.

662
00:32:24,027 --> 00:32:26,280 
He worked through the night
and is sleeping during the day.

663
00:32:27,489 --> 00:32:28,532 
Okay.

664
00:32:29,074 --> 00:32:30,993 
That's fine.
Just keep me posted next time.

665
00:32:31,160 --> 00:32:32,161 
Okay?

666
00:32:32,578 --> 00:32:33,579 
Okay.

667
00:32:35,247 --> 00:32:36,248 
So...

668
00:32:36,290 --> 00:32:38,375 
Can you add my Insta ID now?

669
00:32:38,417 --> 00:32:39,459 
Chokichosky.

670
00:32:39,459 --> 00:32:40,794 
Chokay... I mean, okay.

671
00:32:42,504 --> 00:32:44,131 
[Straight from the heart]

672
00:32:44,256 --> 00:32:46,425 
If you're going for physiotherapy,
use the car.

673
00:32:46,466 --> 00:32:49,386 
Ha! It's such a struggle for me
to climb down into that low car

674
00:32:49,386 --> 00:32:50,596 
and then haul myself back up.

675
00:32:51,013 --> 00:32:52,973 
An auto rickshaw is far
more comfortable.

676
00:32:53,807 --> 00:32:55,559 
Don't you have a puja today?

677
00:32:55,559 --> 00:32:56,602 
Yes.

678
00:32:56,643 --> 00:32:57,895 
- Be careful.
- Okay.

679
00:32:58,812 --> 00:33:01,648 
What, am I supposed
to drive it myself now?

680
00:33:05,360 --> 00:33:07,529 
Hey, what's all this
you've been chopping off?

681
00:33:07,571 --> 00:33:08,780 
Will you destroy all the plants?

682
00:33:08,822 --> 00:33:10,491 
For the plants,
this is just like a haircut.

683
00:33:10,532 --> 00:33:11,658 
They might even
be enjoying it.

684
00:33:11,867 --> 00:33:13,285 
I'm crazy about plants, you know.

685
00:33:13,368 --> 00:33:14,411 
Shall we go?

686
00:33:15,996 --> 00:33:17,039 
Name?

687
00:33:18,207 --> 00:33:19,833 
Hibiscus rosa-sinensis.

688
00:33:19,917 --> 00:33:21,001 
It's also called "China Rose".

689
00:33:21,001 --> 00:33:23,003 
Not that!
What's your name?

690
00:33:23,045 --> 00:33:24,046 
Oh!

691
00:33:24,171 --> 00:33:25,172 
I'm Animon.

692
00:33:25,756 --> 00:33:27,549 
- Ready to go?
- Yeah, let's go.

693
00:33:31,595 --> 00:33:33,722 
Feel free to take the car
when you go for your pujas.

694
00:33:35,182 --> 00:33:37,142 
It's okay.
I'll just go in this auto.

695
00:33:46,985 --> 00:33:48,695 
What puja is happening
so late, sir?

696
00:33:48,695 --> 00:33:49,738 
Is it for the Goddess?

697
00:33:49,905 --> 00:33:51,448 
No! It's an exorcism.

698
00:33:57,996 --> 00:33:59,623 
- Advocate Dileep?
- Yes.

699
00:33:59,706 --> 00:34:00,916 
Rupesh had called.

700
00:34:01,875 --> 00:34:03,502 
Need a hand with your supplies?

701
00:34:03,585 --> 00:34:04,878 
No, it's fine.
I have someone with--

702
00:34:09,216 --> 00:34:10,425 
I'll call the driver.

703
00:34:23,939 --> 00:34:24,940 
Can I keep this here?

704
00:34:24,982 --> 00:34:26,066 
Yes, please.

705
00:34:27,526 --> 00:34:28,902 
Just the grass mat is left, right?

706
00:34:29,027 --> 00:34:30,028 
Yes, that's it.

707
00:34:30,904 --> 00:34:32,614 
- You can bring the boy in 10 minutes.
- Okay.

708
00:34:36,243 --> 00:34:37,244 
Deepthi Chechi!

709
00:34:40,038 --> 00:34:41,081 
Here you go.

710
00:34:41,707 --> 00:34:43,083 
It'll be ready in 10 minutes.

711
00:34:46,170 --> 00:34:47,171 
Alright.

712
00:34:53,969 --> 00:34:55,470 
Do you practice
at the District Court here?

713
00:34:55,512 --> 00:34:56,889 
Yes, for the past two months.

714
00:34:57,389 --> 00:34:59,141 
- I'm from Kuttikkanam.
- I see.

715
00:35:02,436 --> 00:35:03,437 
Whose guitar is that?

716
00:35:03,729 --> 00:35:04,813 
That's Kuttu's.

717
00:35:05,105 --> 00:35:06,440 
Ah... I mean, Avinash.

718
00:35:07,024 --> 00:35:08,275 
He plays really well.

719
00:35:08,400 --> 00:35:11,320 
He always says,
"I'm hungry, Latha Chechi."

720
00:35:11,445 --> 00:35:12,696 
Now, he has zero appetite.

721
00:35:13,989 --> 00:35:15,032 
Oh.

722
00:35:15,073 --> 00:35:16,492 
Didn't you take him
to a doctor?

723
00:35:16,533 --> 00:35:18,535 
We did. There's a doctor
at NIMHANS.

724
00:35:18,660 --> 00:35:20,162 
Dr. Raphael.
He's brilliant.

725
00:35:20,704 --> 00:35:21,830 
We consulted him.

726
00:35:21,872 --> 00:35:23,165 
Kuttu is on medication too.

727
00:35:23,457 --> 00:35:26,710 
But my wife insisted
on having this puja done.

728
00:35:26,919 --> 00:35:28,629 
I don't really believe in any of this.

729
00:35:40,891 --> 00:35:41,892 
You can sit.

730
00:35:42,851 --> 00:35:44,478 
Kutta... Sit down, son.

731
00:35:48,148 --> 00:35:49,149 
Sit down.

732
00:35:49,983 --> 00:35:51,109 
You can sit with him, Ma'am.

733
00:35:51,109 --> 00:35:52,402 
That will make him
more comfortable.

734
00:35:53,403 --> 00:35:54,404 
Sit down, son.

735
00:36:00,786 --> 00:36:01,995 
When did all this begin?

736
00:36:02,120 --> 00:36:03,372 
It's been about a week now.

737
00:36:03,789 --> 00:36:06,500 
One night, he walked into our room crying
and lay down beside us.

738
00:36:08,168 --> 00:36:11,129 
He says someone keeps approaching him,
trying to say something.

739
00:36:13,131 --> 00:36:14,299 
A man or a woman?

740
00:36:14,633 --> 00:36:15,759 
It's a young girl.

741
00:36:16,510 --> 00:36:19,179 
Now he needs me with him 24/7.

742
00:36:20,222 --> 00:36:21,598 
Even when he goes
to the bathroom!

743
00:36:25,519 --> 00:36:26,520 
Hello!

744
00:36:29,022 --> 00:36:30,774 
He makes no eye contact at all now.

745
00:36:32,609 --> 00:36:33,610 
I see.

746
00:36:37,364 --> 00:36:38,657 
We're about to begin the puja.

747
00:36:39,283 --> 00:36:41,493 
The spiritual reading suggests
this is a case of possession.

748
00:36:42,536 --> 00:36:43,912 
Once this puja is complete,

749
00:36:43,912 --> 00:36:46,707 
the spirit will leave his body
and merge with the supreme.

750
00:38:05,369 --> 00:38:06,370 
Hi Latha Chechi...

751
00:38:07,120 --> 00:38:08,121 
Huh?

752
00:38:20,133 --> 00:38:22,427 
Kuttu! Oh, my son!

753
00:38:23,470 --> 00:38:24,888 
- Latha, are you seeing this?

754
00:38:25,430 --> 00:38:26,473 
It worked?

755
00:38:26,515 --> 00:38:27,558 
Dileepetta!

756
00:38:27,558 --> 00:38:29,017 
That's not possible!

757
00:38:29,935 --> 00:38:32,646 
- Look, our son!
- Hey, Kuttu! Are you okay?

758
00:38:32,646 --> 00:38:33,689 
Yeah, I am okay.

759
00:38:34,606 --> 00:38:35,607 
Deepthi!

760
00:38:36,024 --> 00:38:37,317 
See? Didn't I tell you?

761
00:38:56,170 --> 00:38:57,171 
- Gho...
- Gho...

762
00:38:57,921 --> 00:38:58,922 
Go on, say it.

763
00:38:59,840 --> 00:39:00,841 
You go ahead.

764
00:39:01,216 --> 00:39:02,593 
The ghost is definitely gone.

765
00:39:03,343 --> 00:39:05,679 
All the chants I sent you
worked like a charm.

766
00:39:05,804 --> 00:39:08,140 
Oh, come on! They had already
consulted a doctor.

767
00:39:08,640 --> 00:39:11,059 
I think the medicine
finally kicked in.

768
00:39:11,977 --> 00:39:12,978 
Oh...

769
00:39:13,395 --> 00:39:18,484 
Still, if that lawyer paid Rs.1 lakh
instead of the Rs.60,000 we asked...

770
00:39:18,901 --> 00:39:20,277 
- Indu...
- What?

771
00:39:21,153 --> 00:39:23,405 
Ever since you started wearing
the sacred thread and doing pujas,

772
00:39:23,447 --> 00:39:25,616 
don't you feel some
kind of divine presence?

773
00:39:26,867 --> 00:39:28,952 
I see this as
a job I'm paid for.

774
00:39:29,286 --> 00:39:31,330 
So shouldn't I just be sincere,
stay disciplined,

775
00:39:31,413 --> 00:39:34,124 
and do the job I was hired for
as honestly as I can?

776
00:39:34,166 --> 00:39:36,543 
- You should.
- That's what this 'presence' means to me.

777
00:39:36,668 --> 00:39:37,711 
Oh.

778
00:39:37,878 --> 00:39:38,921 
I'm leaving.

779
00:39:38,962 --> 00:39:40,797 
And I need a three-day break,
starting day after tomorrow.

780
00:39:40,839 --> 00:39:41,840 
Oh no, no, no!

781
00:39:41,924 --> 00:39:43,425 
I've already scheduled
three pujas for you!

782
00:39:43,467 --> 00:39:45,260 
- Take your break after that.
- No! No way!

783
00:39:45,427 --> 00:39:46,678 
How about 60-40?

784
00:39:47,429 --> 00:39:49,014 
- 70-30.
- Okay.

785
00:39:53,727 --> 00:39:54,895 
Mom, give me your phone.

786
00:39:54,937 --> 00:39:56,438 
She hasn't posted
any status update today!

787
00:39:56,480 --> 00:39:57,481 
Oh.

788
00:40:10,911 --> 00:40:11,995 
Hello?

789
00:40:11,995 --> 00:40:14,748 
There are several types of
silver idols here for today's ritual.

790
00:40:15,290 --> 00:40:16,416 
I've sent you the photos.

791
00:40:16,458 --> 00:40:17,459 
Which one should I get?

792
00:40:17,668 --> 00:40:18,710 
Oh, just a second.

793
00:40:25,425 --> 00:40:26,468 
Get the smallest one.

794
00:40:26,552 --> 00:40:28,095 
Okay, okay.
I'll take this one.

795
00:40:28,470 --> 00:40:31,723 
By the way, who's that Chinese fellow
in your WhatsApp DP?

796
00:40:32,766 --> 00:40:33,767 
Chinese fellow?

797
00:40:43,944 --> 00:40:45,237 
He's a Korean singer.

798
00:40:45,696 --> 00:40:46,989 
Oh, I see.

799
00:40:47,281 --> 00:40:49,241 
For a moment, I thought
I'd called the wrong person.

800
00:40:49,449 --> 00:40:50,826 
- Alright then.
- Okay.

801
00:40:55,581 --> 00:40:56,582 
Thank you.

802
00:40:57,040 --> 00:40:58,041 
Okay.

803
00:41:13,682 --> 00:41:14,683 
Hello.

804
00:41:14,850 --> 00:41:16,059 
You're Prabhendu, aren't you?

805
00:41:16,518 --> 00:41:17,519 
I'm Sreekuttan.

806
00:41:18,020 --> 00:41:19,271 
I used to be
Rupeshettan's assistant.

807
00:41:19,813 --> 00:41:20,814 
Oh!

808
00:41:20,856 --> 00:41:22,441 
Rupeshettan used
to talk about a cousin

809
00:41:22,482 --> 00:41:23,817 
who left home twelve years ago,

810
00:41:24,026 --> 00:41:27,070 
threw away his sacred thread, and has
been wandering around playing the guitar.

811
00:41:28,780 --> 00:41:29,823 
So that's you, huh?

812
00:41:30,699 --> 00:41:32,367 
And on top of that, you're an atheist!

813
00:41:33,368 --> 00:41:34,536 
Good heavens!

814
00:41:35,078 --> 00:41:36,288 
Let's keep this between us.

815
00:41:38,290 --> 00:41:40,959 
So what if I charge a little extra?

816
00:41:41,126 --> 00:41:42,794 
You're better off with me by your side.

817
00:41:43,545 --> 00:41:44,588 
Okay, right?

818
00:41:46,173 --> 00:41:47,382 
Yes, we're okay!

819
00:42:16,328 --> 00:42:17,329 
Oh dear...

820
00:42:18,080 --> 00:42:19,456 
What just happened?

821
00:42:19,873 --> 00:42:21,375 
He must be hurt.
Move, move.

822
00:42:23,502 --> 00:42:25,170 
- Are you hurt?
- You're okay, right?

823
00:42:25,295 --> 00:42:27,381 
- Hello!
- Is he okay?

824
00:42:30,968 --> 00:42:32,177 
Oh Goddess!

825
00:42:33,679 --> 00:42:35,681 
If I've done anything wrong
without meaning to,

826
00:42:36,390 --> 00:42:37,850 
please forgive me, Priest.

827
00:42:39,685 --> 00:42:40,686 
Let's go.

828
00:42:48,277 --> 00:42:49,570 
Chechi, are you Prabhendu?

829
00:42:49,778 --> 00:42:52,030 
- Huh?
- I asked if you're Prabhendu.

830
00:42:52,239 --> 00:42:54,074 
- No. Why?
- I have a parcel for Prabhendu.

831
00:42:54,616 --> 00:42:56,118 
- Give it to me.
- To you?

832
00:42:56,160 --> 00:42:58,162 
- What's the problem?
- Go call Prabhendu Chechi.

833
00:42:58,162 --> 00:42:59,413 
I'll hand it over to her myself.

834
00:42:59,496 --> 00:43:00,831 
Not Chechi.
He's a Chettan.

835
00:43:01,290 --> 00:43:02,708 
- Chettan?
- Yes.

836
00:43:03,417 --> 00:43:04,877 
Alright. Go call him then.

837
00:43:05,169 --> 00:43:06,837 
I'll make sure
the crows don't peck it.

838
00:43:07,713 --> 00:43:08,839 
Wait here.

839
00:43:10,757 --> 00:43:12,301 
There's a parcel for you, Indutty.

840
00:43:14,136 --> 00:43:15,429 
For me?
What could it be?

841
00:43:17,848 --> 00:43:18,974 
I haven't ordered anything!

842
00:43:19,016 --> 00:43:20,184 
Maybe you've got the wrong address.

843
00:43:20,184 --> 00:43:22,644 
Prabhendu N. Namboothiri,
Mullasseri House.

844
00:43:22,686 --> 00:43:23,729 
That's you, right?

845
00:43:23,812 --> 00:43:24,980 
- Yeah.
- Here you go.

846
00:43:28,192 --> 00:43:30,110 
But I don't even have your app
on my phone...

847
00:43:31,278 --> 00:43:32,112 
It's there, right?

848
00:43:32,154 --> 00:43:33,655 
You'll get an OTP.
Can you read it out?

849
00:43:35,157 --> 00:43:37,242 
- 6, 2, 0...
- 6, 2, 0...

850
00:43:37,242 --> 00:43:39,244 
- 4, 0, 9.
- 4, 0, 9.

851
00:43:39,369 --> 00:43:40,996 
- Okay.
- Wait, what about the payment?

852
00:43:41,330 --> 00:43:42,414 
That's already done.

853
00:43:42,956 --> 00:43:44,708 
Payment was through credit card.

854
00:43:45,000 --> 00:43:47,377 
Credit card?
But I never added my credit card to--

855
00:43:48,212 --> 00:43:49,713 
So that's saved too?

856
00:43:50,422 --> 00:43:51,673 
This is clearly a mistake.

857
00:43:52,007 --> 00:43:53,008 
Please return this.

858
00:43:53,050 --> 00:43:54,384 
I can't just take it back.

859
00:43:54,384 --> 00:43:56,178 
I need a return token
from the company.

860
00:43:56,303 --> 00:43:57,554 
That'll take a couple of days.

861
00:43:58,096 --> 00:43:59,598 
I swear, I didn't order this.

862
00:43:59,640 --> 00:44:01,183 
Sir, if you have a complaint,

863
00:44:01,225 --> 00:44:03,894 
take your time
and call customer care.

864
00:44:03,936 --> 00:44:05,354 
That's what they're there for, right?

865
00:44:13,946 --> 00:44:16,281 
What's going on with your phone?
You've been glued to it for a while.

866
00:44:17,491 --> 00:44:21,411 
I'm just deleting some unnecessary apps
from my phone, Uncle.

867
00:44:22,412 --> 00:44:23,997 
The WhatsApp photo keeps
changing on its own!

868
00:44:24,331 --> 00:44:27,626 
It's downloading apps on its own
and ordering clothes with my credit card!

869
00:44:28,293 --> 00:44:30,045 
Must be some Chinese app.

870
00:44:31,922 --> 00:44:32,923 
Did you lose any money?

871
00:44:33,382 --> 00:44:34,383 
Yup.

872
00:44:34,883 --> 00:44:36,176 
I've requested a refund.

873
00:44:36,885 --> 00:44:37,886 
Hopefully it comes through.

874
00:45:22,181 --> 00:45:23,182 
Hi!

875
00:45:27,352 --> 00:45:28,937 
Hey, don't panic.

876
00:45:31,190 --> 00:45:32,441 
I'll go and come back later.

877
00:45:36,320 --> 00:45:37,404 
Bye!

878
00:46:28,622 --> 00:46:30,457 
Why did you sleep here last night?

879
00:46:30,624 --> 00:46:32,042 
What's with this sudden affection?

880
00:46:34,002 --> 00:46:35,712 
I had a dream last night.

881
00:46:36,797 --> 00:46:37,798 
It really shook me.

882
00:46:37,798 --> 00:46:38,882 
Oh!

883
00:46:39,174 --> 00:46:40,217 
There was a girl...

884
00:46:42,010 --> 00:46:43,512 
She was just sitting there, staring at me.

885
00:46:44,555 --> 00:46:45,848 
A very beautiful girl.

886
00:46:46,098 --> 00:46:49,268 
That's a standard dream for bachelors
well past their marriage age.

887
00:46:49,518 --> 00:46:51,395 
Even at my age,
I get such dreams.

888
00:46:51,520 --> 00:46:52,479 
So naturally, you would too!

889
00:46:53,230 --> 00:46:54,356 
This wasn't like that.

890
00:46:54,940 --> 00:46:57,234 
I even heard her voice clearly.

891
00:46:58,402 --> 00:47:00,028 
She said,
"I'll go and come back later."

892
00:47:00,154 --> 00:47:02,489 
This is a 90-year-old
ancestral home, right?

893
00:47:02,656 --> 00:47:04,158 
All sorts of things can show up here.

894
00:47:04,449 --> 00:47:05,450 
Damn!

895
00:47:05,450 --> 00:47:08,579 
I've been available right next
door for all these years,

896
00:47:08,704 --> 00:47:11,248 
and not a single one
ever came to see me!

897
00:47:11,790 --> 00:47:13,500 
Nah, this one seems pretty modern.

898
00:47:14,418 --> 00:47:15,711 
She didn't even try to scare me.

899
00:47:16,086 --> 00:47:17,880 
She was just sitting there casually,
scrolling through my phone.

900
00:47:19,756 --> 00:47:22,301 
Next time you see her,
send her my way.

901
00:47:22,551 --> 00:47:23,969 
At least I'll have some company.

902
00:47:26,388 --> 00:47:29,516 
Hey, call Paul and ask him
to send an autorickshaw.

903
00:47:29,766 --> 00:47:31,476 
I've got a meeting at ten.

904
00:47:32,561 --> 00:47:33,520 
Okay.

905
00:47:38,025 --> 00:47:39,026 
Hi!

906
00:47:39,902 --> 00:47:40,903 
Good morning.

907
00:47:40,903 --> 00:47:42,279 
Please, come in.

908
00:47:43,280 --> 00:47:44,281 
Come on in.

909
00:47:44,740 --> 00:47:46,283 
Kuttoos had an Android phone, you know.

910
00:47:46,492 --> 00:47:48,535 
I was never really
comfortable with Android.

911
00:47:48,827 --> 00:47:51,914 
The fact that you have an iPhone
is such a relief, Prabha!

912
00:47:52,581 --> 00:47:53,832 
Which 'Kuttoos'?

913
00:47:54,374 --> 00:47:56,043 
Remember the puja you did that day?

914
00:47:56,335 --> 00:47:57,419 
What was his real name again?

915
00:47:57,503 --> 00:47:58,879 
Oh... Avinash!

916
00:47:58,879 --> 00:48:00,672 
Gosh, he was such a cutie!

917
00:48:00,923 --> 00:48:02,174 
But scared out of his mind.

918
00:48:02,341 --> 00:48:04,134 
So scared,
he wouldn't even make eye contact!

919
00:48:04,718 --> 00:48:06,929 
How are you supposed to talk to someone
who won't even look at you?

920
00:48:07,554 --> 00:48:08,972 
But you're very brave, Prabha.

921
00:48:09,348 --> 00:48:10,516 
You have good eye contact.

922
00:48:10,516 --> 00:48:12,017 
I like it.
Ten on Ten!

923
00:48:13,143 --> 00:48:14,645 
But you did get scared yesterday.

924
00:48:14,686 --> 00:48:16,063 
It's totally understandable.

925
00:48:16,104 --> 00:48:17,272 
Anyone would have been scared.

926
00:48:17,314 --> 00:48:18,482 
It was your first time, right?

927
00:48:19,608 --> 00:48:21,944 
By the way, is it okay
if I call you Prabha?

928
00:48:21,985 --> 00:48:22,653 
Sure.

929
00:48:22,694 --> 00:48:25,030 
I noticed your friends calling
you that in your chats.

930
00:48:25,989 --> 00:48:27,699 
Also, it's such an interesting name.

931
00:48:28,283 --> 00:48:29,284 
Prabhendu.

932
00:48:29,785 --> 00:48:30,786 
Super sweet.

933
00:48:31,119 --> 00:48:32,162 
I like it.

934
00:48:32,204 --> 00:48:33,539 
- I really like it.
- Indu!

935
00:48:34,122 --> 00:48:35,791 
- I need the auto rickshaw
only at 11 o'clock.

936
00:48:35,833 --> 00:48:37,251 
- I just read the notice.

937
00:48:37,960 --> 00:48:38,961 
Okay!

938
00:48:43,423 --> 00:48:44,925 
Alright, you can have
your phone back now.

939
00:48:45,092 --> 00:48:46,301 
I don't need it again till the night.

940
00:49:04,528 --> 00:49:05,529 
Anxiety?

941
00:49:08,031 --> 00:49:09,032 
Bipolar?

942
00:49:10,117 --> 00:49:11,160 
No.

943
00:49:11,160 --> 00:49:12,286 
Then what on earth is it?

944
00:49:12,494 --> 00:49:13,495 
Huh?!

945
00:49:13,787 --> 00:49:14,788 
I was talking to her.

946
00:49:15,038 --> 00:49:16,039 
It's not dry yet.

947
00:49:16,540 --> 00:49:17,833 
Can you please call Doctor Raphael?

948
00:49:19,293 --> 00:49:20,711 
That's me.
What's the matter?

949
00:49:21,086 --> 00:49:22,379 
So... I'm a person who performs pujas.

950
00:49:22,421 --> 00:49:24,089 
Three days ago,
I went to a house for a puja.

951
00:49:24,089 --> 00:49:25,966 
- Not a house, actually a flat, for puja--
- Stop, Stop!

952
00:49:27,092 --> 00:49:28,343 
Could you please move, Chechi?

953
00:49:29,678 --> 00:49:31,430 
- Continue.
- Like I said, I perform pujas.

954
00:49:31,471 --> 00:49:33,640 
Three days ago,
I went to a flat for a puja.

955
00:49:33,891 --> 00:49:35,100 
It was meant to drive out a spirit.

956
00:49:35,142 --> 00:49:38,520 
His parents said they had
brought him to you, Doctor.

957
00:49:38,896 --> 00:49:40,564 
Avinash.
He's slightly chubby...

958
00:49:40,606 --> 00:49:41,565 
Oh, yes!

959
00:49:41,607 --> 00:49:43,525 
Anyway, after the puja,
he recovered completely.

960
00:49:43,567 --> 00:49:46,445 
But now I'm experiencing
the same symptoms he had.

961
00:49:47,070 --> 00:49:49,156 
I'm seeing the same girl
he said he used to see.

962
00:49:49,573 --> 00:49:52,534 
I saw her last night,
and again today, in broad daylight.

963
00:49:52,826 --> 00:49:54,912 
I could hear her voice too.
Crystal clear.

964
00:49:54,995 --> 00:49:55,996 
Can you see her right now?

965
00:50:00,125 --> 00:50:01,210 
Not right now.

966
00:50:02,127 --> 00:50:03,170 
And?

967
00:50:03,378 --> 00:50:04,379 
Well, that's all.

968
00:50:04,588 --> 00:50:06,548 
Also, the moment I saw that boy,
I understood what the issue was.

969
00:50:06,590 --> 00:50:09,218 
Seeing people who aren't there,
hearing voices nobody else hears...

970
00:50:09,259 --> 00:50:10,302 
Sheezo-phrenia!

971
00:50:10,302 --> 00:50:11,345 
Schizophrenia.

972
00:50:11,386 --> 00:50:13,680 
I Googled it
and I have all the symptoms.

973
00:50:14,264 --> 00:50:15,265 
- You Googled it?
- Yeah.

974
00:50:15,807 --> 00:50:17,309 
I'm willing to take any medication.

975
00:50:17,893 --> 00:50:20,145 
Am I talking too fast right now?
Doctor, are you following me so far?

976
00:50:20,646 --> 00:50:22,648 
Didn't you say you fixed
Avinash's problem with your puja?

977
00:50:22,689 --> 00:50:23,982 
- Yes.
- Then similarly...

978
00:50:24,149 --> 00:50:26,276 
why not perform a puja
and cure your own condition?

979
00:50:27,486 --> 00:50:28,529 
I...

980
00:50:28,612 --> 00:50:30,030 
I don't believe in God, Doctor.

981
00:50:30,197 --> 00:50:31,281 
I'm...

982
00:50:31,323 --> 00:50:32,366 
an atheist.

983
00:50:32,449 --> 00:50:33,242 
Huh?!

984
00:50:33,283 --> 00:50:35,536 
Then how can you be doing pujas?

985
00:50:36,787 --> 00:50:38,038 
Well...

986
00:50:38,080 --> 00:50:39,623 
I'm basically a musician.

987
00:50:39,790 --> 00:50:42,167 
A guitarist.
I'm on a short break right now.

988
00:50:42,417 --> 00:50:44,878 
I was trained in all these rituals
until I turned nineteen.

989
00:50:45,337 --> 00:50:47,256 
When did you begin
losing faith in this "item"?

990
00:50:47,798 --> 00:50:49,091 
Which "item," Doctor?

991
00:50:50,467 --> 00:50:51,468 
God.

992
00:50:54,596 --> 00:50:55,806 
Well... that...

993
00:50:59,017 --> 00:51:00,143 
Come with me.

994
00:51:08,777 --> 00:51:11,405 
One day, it was just my mother
and me at home.

995
00:51:12,364 --> 00:51:15,784 
My brother, father, and uncle
had gone to Delhi for a puja.

996
00:51:17,035 --> 00:51:21,290 
Mom and I were watching
an A.R. Rahman concert on Doordarshan.

997
00:51:22,624 --> 00:51:23,917 
Mom had Master's degree in Music.

998
00:51:23,959 --> 00:51:25,210 
She even played the veena.

999
00:51:27,087 --> 00:51:29,715 
We have a shrine inside the house,
almost like a small temple.

1000
00:51:30,799 --> 00:51:32,885 
When it was time
to do the puja there,

1001
00:51:32,926 --> 00:51:34,469 
I purified myself and went inside.

1002
00:51:34,970 --> 00:51:36,180 
We call it the 'Thevaram'.

1003
00:51:37,264 --> 00:51:39,141 
Just as I lit the lamp
and began the Puja,

1004
00:51:39,600 --> 00:51:41,101 
I heard my mother
calling out to me loudly.

1005
00:51:42,019 --> 00:51:43,187 
I ignored it.

1006
00:51:44,271 --> 00:51:45,772 
I thought I would
finish the puja first.

1007
00:51:46,273 --> 00:51:47,774 
When I went back,

1008
00:51:48,775 --> 00:51:51,236 
I saw my mom lying face down
on the floor, next to the sofa.

1009
00:51:52,863 --> 00:51:54,406 
The moment I held her,
I knew she was gone.

1010
00:51:55,616 --> 00:51:56,909 
It was a cardiac arrest.

1011
00:52:00,746 --> 00:52:02,873 
I held my mom in my lap
and stared right at the lamp,

1012
00:52:03,290 --> 00:52:05,083 
still burning after the puja.

1013
00:52:06,710 --> 00:52:08,170 
I could see it clearly
from where I was.

1014
00:52:09,671 --> 00:52:10,672 
That day,

1015
00:52:10,881 --> 00:52:12,674 
more than sadness,
what I felt was anger.

1016
00:52:14,551 --> 00:52:15,761 
In that moment,

1017
00:52:16,845 --> 00:52:18,347 
I lost my connection with God.

1018
00:52:19,097 --> 00:52:20,933 
Man, this is your real issue!

1019
00:52:21,767 --> 00:52:23,101 
You have deep-seated trauma.

1020
00:52:23,852 --> 00:52:24,853 
No way.

1021
00:52:24,895 --> 00:52:26,688 
Those two things
have nothing to do with each other.

1022
00:52:26,939 --> 00:52:29,399 
Whether they're connected or not,
let's deal with this trauma first.

1023
00:52:30,692 --> 00:52:32,110 
What if that girl
shows up again?

1024
00:52:32,361 --> 00:52:33,362 
Let her show up.

1025
00:52:33,654 --> 00:52:35,113 
She'll go away
the same way she appeared.

1026
00:52:35,405 --> 00:52:36,573 
I'll give you a simple fix for that.

1027
00:52:37,241 --> 00:52:39,117 
There's a tablet
that contains melatonin.

1028
00:52:39,201 --> 00:52:40,369 
It's not a sleeping pill.

1029
00:52:40,619 --> 00:52:42,162 
Just take it
before you go to bed.

1030
00:52:42,412 --> 00:52:43,580 
You will get a good sleep.

1031
00:52:43,580 --> 00:52:44,540 
Huh?

1032
00:52:44,581 --> 00:52:45,958 
Don't I need any other medicine?

1033
00:52:45,958 --> 00:52:48,710 
There's no better medicine in the world
than a good night's sleep.

1034
00:52:48,919 --> 00:52:50,379 
Trust me.
You're fine.

1035
00:53:32,546 --> 00:53:33,547 
Okay.

1036
00:53:37,426 --> 00:53:38,427 
Okay.

1037
00:53:49,313 --> 00:53:50,314 
You are okay!

1038
00:53:55,360 --> 00:53:56,361 
You are okay!

1039
00:54:53,585 --> 00:54:54,628 
Hi!

1040
00:54:55,420 --> 00:54:58,298 
I didn't want to wake you up,
so I just came and sat here quietly.

1041
00:54:58,757 --> 00:55:00,259 
Anyway, I'm glad
I saw you today.

1042
00:55:00,300 --> 00:55:02,344 
Why should we keep
startling each other like this?

1043
00:55:02,469 --> 00:55:04,012 
We're well past that stage now,
aren't we?

1044
00:55:08,058 --> 00:55:09,226 
Whoa! Relax.

1045
00:55:09,560 --> 00:55:11,019 
This isn't a dream.

1046
00:55:11,770 --> 00:55:13,355 
Look, the time is 1:40 AM.

1047
00:55:13,397 --> 00:55:15,649 
Uncle just went to the wash room
and got back in bed.

1048
00:55:15,691 --> 00:55:17,317 
As usual, he didn't flush.

1049
00:55:17,401 --> 00:55:18,402 
Shall I flush it for him?

1050
00:55:18,527 --> 00:55:19,570 
I can do it from here.

1051
00:55:27,077 --> 00:55:28,245 
Shall I turn on the light?

1052
00:55:31,248 --> 00:55:33,375 
Sorry, I'm just figuring this out.

1053
00:55:34,209 --> 00:55:35,586 
You just need to change the bulb.

1054
00:55:35,878 --> 00:55:36,879 
Indu!

1055
00:55:39,131 --> 00:55:40,382 
I think he got up.

1056
00:55:40,757 --> 00:55:42,676 
Tell you what.
You go back to sleep.

1057
00:55:43,010 --> 00:55:44,178 
You've taken the medicine, right?

1058
00:55:44,386 --> 00:55:47,139 
And if you don't mind,
I need to check some stuff on this.

1059
00:55:47,389 --> 00:55:48,682 
I'll return it in the morning.

1060
00:55:53,270 --> 00:55:54,771 
What was that sound?

1061
00:55:57,399 --> 00:55:59,026 
Oh! He can't see me.

1062
00:56:00,611 --> 00:56:01,778 
Your uncle can't see me.

1063
00:56:02,279 --> 00:56:03,280 
Oh!

1064
00:56:03,489 --> 00:56:04,490 
What do you mean, 'Oh'?

1065
00:56:04,907 --> 00:56:06,200 
I asked what that sound was.

1066
00:56:06,450 --> 00:56:07,451 
Oh, that...

1067
00:56:07,826 --> 00:56:09,745 
I think the bulb blew
from a voltage surge.

1068
00:56:09,786 --> 00:56:10,954 
My dear Indu,

1069
00:56:10,954 --> 00:56:12,956 
just say your prayers
and go to sleep.

1070
00:56:13,081 --> 00:56:16,043 
No faith in God,
but scared out of your wits!

1071
00:56:16,460 --> 00:56:17,503 
Ugh!

1072
00:56:23,550 --> 00:56:24,551 
Go back to sleep, Prabha.

1073
00:56:24,801 --> 00:56:26,011 
I'm okay out here.

1074
00:56:26,094 --> 00:56:29,431 
By the way, good call on placing
the return request for the kurta.

1075
00:56:29,556 --> 00:56:31,433 
I ordered the white kurta
with lavender accents.

1076
00:56:31,475 --> 00:56:33,519 
But I think they sent
white with pink instead.

1077
00:56:33,936 --> 00:56:36,814 
Anyway, I've scheduled
the pickup for tomorrow.

1078
00:56:37,105 --> 00:56:38,357 
Just make sure
you hand it over.

1079
00:56:45,948 --> 00:56:47,407 
Is there something
you want to ask me?

1080
00:56:51,078 --> 00:56:52,454 
Finally!
Go on, ask me.

1081
00:56:55,040 --> 00:56:56,041 
Who... are you?

1082
00:57:01,213 --> 00:57:02,548 
I hate to say this.

1083
00:57:04,132 --> 00:57:05,884 
But I think I'm a ghost.

1084
00:57:07,052 --> 00:57:09,304 
Yeah, I think so.

1085
00:57:31,201 --> 00:57:32,202 
Pradeep...

1086
00:57:32,244 --> 00:57:34,371 
July 12th and 13th
are auspicious days.

1087
00:57:34,663 --> 00:57:35,664 
Plan it accordingly.

1088
00:57:35,831 --> 00:57:36,832 
Okay?

1089
00:57:38,167 --> 00:57:39,459 
What are you doing here
at this hour?

1090
00:57:41,295 --> 00:57:42,421 
What's in the bag?

1091
00:57:45,591 --> 00:57:46,800 
Psst... psst!

1092
00:57:46,967 --> 00:57:48,677 
Don't! Don't!
[chants slokas]

1093
00:57:48,760 --> 00:57:49,928 
Psst... psst!
Over here!

1094
00:57:51,430 --> 00:57:52,431 
Where did you see it?

1095
00:57:52,556 --> 00:57:53,640 
In my room.

1096
00:57:53,849 --> 00:57:55,058 
- It's still here.
- Still there?

1097
00:57:55,100 --> 00:57:56,560 
Why didn't you tell me
this when you called?

1098
00:57:56,643 --> 00:57:58,437 
- But my phone is with her!
- Oh.

1099
00:57:58,520 --> 00:57:59,521 
Come on.

1100
00:58:00,772 --> 00:58:01,982 
Will she hurt me?

1101
00:58:03,609 --> 00:58:05,444 
- I don't think so.
- You don't "think" so?

1102
00:58:06,236 --> 00:58:07,571 
Why is this door locked?

1103
00:58:07,863 --> 00:58:09,448 
So she can't get out.

1104
00:58:09,740 --> 00:58:10,741 
Oh.

1105
00:58:10,824 --> 00:58:11,825 
The ghost? Seriously?

1106
00:58:13,243 --> 00:58:14,369 
Open it.

1107
00:58:17,998 --> 00:58:19,416 
And that?
Open that too!

1108
00:58:21,752 --> 00:58:22,794 
She's gone!

1109
00:58:24,129 --> 00:58:25,714 
Didn't I tell you, Indu?

1110
00:58:26,006 --> 00:58:27,716 
It's just your mind playing tricks.

1111
00:58:28,842 --> 00:58:32,095 
The rest will sort itself
out after the puja.

1112
00:58:32,179 --> 00:58:33,388 
You know who's doing it, right?

1113
00:58:34,890 --> 00:58:36,141 
East should be this side, right?

1114
00:58:37,267 --> 00:58:38,393 
- That side.
- Right.

1115
00:58:39,812 --> 00:58:41,230 
No, I'll handle this.

1116
00:58:41,271 --> 00:58:42,356 
Right now, you're the client.

1117
00:58:42,356 --> 00:58:43,440 
- You've got a lamp?
- Yes.

1118
00:58:43,482 --> 00:58:44,733 
Bring it here.
I need to light it.

1119
00:58:44,733 --> 00:58:45,734 
I'll handle that as well.

1120
00:58:47,361 --> 00:58:49,780 
Once you conquer fear,
the battle is half-won...

1121
00:58:49,822 --> 00:58:51,532 
Hey! Where are you off to?

1122
00:58:52,032 --> 00:58:53,200 
You asked me to bring the lamp.

1123
00:58:53,200 --> 00:58:54,660 
Don't go alone.
I'll come with you.

1124
00:59:01,792 --> 00:59:04,044 
Oil, coconut, matches...
Take everything at once.

1125
00:59:04,086 --> 00:59:06,088 
Don't keep going in and
out while I'm inside.

1126
00:59:06,088 --> 00:59:07,130 
It isn't safe.

1127
00:59:07,130 --> 00:59:08,632 
What are you staring at?
Let's go!

1128
00:59:10,217 --> 00:59:11,760 
My god, I've never
seen anyone so scared!

1129
00:59:14,555 --> 00:59:15,556 
Phew! Safe!

1130
00:59:21,603 --> 00:59:24,356 
Uncle, I've come to collect
a parcel for return.

1131
00:59:24,648 --> 00:59:25,732 
What parcel?

1132
00:59:25,941 --> 00:59:27,109 
It's a kurta set.

1133
00:59:27,985 --> 00:59:29,486 
But nobody in this
house wears kurtas.

1134
00:59:29,570 --> 00:59:30,988 
This one is a ladies' kurta.

1135
00:59:30,988 --> 00:59:33,115 
Prabhendu must be your son, right?

1136
00:59:33,448 --> 00:59:35,033 
- Yes.
- Ah, he ordered it.

1137
00:59:36,285 --> 00:59:37,369 
- Here you go.
- Right!

1138
00:59:38,036 --> 00:59:39,496 
Indutty gave it to
me in the morning.

1139
00:59:40,873 --> 00:59:42,666 
Valentine's Day is
around the corner, right?

1140
00:59:42,666 --> 00:59:44,251 
Must be a gift for someone special.

1141
00:59:44,459 --> 00:59:45,794 
Oh dear, this Indutty!

1142
00:59:54,845 --> 00:59:55,846 
Phew!

1143
00:59:56,221 --> 00:59:57,890 
I'm not just saying this
because I did it...

1144
00:59:57,931 --> 00:59:59,641 
- What?
- The puja was a big success.

1145
00:59:59,725 --> 01:00:00,726 
Hmm.

1146
01:00:01,059 --> 01:00:02,436 
That thing you spoke about...

1147
01:00:02,478 --> 01:00:03,479 
She's a real terror.

1148
01:00:03,645 --> 01:00:05,314 
I watched her leave
with my own eyes!

1149
01:00:07,107 --> 01:00:08,108 
Hmm.

1150
01:00:09,067 --> 01:00:11,153 
I'm thinking maybe
I should see that doctor again.

1151
01:00:11,153 --> 01:00:12,362 
Come on!
What for?

1152
01:00:12,404 --> 01:00:13,614 
This is a form of treatment too.

1153
01:00:13,697 --> 01:00:16,658 
This time, I decided to add
a touch of extra sorcery,

1154
01:00:16,658 --> 01:00:17,743 
just for flavour.

1155
01:00:17,784 --> 01:00:18,785 
And it worked perfectly.

1156
01:00:20,746 --> 01:00:21,788 
Why do you look so unconvinced?

1157
01:00:21,830 --> 01:00:23,123 
No, I'm not doubting anything.

1158
01:00:23,123 --> 01:00:24,625 
Alright then! Get up.

1159
01:00:25,000 --> 01:00:26,001 
Oh my...

1160
01:00:26,084 --> 01:00:27,878 
Let me know once you're
done being scared.

1161
01:00:28,712 --> 01:00:30,255 
There are a few pending pujas.

1162
01:00:30,255 --> 01:00:31,507 
Let's wrap those up too.

1163
01:00:32,216 --> 01:00:33,300 
Alright then, I'll get going.

1164
01:00:33,509 --> 01:00:34,760 
- Okay.
- I forgot something.

1165
01:00:34,843 --> 01:00:37,554 
Your father is upset that you
don't visit the temple anymore.

1166
01:00:37,888 --> 01:00:39,014 
At least go once in a while.

1167
01:00:39,014 --> 01:00:40,057 
Poor soul.

1168
01:00:40,057 --> 01:00:41,058 
What are you thinking?

1169
01:00:41,350 --> 01:00:42,351 
That item?

1170
01:00:42,392 --> 01:00:43,477 
She's gone!

1171
01:00:43,477 --> 01:00:44,895 
Chill! Okay?

1172
01:00:45,521 --> 01:00:47,356 
Let me see how she
dares to return now!

1173
01:00:47,606 --> 01:00:48,607 
Okay.

1174
01:00:50,484 --> 01:00:51,527 
Huh!

1175
01:00:51,568 --> 01:00:52,611 
Done getting shocked?

1176
01:00:55,239 --> 01:00:56,323 
Who's he calling an "item"?

1177
01:00:56,365 --> 01:00:57,366 
Do I look like an item?

1178
01:01:13,298 --> 01:01:14,550 
Don't go without talking to me.

1179
01:01:14,758 --> 01:01:16,844 
If you keep running away,
that's all you'll ever do.

1180
01:01:18,053 --> 01:01:21,431 
Listen... have I done anything to you
like those horror-movie ghosts?

1181
01:01:23,851 --> 01:01:24,852 
Yes or no?

1182
01:01:26,395 --> 01:01:27,396 
No.

1183
01:01:27,479 --> 01:01:29,231 
Other than you getting
shocked seeing me

1184
01:01:29,231 --> 01:01:30,691 
and me getting shocked
seeing you,

1185
01:01:30,732 --> 01:01:32,442 
have I troubled you in any way?

1186
01:01:34,653 --> 01:01:35,654 
Yes or no?

1187
01:01:37,156 --> 01:01:38,198 
No.

1188
01:01:38,615 --> 01:01:40,951 
Look, I don't have
clarity on this either.

1189
01:01:41,034 --> 01:01:42,578 
I don't even know what happened to me.

1190
01:01:42,619 --> 01:01:45,289 
And... I have no clue
why I'm following you around

1191
01:01:45,330 --> 01:01:47,124 
as if we're connected
via Bluetooth.

1192
01:01:47,207 --> 01:01:48,750 
Do you even realise
how hard this is for me?

1193
01:01:52,087 --> 01:01:53,088 
Huh?

1194
01:01:54,339 --> 01:01:55,340 
It's just that...

1195
01:01:55,966 --> 01:01:57,092 
you didn't ask yes or no.

1196
01:01:57,968 --> 01:02:00,095 
For the love of Jesus,
don't be scared of me!

1197
01:02:00,387 --> 01:02:01,722 
It makes me feel guilty
for no reason.

1198
01:02:02,514 --> 01:02:03,557 
Jesus?

1199
01:02:04,433 --> 01:02:05,434 
Huh?

1200
01:02:07,478 --> 01:02:08,770 
So, you're a Christian?

1201
01:02:09,688 --> 01:02:10,689 
Oh! Yeah.

1202
01:02:12,399 --> 01:02:13,442 
Oh!!

1203
01:02:15,194 --> 01:02:16,278 
No wonder!

1204
01:02:57,903 --> 01:02:58,946 
Do you sell crosses here?

1205
01:03:00,113 --> 01:03:01,114 
What's the purpose?

1206
01:03:02,241 --> 01:03:03,283 
For...

1207
01:03:03,492 --> 01:03:04,535 
protection.

1208
01:03:04,576 --> 01:03:05,702 
Protection from what?

1209
01:03:06,870 --> 01:03:08,288 
No, no... just general safety.

1210
01:03:08,539 --> 01:03:09,706 
Safety from what exactly?

1211
01:03:09,706 --> 01:03:11,625 
For my own peace of mind, Chetta.

1212
01:03:12,292 --> 01:03:13,293 
Wood or metal?

1213
01:03:14,336 --> 01:03:15,671 
Which one is more powerful?

1214
01:03:15,879 --> 01:03:18,006 
This isn't a lightbulb
you pick by wattage.

1215
01:03:18,715 --> 01:03:20,259 
That depends on your faith.

1216
01:03:20,592 --> 01:03:21,593 
Lali!

1217
01:03:21,677 --> 01:03:22,719 
Yes?

1218
01:03:23,262 --> 01:03:24,555 
Show him the crosses.

1219
01:03:26,265 --> 01:03:27,558 
Are you Roman Catholic?

1220
01:03:29,309 --> 01:03:30,310 
No.

1221
01:03:30,394 --> 01:03:31,812 
Oh, from the Jacobite Church then.

1222
01:03:33,564 --> 01:03:34,857 
Err...

1223
01:03:34,982 --> 01:03:35,983 
No.

1224
01:03:38,527 --> 01:03:39,778 
Mar Thoma church, then?

1225
01:03:41,113 --> 01:03:42,239 
Mar...

1226
01:03:42,948 --> 01:03:43,949 
Yes.

1227
01:03:45,617 --> 01:03:47,244 
- Huh?
- Yes, you're right.

1228
01:03:47,286 --> 01:03:48,704 
Ah, I knew it!

1229
01:03:48,745 --> 01:03:50,497 
The moment I saw you,

1230
01:03:50,539 --> 01:03:52,583 
I knew you were
a proper Mar Thoma boy.

1231
01:03:52,875 --> 01:03:54,209 
- Yes.
- Right.

1232
01:03:54,251 --> 01:03:56,336 
So, pick whichever one
you like. Okay?

1233
01:04:21,653 --> 01:04:23,071 
So, this should clear things up, right?

1234
01:04:25,616 --> 01:04:27,993 
I mean, I'm literally standing
surrounded by crosses right now.

1235
01:04:28,160 --> 01:04:29,161 
Including you.

1236
01:04:30,871 --> 01:04:32,581 
Hey! If Jesus had a problem with me,

1237
01:04:32,623 --> 01:04:34,500 
wouldn't I be gone by now?

1238
01:04:37,044 --> 01:04:38,921 
Look, I honestly don't know
how I became a ghost,

1239
01:04:38,962 --> 01:04:43,133 
or why I am one,
or how to stop being one.

1240
01:04:43,550 --> 01:04:44,927 
And you know
what's the funny part?

1241
01:04:45,052 --> 01:04:47,221 
I can't remember
a single important detail!

1242
01:04:47,596 --> 01:04:49,097 
I can't even recall my name!

1243
01:04:54,061 --> 01:04:55,062 
Answer it.

1244
01:04:59,358 --> 01:05:01,068 
- Faizal...
- Hey, Prabha...

1245
01:05:01,109 --> 01:05:03,904 
Wherever you are, drop everything
and get to the studio by midnight.

1246
01:05:03,904 --> 01:05:05,656 
Viraj sir said he'll
join on a video call.

1247
01:05:05,656 --> 01:05:08,075 
He wants to test you
for a track in his next film.

1248
01:05:08,242 --> 01:05:09,576 
I'm kind of stuck right now.

1249
01:05:10,202 --> 01:05:11,620 
Can we reschedule?

1250
01:05:11,787 --> 01:05:14,414 
Don't be an idiot, Prabha!

1251
01:05:14,915 --> 01:05:16,708 
If you miss this now,
there won't be another chance.

1252
01:05:16,792 --> 01:05:19,294 
I've given Saadhya my word.
Stop stalling and get here.

1253
01:05:19,294 --> 01:05:20,379 
It's 5:00 PM already.

1254
01:05:20,629 --> 01:05:21,630 
- I'll be there.
- Okay.

1255
01:05:26,844 --> 01:05:27,845 
I heard that.

1256
01:05:28,262 --> 01:05:29,304 
Congrats.

1257
01:06:06,633 --> 01:06:08,260 
Ah! Come in, come in.

1258
01:06:11,180 --> 01:06:13,348 
I didn't take the bike,
in case it rained tonight.

1259
01:06:13,474 --> 01:06:15,434 
Caught a direct bus.
It was pretty comfortable.

1260
01:06:15,851 --> 01:06:17,686 
You don't mind me
eating non-veg, do you?

1261
01:06:18,061 --> 01:06:19,021 
Not at all.

1262
01:06:19,146 --> 01:06:20,689 
I think I'll order a dosa.

1263
01:06:20,898 --> 01:06:22,107 
I'll order for you, man.

1264
01:06:22,149 --> 01:06:23,150 
You haven't eaten yet?

1265
01:06:24,234 --> 01:06:25,569 
How about podi masala dosa?

1266
01:06:26,820 --> 01:06:27,821 
Yeah.

1267
01:06:27,863 --> 01:06:29,198 
Who are you looking for?

1268
01:06:29,615 --> 01:06:30,616 
Oh, nothing.

1269
01:06:30,866 --> 01:06:32,659 
I asked if podi masala dosa is okay.

1270
01:06:32,701 --> 01:06:33,702 
Yeah, that's fine.

1271
01:06:35,287 --> 01:06:37,581 
Dude, hold on.
Saadhya's calling.

1272
01:06:38,165 --> 01:06:39,458 
Hello, Saadhya...

1273
01:06:40,792 --> 01:06:41,793 
Yeah.

1274
01:06:41,835 --> 01:06:43,045 
He's logged in already?

1275
01:06:43,045 --> 01:06:44,505 
No, no problem.
We're coming.

1276
01:06:44,588 --> 01:06:46,882 
Dude, Viraj sir has already logged in.

1277
01:06:46,924 --> 01:06:48,050 
Come on, hurry up!

1278
01:06:48,175 --> 01:06:49,176 
What about my dosa?

1279
01:06:49,426 --> 01:06:51,803 
I'm ditching my biriyani, and you're
worried about your dosa? Move!

1280
01:07:08,070 --> 01:07:09,154 
Prabha, ready.

1281
01:07:09,238 --> 01:07:10,364 
He's here.

1282
01:07:10,364 --> 01:07:11,824 
Hi Faizal. All good?

1283
01:07:11,990 --> 01:07:13,951 
Hi, sir. All good, sir.
All good.

1284
01:07:14,243 --> 01:07:17,120 
The guitarist. Is he ready?
What's his name?

1285
01:07:17,454 --> 01:07:19,414 
Prabhendu, sir.
Prabhendu.

1286
01:07:19,498 --> 01:07:20,582 
Shall I call him here, sir?

1287
01:07:20,624 --> 01:07:21,834 
No, no. No need.

1288
01:07:21,875 --> 01:07:23,335 
I can hear what he plays, right?

1289
01:07:23,377 --> 01:07:24,461 
Yeah, of course. Of course.

1290
01:07:24,503 --> 01:07:25,796 
Okay then.
Let's start now.

1291
01:07:27,506 --> 01:07:28,549 
Hey...

1292
01:07:28,715 --> 01:07:30,092 
Sir has composed a new track.

1293
01:07:30,092 --> 01:07:31,218 
He needs a guitar groove for it.

1294
01:07:31,635 --> 01:07:32,636 
Kill it!

1295
01:08:05,085 --> 01:08:07,337 
Faizal, I need a catchy
riff for the melody.

1296
01:08:07,379 --> 01:08:08,380 
Yes, sir. Yes, sir.

1297
01:08:09,256 --> 01:08:10,424 
Prabha... 2-bar cue.

1298
01:08:10,799 --> 01:08:11,800 
Yeah, okay.

1299
01:08:21,518 --> 01:08:22,811 
No, no.
Stop, stop.

1300
01:08:22,853 --> 01:08:25,022 
Prabhendu, I don't want that.

1301
01:08:25,230 --> 01:08:28,025 
It's not sounding good.
Try some strumming.

1302
01:08:30,819 --> 01:08:32,404 
Prabha, don't try anything
too fancy.

1303
01:08:32,446 --> 01:08:33,822 
Just stick to your comfort zone.

1304
01:08:33,822 --> 01:08:34,865 
Okay.

1305
01:08:50,005 --> 01:08:51,173 
No, no, no.

1306
01:08:51,340 --> 01:08:52,799 
What are you doing, man?

1307
01:08:52,966 --> 01:08:55,385 
Feel the melody and try again.

1308
01:08:56,929 --> 01:08:58,347 
Faizal, give him a shorter cue.

1309
01:08:58,514 --> 01:08:59,515 
Sure. Sure, sir.

1310
01:09:00,307 --> 01:09:01,809 
Prabha, what's wrong with you?

1311
01:09:02,309 --> 01:09:03,560 
Let's go. Ready.

1312
01:09:04,144 --> 01:09:05,145 
Okay.

1313
01:09:05,771 --> 01:09:06,730 
Take.

1314
01:09:13,529 --> 01:09:14,571 
Stop, stop, stop.

1315
01:09:14,696 --> 01:09:16,240 
This is not even close!

1316
01:09:16,573 --> 01:09:17,991 
Faizal, what is this?

1317
01:09:17,991 --> 01:09:19,827 
I already have people in Mumbai
who play like this.

1318
01:09:20,077 --> 01:09:21,537 
I want that magic!

1319
01:09:21,578 --> 01:09:24,248 
We shouldn't waste our time.
Let's look for someone else.

1320
01:09:24,331 --> 01:09:25,666 
He just can't do it.

1321
01:09:32,923 --> 01:09:34,383 
Just follow the melody.

1322
01:09:37,261 --> 01:09:38,303 
Huh?!

1323
01:09:41,515 --> 01:09:42,558 
What is it, man?

1324
01:09:43,350 --> 01:09:44,518 
Oh, it's nothing.

1325
01:09:45,477 --> 01:09:46,895 
Prabha, focus only on the melody.

1326
01:09:47,104 --> 01:09:48,105 
It's that simple.

1327
01:09:56,655 --> 01:09:57,656 
Play this.

1328
01:10:00,409 --> 01:10:01,451 
Prabha...

1329
01:10:01,994 --> 01:10:02,995 
What do I do?

1330
01:10:04,830 --> 01:10:06,039 
- Ready.
- Okay, man.

1331
01:10:06,748 --> 01:10:08,375 
Sir... One last time, sir?

1332
01:10:08,959 --> 01:10:10,502 
Okay, try.

1333
01:10:10,711 --> 01:10:12,212 
Okay, sir.
Thank you, thank you.

1334
01:10:12,212 --> 01:10:13,255 
Prabha, take.

1335
01:10:35,694 --> 01:10:37,279 
Oh, nice!
I like it!

1336
01:10:37,488 --> 01:10:39,781 
Faizal, this is exactly what I want!

1337
01:10:39,865 --> 01:10:40,866 
Thank you, sir.

1338
01:10:40,908 --> 01:10:42,618 
Prabha, that's brilliant.
Stick with that.

1339
01:10:44,786 --> 01:10:46,079 
Super. Add one more layer.

1340
01:10:49,500 --> 01:10:51,460 
Faizal, turn up the reverb.

1341
01:10:51,502 --> 01:10:52,503 
I'll add one more layer.

1342
01:10:52,544 --> 01:10:53,629 
Ready!

1343
01:11:02,679 --> 01:11:03,680 
Too good, man!

1344
01:11:04,431 --> 01:11:05,432 
Continue!

1345
01:11:23,450 --> 01:11:24,243 
Too good!

1346
01:11:24,284 --> 01:11:26,245 
Faizal, call him!
I want to see him.

1347
01:11:26,745 --> 01:11:27,788 
Sure, sir.

1348
01:11:27,955 --> 01:11:29,331 
Prabha, come over here.

1349
01:11:29,414 --> 01:11:30,457 
Sir wants to see you.

1350
01:11:38,882 --> 01:11:40,217 
You killed it, man!

1351
01:11:41,301 --> 01:11:43,178 
You just made the tune better,
Prabhendu.

1352
01:11:43,387 --> 01:11:45,264 
We will do the full song together
in Mumbai.

1353
01:11:45,430 --> 01:11:46,431 
Thank you, sir.

1354
01:11:46,515 --> 01:11:47,516 
Perfect!

1355
01:11:47,558 --> 01:11:49,393 
Faizal, I'll ask Saadhya to coordinate.

1356
01:11:49,434 --> 01:11:50,435 
Okay.

1357
01:12:29,266 --> 01:12:30,934 
Your destination is on the left.

1358
01:12:33,729 --> 01:12:34,813 
Hey! Kiddo!

1359
01:12:45,491 --> 01:12:46,492 
Hey, look at that.

1360
01:12:47,701 --> 01:12:49,620 
To be honest,
I didn't quite get that initially.

1361
01:12:50,996 --> 01:12:51,997 
Great!

1362
01:12:53,665 --> 01:12:54,666 
And then?

1363
01:12:54,750 --> 01:12:56,418 
That's exactly what I was thinking.

1364
01:12:56,710 --> 01:12:59,338 
I know music, and I know
how guitar chords work.

1365
01:13:00,380 --> 01:13:01,381 
Oh Jesus!

1366
01:13:01,507 --> 01:13:03,050 
Kuttoos was a guitarist too!

1367
01:13:03,550 --> 01:13:05,052 
Music connects the three of us!

1368
01:13:07,221 --> 01:13:08,222 
Strange!

1369
01:13:08,680 --> 01:13:09,973 
Also, you're an acoustic guy?

1370
01:13:10,974 --> 01:13:12,559 
Electric Guitar is my favourite.

1371
01:13:12,976 --> 01:13:14,812 
But people like Viraj sir

1372
01:13:15,103 --> 01:13:17,981 
usually prefer acoustic
when they're composing.

1373
01:13:17,981 --> 01:13:19,817 
Ah, I see.

1374
01:13:21,360 --> 01:13:23,153 
Looks like you've lost your
fear and found some guts.

1375
01:13:24,196 --> 01:13:25,280 
The fear is gone,

1376
01:13:25,739 --> 01:13:26,990 
but the confusion remains.

1377
01:13:27,491 --> 01:13:28,617 
Just relax, Prabha.

1378
01:13:28,742 --> 01:13:30,285 
I think I'm just delulu.

1379
01:13:30,953 --> 01:13:32,996 
Alright. So, delulu...
Ordering things online--

1380
01:13:34,206 --> 01:13:35,791 
Delulu means delusion.

1381
01:13:36,250 --> 01:13:38,126 
Seeing things that don't exist.

1382
01:13:38,585 --> 01:13:40,295 
What's the Malayalam word
for delusion?

1383
01:13:40,671 --> 01:13:42,506 
The Malayalam word for delusion...

1384
01:13:43,882 --> 01:13:44,883 
"Delulu" works.

1385
01:13:45,300 --> 01:13:46,301 
Actually, it's cute.

1386
01:13:46,593 --> 01:13:48,095 
You can just call me Delulu
from now on.

1387
01:13:49,221 --> 01:13:50,681 
- Delulu!
- Delulu...

1388
01:13:51,265 --> 01:13:53,308 
Can you please stop ordering
all these clothes?

1389
01:13:53,517 --> 01:13:55,102 
I'm a little short on cash right now.

1390
01:13:55,561 --> 01:13:56,895 
Let me explain why, Prabha.

1391
01:13:57,146 --> 01:13:59,189 
I remember every outfit
I used to wear.

1392
01:13:59,565 --> 01:14:01,525 
But my favourite kurti...

1393
01:14:01,525 --> 01:14:03,443 
The white one with
lavender flowers on it...

1394
01:14:03,485 --> 01:14:05,070 
I simply can't wear that one now.

1395
01:14:05,404 --> 01:14:07,906 
So I thought, maybe I
could wear it if I saw it.

1396
01:14:09,241 --> 01:14:10,242 
Oh.

1397
01:14:10,951 --> 01:14:11,952 
Hey...

1398
01:14:12,661 --> 01:14:14,163 
Can you conjure up
a 500 rupee note?

1399
01:14:14,371 --> 01:14:16,790 
Hey! I'm not some genie
you summon from a bottle!

1400
01:14:16,957 --> 01:14:18,959 
I can handle a few simple things.

1401
01:14:19,042 --> 01:14:20,043 
I have some skills.

1402
01:14:20,335 --> 01:14:23,130 
Like last week, when that guy acted smart
with you, and I made his bike crash.

1403
01:14:23,130 --> 01:14:24,173 
Stuff like that.

1404
01:14:24,298 --> 01:14:25,591 
Which guy? Sreekuttan?

1405
01:14:25,716 --> 01:14:26,967 
I don't know his name.

1406
01:14:27,301 --> 01:14:29,094 
Oh my God!!!

1407
01:14:29,636 --> 01:14:31,555 
Oh, sorry!
Not God, not God.

1408
01:14:34,308 --> 01:14:37,144 
Actually, I do remember
certain things about myself.

1409
01:14:37,436 --> 01:14:40,355 
Like my lifestyle, my habits,
my interests.

1410
01:14:41,607 --> 01:14:43,650 
But I can't remember
any of the main things.

1411
01:14:44,568 --> 01:14:45,944 
Like my family,
or my friends...

1412
01:14:46,904 --> 01:14:47,905 
Nothing at all!

1413
01:14:48,822 --> 01:14:49,823 
Except for one thing.

1414
01:14:50,324 --> 01:14:51,366 
What's that?

1415
01:14:51,825 --> 01:14:54,620 
Right before I died,
someone, somewhere, said "Yes."

1416
01:14:55,829 --> 01:14:57,581 
It's like someone wanted me to die.

1417
01:14:58,540 --> 01:14:59,541 
Who was it?

1418
01:15:00,209 --> 01:15:01,210 
I don't know.

1419
01:15:02,169 --> 01:15:04,296 
Well... I meant to say this
back at the studio.

1420
01:15:05,130 --> 01:15:06,673 
You have a beautiful voice, Delulu.

1421
01:15:07,716 --> 01:15:08,717 
You're gifted.

1422
01:15:10,052 --> 01:15:11,428 
If you hadn't died...

1423
01:15:12,137 --> 01:15:13,347 
you would've become a star.

1424
01:15:14,515 --> 01:15:16,767 
Now that I'm dead,
becoming a star is my only option, right?

1425
01:15:44,586 --> 01:15:51,343 
~ When someone sat close to me at night,
like new-fallen rain in cool delight ~

1426
01:15:51,426 --> 01:15:57,015 
~ My heart shifted, lighter than ever,
turning at once to a moonlit river ~

1427
01:15:58,100 --> 01:16:01,603 
~ Slowly unfolding its wings
in tender delight ~

1428
01:16:01,728 --> 01:16:05,107 
~ Weaving a chain of laughter
pure and bright ~

1429
01:16:05,149 --> 01:16:10,696 
~ My mind fills up
on its own tonight ~

1430
01:16:11,947 --> 01:16:17,578 
~ Come, let's go to distances
we've never seen ~

1431
01:16:17,953 --> 01:16:23,959 
~ Becoming two lovely,
colourful clouds serene ~

1432
01:16:24,001 --> 01:16:25,627 
~ In this new birth
where our paths convene ~

1433
01:16:25,669 --> 01:16:31,425 
~ Let's find our shelter on a blossom
branch kissed by morning dew ~

1434
01:16:31,466 --> 01:16:34,887 
~ Becoming the breath
that rises soft and true ~

1435
01:16:35,053 --> 01:16:39,141 
~ Till every painful memory
softens and bids adieu ~

1436
01:17:33,111 --> 01:17:34,112 
Stop!

1437
01:17:37,699 --> 01:17:41,036 
~ From which stretch of sky
did I fall and fly ~

1438
01:17:41,119 --> 01:17:44,540 
~ A lost little star
slipping out of the sky? ~

1439
01:17:44,540 --> 01:17:50,295 
~ Who else must I search for
as days drift by? ~

1440
01:17:51,380 --> 01:17:54,842 
~ I still don't know
the right paths to surmise ~

1441
01:17:54,883 --> 01:17:58,262 
~ Yet I carried a deep desire
for a safe haven's rise ~

1442
01:17:58,303 --> 01:18:04,351 
~ Which lingered as moisture
gently filling my eyes ~

1443
01:18:05,185 --> 01:18:08,272 
~ In all this rush
that surrounds me endlessly ~

1444
01:18:08,480 --> 01:18:11,108 
~ Isn't there someone nearby
who cares for me? ~

1445
01:18:11,108 --> 01:18:15,112 
~ Even at my lightest mischief,
soft and carefree ~

1446
01:18:15,404 --> 01:18:17,781 
~ Doesn't he keep smiling,
happily? ~

1447
01:18:17,823 --> 01:18:25,539 
~ Will you join your hands
and shape a swing? ~

1448
01:18:25,706 --> 01:18:32,546 
~ If you do, I will step forward with joy
and gently begin to swing ~

1449
01:18:32,546 --> 01:18:39,344 
~ When someone sat close to me at night,
like new-fallen rain in cool delight ~

1450
01:18:39,470 --> 01:18:45,058 
~ My heart shifted, lighter than ever,
turning at once to a moonlit river ~

1451
01:18:46,059 --> 01:18:49,521 
~ Slowly unfolding its wings
in tender delight ~

1452
01:18:49,605 --> 01:18:53,066 
~ Weaving a chain of laughter
pure and bright ~

1453
01:18:53,066 --> 01:18:58,655 
~ My mind fills up
on its own tonight ~

1454
01:19:31,313 --> 01:19:32,231 
[Astrologer: Krishnanunni Panicker]

1455
01:19:32,272 --> 01:19:34,942 
So you just want me to visit
the houses you're trying to sell?

1456
01:19:35,567 --> 01:19:36,860 
Not every one of them, Rupe.

1457
01:19:37,194 --> 01:19:38,987 
Only the ones where
unnatural deaths have happened.

1458
01:19:39,363 --> 01:19:42,950 
Yes, houses where notorious murders
have occurred.

1459
01:19:43,116 --> 01:19:44,409 
And suicides.

1460
01:19:44,785 --> 01:19:46,161 
Altogether,

1461
01:19:46,203 --> 01:19:49,623 
I've got nearly 28 such houses
on hold across Kerala.

1462
01:19:50,249 --> 01:19:52,042 
Will one puja take care
of all of them?

1463
01:19:52,042 --> 01:19:54,711 
Not like that. First, I will do
an astrological assessment

1464
01:19:54,753 --> 01:19:56,588 
and then determine
the required remedies.

1465
01:19:56,630 --> 01:19:58,257 
After that, you just have to
carry them out.

1466
01:19:58,340 --> 01:20:00,300 
Your learned cousin is the one

1467
01:20:00,300 --> 01:20:02,386 
who went for the lawyer's
son's puja that day, right?

1468
01:20:02,469 --> 01:20:04,388 
He's very skilled.
It'd be great if he came too.

1469
01:20:04,388 --> 01:20:06,348 
No chance!
Prabhendu works only part-time.

1470
01:20:06,348 --> 01:20:07,724 
He only deals with
cases involving children.

1471
01:20:07,766 --> 01:20:10,227 
Risky cases like these
are handled by me personally.

1472
01:20:10,853 --> 01:20:12,104 
Yes, what is it?

1473
01:20:12,104 --> 01:20:14,148 
I'm looking for the office
of the family court lawyer.

1474
01:20:14,314 --> 01:20:15,524 
Is it a mutual divorce?

1475
01:20:15,607 --> 01:20:17,359 
No. I'm okay with it.

1476
01:20:17,401 --> 01:20:19,027 
But my wife is the one
who wants to end it.

1477
01:20:19,069 --> 01:20:20,779 
That's something
we can resolve right here.

1478
01:20:20,946 --> 01:20:22,531 
Still, go meet the lawyer.

1479
01:20:22,531 --> 01:20:24,074 
- It's the office next door.
- Okay.

1480
01:20:24,616 --> 01:20:26,827 
So, what about the payment?

1481
01:20:27,161 --> 01:20:31,456 
What if there's more than one ghost in
those houses where mass murders occurred?

1482
01:20:32,040 --> 01:20:33,125 
That depends.

1483
01:20:33,167 --> 01:20:35,586 
We'll even leave some
room for you to negotiate.

1484
01:20:37,337 --> 01:20:39,548 
If that's the case... err...

1485
01:20:40,424 --> 01:20:41,758 
a per-head rate for each ghost.

1486
01:20:45,387 --> 01:20:46,388 
- Isn't it okay?
- Okay.

1487
01:20:46,430 --> 01:20:47,347 
Okay!

1488
01:20:47,389 --> 01:20:48,640 
Lord Guruvayurappa!

1489
01:20:51,059 --> 01:20:52,686 
Just hold this
and give it one pull.

1490
01:20:54,563 --> 01:20:55,606 
Wow, this is so easy!

1491
01:20:55,606 --> 01:20:56,732 
Also, no tears wasted.

1492
01:20:56,773 --> 01:20:57,816 
- Thulasi!

1493
01:20:58,984 --> 01:20:59,985 
Your dad!

1494
01:21:01,695 --> 01:21:04,406 
Grab Pappu's blue spray
from the kitchen.

1495
01:21:05,449 --> 01:21:06,909 
Or never mind.
I'll come there.

1496
01:21:07,701 --> 01:21:08,702 
Okay.

1497
01:21:08,702 --> 01:21:09,745 
Indutty...

1498
01:21:10,204 --> 01:21:11,246 
Your dad is coming.

1499
01:21:11,413 --> 01:21:13,332 
Get going. I'll call you
when lunch is ready.

1500
01:21:27,137 --> 01:21:28,847 
Huh?!
You're here?

1501
01:21:29,181 --> 01:21:30,265 
Who is in there then?

1502
01:21:32,726 --> 01:21:35,062 
It... it...
it's from the speaker, Uncle.

1503
01:21:36,647 --> 01:21:38,023 
Then how did it stop now?

1504
01:21:38,232 --> 01:21:39,817 
Oh, really?
Let me check.

1505
01:21:43,654 --> 01:21:46,657 
Hey, don't pull these kinds of stunts
when I'm not around.

1506
01:21:47,699 --> 01:21:48,700 
Sorry!

1507
01:21:51,036 --> 01:21:52,913 
I thought you had grand plans
for cooking today?

1508
01:21:52,996 --> 01:21:55,165 
What happened?
Finished helping her already?

1509
01:21:56,458 --> 01:21:57,876 
Well... it's just...

1510
01:21:59,711 --> 01:22:01,046 
Dad was there with Pappu.

1511
01:22:01,213 --> 01:22:02,381 
So I just came back inside.

1512
01:22:03,257 --> 01:22:05,509 
By the way, why aren't you two
talking to each other?

1513
01:22:05,843 --> 01:22:07,052 
What's the reason?

1514
01:22:07,553 --> 01:22:08,554 
It's because of Pappu.

1515
01:22:09,012 --> 01:22:10,222 
What did Pappu do?

1516
01:22:11,098 --> 01:22:12,099 
Well...

1517
01:22:14,101 --> 01:22:15,394 
The day my mom passed away...

1518
01:22:16,186 --> 01:22:17,146 
everyone was here.

1519
01:22:18,063 --> 01:22:20,190 
It was chaotic,
with all the crying and commotion.

1520
01:22:21,775 --> 01:22:23,235 
When it was time
to take her body away,

1521
01:22:23,569 --> 01:22:25,070 
Pappu suddenly started
barking non-stop.

1522
01:22:26,530 --> 01:22:27,906 
Mom was his favourite person.

1523
01:22:28,740 --> 01:22:30,117 
He was tied up
in the backyard then.

1524
01:22:31,451 --> 01:22:32,953 
So I hurried out
and brought him inside.

1525
01:22:34,705 --> 01:22:36,582 
He deserved to see Mom
one last time, right?

1526
01:22:38,083 --> 01:22:40,752 
The moment Dad saw him,
he shouted,

1527
01:22:41,003 --> 01:22:42,004 
"Both of you, get out!"

1528
01:22:44,423 --> 01:22:45,883 
Dad never liked animals.

1529
01:22:46,633 --> 01:22:48,093 
He wouldn't even look at Pappu.

1530
01:22:50,137 --> 01:22:51,889 
I took him and stood outside...

1531
01:22:53,140 --> 01:22:54,600 
until all the rituals were over.

1532
01:22:58,395 --> 01:22:59,646 
Dad took away...

1533
01:23:00,230 --> 01:23:02,274 
the last chance for me
and Pappu...

1534
01:23:03,442 --> 01:23:04,610 
to be with Mom.

1535
01:23:07,112 --> 01:23:08,822 
From that day on,
I've barely spoken to him.

1536
01:23:10,115 --> 01:23:12,075 
And neither has Dad, not since I removed
my sacred thread.

1537
01:23:13,952 --> 01:23:14,953 
But that was back then, right?

1538
01:23:15,579 --> 01:23:17,414 
Now you've got
your sacred thread again,

1539
01:23:17,414 --> 01:23:19,333 
and your Dad is now
Pappu's favourite person.

1540
01:23:19,541 --> 01:23:20,876 
Then why aren't you two talking?

1541
01:23:22,377 --> 01:23:23,462 
It's not possible now.

1542
01:23:23,504 --> 01:23:24,546 
We just... got set that way.

1543
01:23:24,838 --> 01:23:26,089 
Then just reset it!

1544
01:23:26,757 --> 01:23:27,758 
Look, Prabha...

1545
01:23:27,800 --> 01:23:30,761 
staying upset with someone
and holding onto it forever...

1546
01:23:30,803 --> 01:23:32,221 
it's simply exhausting.

1547
01:23:32,888 --> 01:23:34,473 
Life's too short for all that!

1548
01:23:35,265 --> 01:23:36,308 
Hmm.

1549
01:23:37,017 --> 01:23:38,018 
Point.

1550
01:23:38,352 --> 01:23:39,353 
Thank you.

1551
01:23:48,153 --> 01:23:49,238 
Errr...

1552
01:23:49,404 --> 01:23:50,572 
I'm on the phone, Uncle.

1553
01:23:50,989 --> 01:23:52,658 
Thulasi has called
us to have lunch.

1554
01:23:52,699 --> 01:23:53,826 
Come on.

1555
01:24:00,874 --> 01:24:02,125 
- Yes, I'll be there.

1556
01:24:02,793 --> 01:24:03,836 
I'll tell Indu.

1557
01:24:03,919 --> 01:24:04,962 
Alright.

1558
01:24:04,962 --> 01:24:06,380 
- Was that Neelakandan?
- Yes.

1559
01:24:06,964 --> 01:24:08,674 
Deepu chettan has come home,
along with everyone.

1560
01:24:08,882 --> 01:24:10,884 
He called to ask if Indu
will attend the temple festival.

1561
01:24:11,635 --> 01:24:13,470 
Uncle is hesitant
to ask him directly.

1562
01:24:14,138 --> 01:24:16,431 
Indu had lunch, took his bike,
and went off somewhere.

1563
01:24:16,598 --> 01:24:17,766 
Is that so?

1564
01:24:19,017 --> 01:24:20,018 
Uncle...

1565
01:24:20,602 --> 01:24:22,521 
Has Indu been acting
a little unusual lately?

1566
01:24:22,563 --> 01:24:25,440 
- Ha! I was just about to ask you that.
- Oh really?

1567
01:24:25,524 --> 01:24:26,733 
- One thing's certain.
- What?

1568
01:24:26,775 --> 01:24:28,652 
- He's possessed.
- By a ghost?

1569
01:24:28,694 --> 01:24:30,529 
Not a ghost!
Possessed by love for a girl!

1570
01:24:31,196 --> 01:24:32,197 
How do you know?

1571
01:24:32,447 --> 01:24:33,991 
I caught him red-handed today.

1572
01:24:33,991 --> 01:24:36,577 
He was whispering away
on the phone.

1573
01:24:36,827 --> 01:24:38,203 
From the looks of it,

1574
01:24:38,203 --> 01:24:40,247 
it was definitely a girl
on the other end.

1575
01:24:40,289 --> 01:24:41,999 
Oh! I had no idea!

1576
01:24:42,708 --> 01:24:44,668 
There's a lot
you've got no idea about!

1577
01:24:45,085 --> 01:24:47,212 
Do you even know
all the puja rituals?

1578
01:24:47,254 --> 01:24:48,380 
Well,

1579
01:24:48,630 --> 01:24:51,258 
you should've thought of that when
you got your sister married to a cook!

1580
01:24:51,592 --> 01:24:53,343 
The fact that I made it this far
from that background

1581
01:24:53,385 --> 01:24:54,553 
is purely because of my own talent!

1582
01:24:54,595 --> 01:24:56,013 
That much I'll accept.

1583
01:24:57,306 --> 01:24:58,307 
Uncle...

1584
01:24:58,474 --> 01:25:01,268 
I'm thinking of
focusing on exorcisms.

1585
01:25:01,435 --> 01:25:04,563 
There are families that have been
doing that for generations, Rupe.

1586
01:25:04,897 --> 01:25:07,024 
To avoid the side effects,

1587
01:25:07,274 --> 01:25:11,361 
you need the expertise and spiritual energy
passed down through generations.

1588
01:25:11,487 --> 01:25:13,322 
I'm doing this after proper study.

1589
01:25:13,447 --> 01:25:14,656 
So I'm not scared.

1590
01:25:14,781 --> 01:25:16,283 
- Fear is a good thing!
- Huh?!

1591
01:25:16,325 --> 01:25:19,369 
Fear was the very first emotion
humans ever had...

1592
01:25:19,661 --> 01:25:20,996 
for basic safety.

1593
01:25:21,538 --> 01:25:23,916 
I do follow basic safety precautions
when I perform exorcisms.

1594
01:25:23,957 --> 01:25:26,627 
There are three types of spirits.
Do you know?

1595
01:25:26,668 --> 01:25:28,086 
Hmm. I don't.

1596
01:25:28,086 --> 01:25:29,421 
Randukama...

1597
01:25:29,421 --> 01:25:30,672 
Bhokthukama...

1598
01:25:30,714 --> 01:25:32,090 
and Handukama.

1599
01:25:32,090 --> 01:25:34,092 
The first two are relatively harmless.

1600
01:25:34,468 --> 01:25:37,596 
But the Handukama
comes only to kill!

1601
01:25:38,180 --> 01:25:39,807 
It won't go back
without taking a life.

1602
01:25:43,936 --> 01:25:44,937 
Oh god!

1603
01:25:46,647 --> 01:25:48,065 
Annamma Joseph.

1604
01:25:48,607 --> 01:25:50,526 
Born in 1932.

1605
01:25:52,069 --> 01:25:53,153 
Not this one either.

1606
01:25:53,320 --> 01:25:54,321 
Delulu!

1607
01:25:54,446 --> 01:25:55,948 
Here's one...
a girl named Tessa.

1608
01:25:56,198 --> 01:25:57,199 
Born in '88.

1609
01:25:57,991 --> 01:25:59,827 
Try to remember...
Could your name be Tessa?

1610
01:25:59,910 --> 01:26:02,371 
No! Born in '88 means
she's over 30!

1611
01:26:02,788 --> 01:26:04,206 
How old do I look to you?

1612
01:26:04,289 --> 01:26:05,707 
About twen--

1613
01:26:06,083 --> 01:26:07,251 
Thirty-thirty two!

1614
01:26:07,292 --> 01:26:08,961 
What?! I'm not that old!

1615
01:26:11,088 --> 01:26:13,006 
Are there any other
Mar Thoma churches around here?

1616
01:26:13,340 --> 01:26:14,675 
Let's see... around here...

1617
01:26:15,843 --> 01:26:17,427 
If you're a ghost
who's crossed districts,

1618
01:26:17,427 --> 01:26:19,263 
we might have to check
the Kottayam-Thiruvalla area.

1619
01:26:19,805 --> 01:26:21,181 
It's alright.
We'll keep looking.

1620
01:26:22,808 --> 01:26:23,934 
Lillykutty!

1621
01:26:24,184 --> 01:26:25,894 
I just wish I could at
least remember my name.

1622
01:26:26,395 --> 01:26:27,479 
Don't worry, Delulu.

1623
01:26:27,563 --> 01:26:28,689 
We will keep trying.

1624
01:26:29,022 --> 01:26:30,065 
Won't we, Lillykutty?

1625
01:26:30,107 --> 01:26:31,775 
- Did you know my grandmother?
- Huh?

1626
01:26:33,110 --> 01:26:34,778 
I asked whether you knew my grandmother.

1627
01:26:35,696 --> 01:26:37,197 
Yes... your grandmother...

1628
01:26:37,573 --> 01:26:39,366 
I went to her tuition
classes back in eighth grade.

1629
01:26:39,950 --> 01:26:41,076 
Don't you recognize us?

1630
01:26:41,535 --> 01:26:42,536 
Yes, I do.

1631
01:26:43,495 --> 01:26:45,706 
Kalarickal Davis...
the one who lives near the tile factory?

1632
01:26:45,747 --> 01:26:47,666 
Of course!
Davis Chettan is like family to us!

1633
01:26:47,708 --> 01:26:48,834 
I am Davis!

1634
01:26:50,169 --> 01:26:51,253 
Davis Chetta...

1635
01:26:51,253 --> 01:26:53,797 
Are there any other
new cemeteries nearby?

1636
01:26:54,882 --> 01:26:56,842 
Cemetery?
There's St. George Cemetery.

1637
01:26:57,426 --> 01:26:58,427 
I already went there.

1638
01:26:58,594 --> 01:26:59,595 
Anything else, dear?

1639
01:26:59,887 --> 01:27:01,263 
Then... there's Paleparambil...

1640
01:27:01,263 --> 01:27:02,431 
Did you go to Paleparambil Church?

1641
01:27:02,431 --> 01:27:03,724 
Yeah, I went there too.

1642
01:27:03,807 --> 01:27:05,100 
There are no other cemeteries.

1643
01:27:06,101 --> 01:27:08,395 
None, huh?
Hmm, alright then.

1644
01:27:09,396 --> 01:27:10,647 
Okay, get up.
Let's go.

1645
01:27:11,857 --> 01:27:12,858 
Okay.

1646
01:27:13,358 --> 01:27:14,359 
Come on.

1647
01:27:14,735 --> 01:27:17,404 
You look really beautiful after switching
from that T-shirt to a churidar.

1648
01:27:46,141 --> 01:27:47,559 
Rupe! Where's Indu?

1649
01:27:48,060 --> 01:27:50,020 
I brought him.
But he didn't come inside.

1650
01:27:50,062 --> 01:27:52,064 
Go check on him, Rupe.
Ask him to come and be here.

1651
01:27:52,105 --> 01:27:53,190 
Okay, Deepu Chetta.

1652
01:27:59,154 --> 01:28:00,739 
That's Animon for you!

1653
01:28:01,406 --> 01:28:02,407 
My turn.

1654
01:28:03,784 --> 01:28:05,452 
Don't miss.
You see that teddy bear? That's the prize.

1655
01:28:05,494 --> 01:28:06,703 
I need it for my autorickshaw.

1656
01:28:07,913 --> 01:28:09,122 
Wait and watch!

1657
01:28:12,876 --> 01:28:13,919 
It didn't pop?

1658
01:28:13,961 --> 01:28:14,962 
Not even close!

1659
01:28:15,254 --> 01:28:16,880 
Guess I've lost my teddy bear.

1660
01:28:20,634 --> 01:28:21,635 
Just a minute.

1661
01:28:25,597 --> 01:28:26,640 
Psst!

1662
01:28:35,607 --> 01:28:38,152 
One single shot.
Make it pop, okay?

1663
01:28:38,527 --> 01:28:39,903 
- Okay.
- Okay.

1664
01:28:41,196 --> 01:28:42,114 
What?

1665
01:28:42,114 --> 01:28:43,198 
You called me, didn't you?

1666
01:28:43,657 --> 01:28:45,576 
Err... it's just...
balloon...

1667
01:28:45,617 --> 01:28:46,785 
It didn't pop.

1668
01:28:46,869 --> 01:28:47,870 
- Huh?
- Sorry.

1669
01:28:51,999 --> 01:28:53,750 
Don't worry.
No one saw it except me.

1670
01:28:54,418 --> 01:28:55,919 
My prestige is
on the line here, okay?

1671
01:28:56,044 --> 01:28:57,671 
It has to pop
on the count of three.

1672
01:28:57,754 --> 01:28:58,755 
Done.

1673
01:28:59,715 --> 01:29:00,757 
One...

1674
01:29:01,967 --> 01:29:02,968 
Two...

1675
01:29:08,640 --> 01:29:09,641 
Sorry!

1676
01:29:15,230 --> 01:29:17,858 
[Traditional satirical storytelling
performance on stage]

1677
01:29:33,081 --> 01:29:34,082 
Bless you!

1678
01:29:48,138 --> 01:29:49,348 
You stole it already?!

1679
01:29:49,431 --> 01:29:50,849 
Ugh! No!

1680
01:29:51,016 --> 01:29:52,476 
I just need one good look
at someone.

1681
01:29:52,518 --> 01:29:53,560 
I can wear it.

1682
01:29:53,644 --> 01:29:54,728 
How do I look?

1683
01:29:54,978 --> 01:29:56,563 
Hmm... not bad.

1684
01:29:57,606 --> 01:29:59,233 
A little appreciation would be nice.

1685
01:30:00,192 --> 01:30:01,401 
I have to feel like it, right?

1686
01:30:01,485 --> 01:30:03,153 
Hey, you!
Over here!

1687
01:30:04,279 --> 01:30:05,906 
Talking to yourself? Huh?

1688
01:30:06,323 --> 01:30:07,324 
What?!

1689
01:30:08,075 --> 01:30:09,535 
I'm on the phone!

1690
01:30:09,618 --> 01:30:11,203 
So you were lost in that,
weren't you?

1691
01:30:11,245 --> 01:30:12,746 
Every young prince these days

1692
01:30:12,746 --> 01:30:14,331 
sleeps and wakes up
with that thing in hand.

1693
01:30:14,373 --> 01:30:15,624 
Put it away!

1694
01:30:15,707 --> 01:30:17,084 
Who's this "young prince"?

1695
01:30:20,671 --> 01:30:22,005 
- Prabhendu.
- Oh.

1696
01:30:22,047 --> 01:30:26,802 
Indu looks radiant today.
Looks like he's met his maiden.

1697
01:30:26,927 --> 01:30:27,761 
Indu!

1698
01:30:29,388 --> 01:30:30,889 
It's Rupa.
He's probably calling me to the temple.

1699
01:30:30,931 --> 01:30:31,974 
- Come on, let's go!
- Hey!

1700
01:30:32,015 --> 01:30:33,183 
- Indu!
- Are you leaving?

1701
01:30:35,978 --> 01:30:38,272 
Hey, Prabha...
your ticket to Bombay has arrived.

1702
01:30:38,647 --> 01:30:40,566 
For Viraj Trivedi's recording session.

1703
01:30:41,942 --> 01:30:43,569 
Aren't you coming to Bombay, Delulu?

1704
01:30:43,819 --> 01:30:44,820 
Of course I am!

1705
01:30:45,487 --> 01:30:47,614 
Anyway, I've got nothing else
to do here, right?

1706
01:30:48,240 --> 01:30:49,241 
Hey...

1707
01:30:49,366 --> 01:30:51,326 
When the flight is
up above the clouds,

1708
01:30:51,326 --> 01:30:52,828 
will you be tempted
to go to heaven?

1709
01:30:54,621 --> 01:30:56,248 
I'll save the rest of my laughter
for tomorrow!

1710
01:30:59,209 --> 01:31:00,752 
Hey, your brother's calling.

1711
01:31:01,545 --> 01:31:03,046 
Don't pick up!
That'll just bring trouble.

1712
01:31:03,088 --> 01:31:04,631 
Must be because
I didn't enter the temple.

1713
01:31:04,631 --> 01:31:06,884 
You're seeing a ghost this close...

1714
01:31:06,925 --> 01:31:08,886 
Yet, why don't you believe in God?

1715
01:31:09,553 --> 01:31:11,180 
The answer lies
within the question itself.

1716
01:31:11,638 --> 01:31:12,931 
It's because I can't see God.

1717
01:31:14,141 --> 01:31:15,726 
Can you see music, Prabha?

1718
01:31:16,477 --> 01:31:18,145 
You can only hear music, right?

1719
01:31:18,604 --> 01:31:20,647 
Yeah, I mean... we can play or sing.

1720
01:31:20,647 --> 01:31:22,733 
That's just like taking a printout
from a printer.

1721
01:31:23,025 --> 01:31:25,486 
But what I meant was...

1722
01:31:25,777 --> 01:31:26,987 
the original source.
Music itself.

1723
01:31:27,571 --> 01:31:28,780 
Where does music come from?

1724
01:31:29,114 --> 01:31:30,282 
It's...

1725
01:31:31,533 --> 01:31:33,076 
It's talent and practice.

1726
01:31:33,118 --> 01:31:34,286 
Exactly!

1727
01:31:34,328 --> 01:31:36,413 
Talent is God,
and practice is prayer!

1728
01:31:36,497 --> 01:31:37,498 
Simple!

1729
01:31:37,539 --> 01:31:38,540 
Incredible!

1730
01:31:38,582 --> 01:31:40,167 
A devil is vouching for God!

1731
01:31:40,501 --> 01:31:41,835 
Don't call me Devil!

1732
01:31:42,169 --> 01:31:43,587 
I am a nice spirit!

1733
01:31:43,796 --> 01:31:44,797 
A good soul.

1734
01:31:44,838 --> 01:31:45,923 
Sorry, sorry!

1735
01:31:45,964 --> 01:31:48,300 
I'm not entirely convinced
about you either, Delulu.

1736
01:31:48,801 --> 01:31:51,887 
I keep calming myself down by thinking
you're nothing more than my imagination.

1737
01:31:52,095 --> 01:31:54,473 
A very powerful and
impactful hallucination.

1738
01:31:55,474 --> 01:31:56,517 
Oh Jesus!

1739
01:31:56,517 --> 01:31:58,685 
So you're saying
my skills are worthless?

1740
01:31:58,852 --> 01:32:00,103 
Ha! Skills?

1741
01:32:00,395 --> 01:32:01,897 
You're still on a learner's permit!

1742
01:32:01,897 --> 01:32:03,398 
You tried switching on the light
and blew the bulb!

1743
01:32:03,398 --> 01:32:04,650 
Can you even touch anyone at all?

1744
01:32:05,067 --> 01:32:06,068 
Pathetic!

1745
01:32:08,821 --> 01:32:09,863 
Yes, I can.

1746
01:32:11,657 --> 01:32:12,658 
Huh?!

1747
01:32:24,753 --> 01:32:25,754 
This...

1748
01:32:26,755 --> 01:32:28,048 
This breeze that hit me just now...

1749
01:32:28,382 --> 01:32:29,424 
That was my touch.

1750
01:32:29,591 --> 01:32:31,301 
Breeze is the easiest medium
to do that.

1751
01:32:31,927 --> 01:32:32,970 
A soft breeze.

1752
01:32:37,641 --> 01:32:38,684 
Give me the phone.

1753
01:32:41,812 --> 01:32:43,689 
Let me see
if I can take a picture.

1754
01:32:43,814 --> 01:32:45,149 
Go ahead.
You won't get anything.

1755
01:32:49,194 --> 01:32:50,195 
Did it work?

1756
01:32:50,904 --> 01:32:51,905 
Let me try a video.

1757
01:32:52,156 --> 01:32:53,157 
Hmm.

1758
01:32:54,741 --> 01:32:55,951 
Did it work now?

1759
01:32:56,076 --> 01:32:57,077 
You won't see me in it.

1760
01:33:04,376 --> 01:33:06,170 
Google Pay is risky.
Do you have cash?

1761
01:33:06,336 --> 01:33:08,213 
Crush it properly,
mix it with water and have it.

1762
01:33:08,255 --> 01:33:09,339 
Okay bro, thanks.

1763
01:33:09,381 --> 01:33:10,382 
Huh?

1764
01:33:10,716 --> 01:33:12,092 
- Hey!
- Where?

1765
01:33:12,759 --> 01:33:13,760 
What is it?

1766
01:33:13,802 --> 01:33:14,803 
What is it?

1767
01:33:15,137 --> 01:33:16,305 
Wait, we're coming.
Come on.

1768
01:33:17,848 --> 01:33:19,057 
I'm screwed!

1769
01:33:20,309 --> 01:33:21,560 
Come on, get up!
Let's go!

1770
01:33:21,643 --> 01:33:22,644 
What's wrong?

1771
01:33:22,686 --> 01:33:23,896 
I'll tell you later.
Let's go!

1772
01:33:28,233 --> 01:33:29,776 
Hello... how high are you...

1773
01:33:29,776 --> 01:33:31,528 
I mean... Hi... how are you?

1774
01:33:31,695 --> 01:33:33,155 
What were you filming
on your phone?

1775
01:33:33,155 --> 01:33:34,740 
No, I wasn't filming you guys!

1776
01:33:35,073 --> 01:33:36,533 
He'll show it
to the cops, Sreerag.

1777
01:33:36,742 --> 01:33:38,118 
Didn't we chase this guy off
the other day?

1778
01:33:38,160 --> 01:33:39,077 
Don't you remember?

1779
01:33:39,119 --> 01:33:41,163 
Boys, honestly,
I have nothing against you.

1780
01:33:43,624 --> 01:33:44,625 
Give me your phone.

1781
01:33:44,917 --> 01:33:46,168 
Don't give it to them, Prabha.

1782
01:33:47,586 --> 01:33:48,921 
Let me deal with this.

1783
01:33:51,298 --> 01:33:52,299 
You can check my gallery.

1784
01:33:52,424 --> 01:33:53,634 
I haven't taken any pictures!

1785
01:33:54,343 --> 01:33:55,636 
These guys are so rude, Prabha!

1786
01:33:55,636 --> 01:33:56,678 
Grab the phone from him.

1787
01:33:56,678 --> 01:33:58,305 
Just be quiet, Delulu!

1788
01:33:58,680 --> 01:33:59,681 
- Huh?
- Huh?

1789
01:33:59,723 --> 01:34:00,724 
- Huh?
- Huh?

1790
01:34:01,558 --> 01:34:02,768 
Hit him, Prabha!

1791
01:34:03,018 --> 01:34:04,603 
- Idiots!
- Delulu, please!

1792
01:34:04,645 --> 01:34:05,896 
I can solve this!

1793
01:34:05,896 --> 01:34:07,147 
What's wrong with this guy?

1794
01:34:07,523 --> 01:34:08,774 
Just give me the phone, Kiddo.

1795
01:34:08,816 --> 01:34:10,192 
I don't usually get involved
in things like these.

1796
01:34:10,192 --> 01:34:11,985 
I don't even know
who you guys are.

1797
01:34:13,320 --> 01:34:14,530 
How about I let you know?

1798
01:34:44,059 --> 01:34:45,060 
Alright then.

1799
01:34:45,269 --> 01:34:46,270 
Okay.

1800
01:34:46,520 --> 01:34:47,479 
Let's go.

1801
01:34:55,571 --> 01:34:56,572 
Sreerag...

1802
01:34:56,697 --> 01:34:57,698 
Hey!

1803
01:35:00,284 --> 01:35:01,326 
I just...

1804
01:35:01,994 --> 01:35:03,245 
I got high all of a sudden.

1805
01:35:03,579 --> 01:35:05,038 
- Is he gone?
- Yeah, perfect!

1806
01:35:05,330 --> 01:35:07,474
While you stood there like a tableau,
he walked off with the phone.

1807
01:35:07,484 --> 01:35:08,917
Huh? When?

1808
01:35:08,959 --> 01:35:10,252
Come on! If we hurry,
we can catch him.

1809
01:35:12,004 --> 01:35:13,005 
Right!

1810
01:35:14,298 --> 01:35:15,507 
Are they following us?

1811
01:35:16,884 --> 01:35:18,510 
- Yes.
- Oh no!

1812
01:35:18,927 --> 01:35:20,137 
They are just kids, Prabha.

1813
01:35:20,179 --> 01:35:21,638 
This is bad,
this is really bad!

1814
01:35:21,680 --> 01:35:22,848 
Stop for a second, Prabha.

1815
01:35:23,599 --> 01:35:25,851 
Are you planning to spend your
whole life being scared like this?

1816
01:35:27,644 --> 01:35:28,645 
Are you?

1817
01:35:31,523 --> 01:35:32,524 
No.

1818
01:35:41,200 --> 01:35:42,242 
Oh no!

1819
01:35:48,040 --> 01:35:49,291 
Dude, go get him!

1820
01:36:21,824 --> 01:36:23,909 
- Where's my bike key?
- Huh?

1821
01:36:23,951 --> 01:36:25,118 
The bike key, where is it?

1822
01:36:25,118 --> 01:36:26,453 
Can we talk after this?

1823
01:36:26,495 --> 01:36:27,621 
Fine, fine.

1824
01:36:43,178 --> 01:36:44,346 
Dude, don't leave!

1825
01:36:45,889 --> 01:36:47,099 
Oh no!

1826
01:36:47,099 --> 01:36:48,934 
- Hereafter...
- Hereafter?

1827
01:36:49,184 --> 01:36:52,020 
- If you ever pull this kind of stunt--
- "on this street again..."

1828
01:36:52,020 --> 01:36:54,481 
- I'll smash your face--
- "and change its shape," right?

1829
01:36:54,523 --> 01:36:56,525 
- Yes!
- That's fine, Chetta. No problem.

1830
01:36:56,525 --> 01:36:57,401 
- Hmm.
- Right.

1831
01:36:57,442 --> 01:36:58,735 
Scram!

1832
01:36:58,944 --> 01:37:00,195 
Oh, sorry, Chetta!

1833
01:37:05,701 --> 01:37:07,286 
- All good?
- Absolutely!

1834
01:37:07,828 --> 01:37:08,829 
Let's go!

1835
01:37:15,210 --> 01:37:16,503 
What's the check-in time?

1836
01:37:17,504 --> 01:37:18,881 
Ah... At 2:00 PM.

1837
01:37:19,840 --> 01:37:21,133 
And the return flight?

1838
01:37:22,050 --> 01:37:25,137 
That... we'll book that only
after tomorrow's recording.

1839
01:37:28,557 --> 01:37:31,226 
Deepu Chetta, the reason I didn't
enter the temple yesterday...

1840
01:37:31,685 --> 01:37:33,645 
It's not something
anyone should be forced to do.

1841
01:37:34,438 --> 01:37:35,814 
It's your choice.

1842
01:37:36,398 --> 01:37:38,066 
God is inside us, after all.

1843
01:37:38,692 --> 01:37:41,487 
Temples and churches
are just like mirrors

1844
01:37:41,820 --> 01:37:43,280 
that reflect that power.

1845
01:37:44,823 --> 01:37:46,283 
Dad's a bit upset...

1846
01:37:46,617 --> 01:37:49,244 
that even after taking up pujas,
I still avoid entering temples.

1847
01:37:49,745 --> 01:37:51,788 
I've already talked to him
and sorted it out.

1848
01:37:52,080 --> 01:37:55,292 
Dad knows very well how
sincerely you perform the pujas.

1849
01:37:55,834 --> 01:37:57,920 
And that's why
your pujas are so effective.

1850
01:37:57,920 --> 01:37:59,296 
Exactly!

1851
01:37:59,505 --> 01:38:00,339 
Hey...

1852
01:38:00,380 --> 01:38:01,673 
- What is it?
- What is it?

1853
01:38:01,882 --> 01:38:02,841 
- Huh?
- Huh?

1854
01:38:02,841 --> 01:38:04,259 
- What?
- Don't you hear a sound...

1855
01:38:04,259 --> 01:38:05,177 
coming from the car?

1856
01:38:05,219 --> 01:38:06,220 
- Really?
- Yes.

1857
01:38:07,054 --> 01:38:07,846 
Oh, yeah.

1858
01:38:07,846 --> 01:38:09,765 
You've got such sharp ears, Indu!

1859
01:38:10,641 --> 01:38:12,476 
Looks like the car is due
for a service.

1860
01:38:12,726 --> 01:38:13,852 
Yes, yes.

1861
01:38:19,233 --> 01:38:20,442 
17-B

1862
01:38:21,151 --> 01:38:22,820 
You can sit here, Prabha.
I'll be over there.

1863
01:38:47,553 --> 01:38:48,887 
I was in Bangalore.

1864
01:38:49,304 --> 01:38:51,014 
Yes. I was in Bangalore.

1865
01:38:52,850 --> 01:38:54,560 
Did you board the wrong flight?

1866
01:38:54,893 --> 01:38:56,353 
This flight is going to Mumbai.

1867
01:38:56,395 --> 01:38:58,105 
Prabha! It's me, Delulu!

1868
01:38:59,273 --> 01:39:00,357 
Huh?

1869
01:39:00,357 --> 01:39:02,401 
But how? You've started
possessing people now?

1870
01:39:02,442 --> 01:39:03,819 
How else can I talk to you?

1871
01:39:04,111 --> 01:39:05,612 
This girl was a perfect fit.

1872
01:39:05,863 --> 01:39:08,073 
Hmm! Your 'perfection'
is getting out of hand!

1873
01:39:08,157 --> 01:39:09,408 
Yes, yes.
Prabha, listen.

1874
01:39:09,491 --> 01:39:11,827 
I used to fly from Kochi
airport to Bangalore.

1875
01:39:11,952 --> 01:39:13,120 
I'm very sure.

1876
01:39:14,121 --> 01:39:15,747 
Did getting on the flight
trigger her memories?

1877
01:39:16,540 --> 01:39:17,958
Quick! Remember the rest.

1878
01:39:17,968 --> 01:39:19,042
Who was the one who said "Yes"?

1879
01:39:22,045 --> 01:39:23,088
Think quickly!

1880
01:39:23,088 --> 01:39:24,089 
Even half of it is fine.

1881
01:39:24,131 --> 01:39:26,008 
We'll figure out the rest
on the return flight.

1882
01:39:31,430 --> 01:39:32,431 
Don't stress yourself.

1883
01:39:32,556 --> 01:39:34,892 
Perhaps it will just come back
bit by bit.

1884
01:39:36,685 --> 01:39:37,728 
Prabha...

1885
01:39:37,728 --> 01:39:39,605 
I'm sensing something else too.

1886
01:39:41,190 --> 01:39:42,191 
What is it?

1887
01:39:43,317 --> 01:39:44,943 
Now that I've remembered
this one thing,

1888
01:39:45,235 --> 01:39:46,612 
I feel much lighter.

1889
01:39:47,571 --> 01:39:49,740 
It feels like a burden
has been taken off me.

1890
01:39:50,824 --> 01:39:51,992 
That's a good thing, right?

1891
01:39:52,409 --> 01:39:54,077 
Guess you're on your way
to salvation.

1892
01:39:54,203 --> 01:39:56,997 
I think once you find out
who said that 'Yes,'

1893
01:39:56,997 --> 01:39:58,582 
you'll move on for good.

1894
01:39:58,916 --> 01:39:59,917 
Full free!

1895
01:39:59,958 --> 01:40:01,543 
So you won't miss me if I go?

1896
01:40:02,169 --> 01:40:03,295 
Ha, great!

1897
01:40:03,670 --> 01:40:05,798 
Isn't it more important
that you get your freedom?

1898
01:40:05,964 --> 01:40:07,132 
Salvation is important!

1899
01:40:07,508 --> 01:40:08,592 
Wow!

1900
01:40:08,592 --> 01:40:09,927 
So you won't miss me at all, huh?

1901
01:40:22,773 --> 01:40:23,774 
Psst!

1902
01:40:26,026 --> 01:40:27,027 
Psst!

1903
01:40:28,278 --> 01:40:29,279 
Psst!

1904
01:40:32,074 --> 01:40:33,075 
Yeah?

1905
01:40:34,117 --> 01:40:35,285 
I'll miss you too.

1906
01:40:36,078 --> 01:40:37,079 
What?!

1907
01:40:37,496 --> 01:40:38,789 
I will miss you.

1908
01:40:38,872 --> 01:40:40,207 
Psst! Prabha!

1909
01:40:41,750 --> 01:40:43,168 
Sorry! I lost the connection.

1910
01:40:50,634 --> 01:40:51,802 
Sorry, Madam.

1911
01:40:52,386 --> 01:40:53,720 
- Creep!
- Yup!

1912
01:40:57,724 --> 01:40:59,017 
I knew you'd miss me!

1913
01:41:00,519 --> 01:41:01,728 
I knew you'd miss me!

1914
01:41:31,925 --> 01:41:33,010 
Hello?

1915
01:41:34,178 --> 01:41:35,304 
No.

1916
01:41:35,512 --> 01:41:36,597 
He's almost here.

1917
01:41:38,182 --> 01:41:40,434 
I've packed all his things
in carton boxes.

1918
01:41:41,977 --> 01:41:44,521 
His clothes, shoes, and books.

1919
01:41:46,023 --> 01:41:48,400 
And the bluetooth
speaker he gifted me.

1920
01:41:49,276 --> 01:41:51,653 
Hey, he's here.
I'll call you later.

1921
01:41:51,820 --> 01:41:52,905 
Thanks, dear.

1922
01:42:03,624 --> 01:42:04,625 
Hey...

1923
01:42:04,666 --> 01:42:05,959 
Are you okay, Saadhya?

1924
01:42:06,335 --> 01:42:07,336 
I'll be fine.

1925
01:42:07,419 --> 01:42:08,462 
Don't worry.

1926
01:42:09,254 --> 01:42:10,547 
These are your things.

1927
01:42:12,508 --> 01:42:13,592 
Thanks.

1928
01:42:15,719 --> 01:42:17,513 
- See, I--
- I'm getting late for work.

1929
01:42:18,180 --> 01:42:19,223 
You take care, okay?

1930
01:42:19,264 --> 01:42:20,307 
Enjoy New York.

1931
01:42:34,655 --> 01:42:35,656 
Superb!

1932
01:42:35,739 --> 01:42:36,949 
Didn't I tell you?

1933
01:42:47,417 --> 01:42:49,294 
He is such a find, Saadhya!

1934
01:42:49,461 --> 01:42:50,838 
Prabhendu, beautiful!

1935
01:42:51,088 --> 01:42:52,089 
Please come here.

1936
01:42:52,089 --> 01:42:53,090 
Thank you, sir.

1937
01:42:59,721 --> 01:43:01,223 
She is the one who found you.

1938
01:43:01,640 --> 01:43:02,683 
- Oh.
- Hi.

1939
01:43:02,891 --> 01:43:03,892 
Saadhya.

1940
01:43:04,560 --> 01:43:05,769 
Faizal keeps talking about you.

1941
01:43:05,894 --> 01:43:07,855 
He's your biggest well-wisher, Prabhendu.

1942
01:43:08,230 --> 01:43:10,023 
- Oh!
- Shift to Mumbai soon.

1943
01:43:10,065 --> 01:43:11,066 
We need you here.

1944
01:43:11,108 --> 01:43:12,109 
Sure, sir.

1945
01:43:12,568 --> 01:43:13,986 
- Just a minute, Saadhya.
- Ah, sure, sir.

1946
01:43:13,986 --> 01:43:15,237 
- Come on.
- Okay.

1947
01:43:15,320 --> 01:43:17,281 
Good night, Prabhendu.
Until next time.

1948
01:43:17,322 --> 01:43:18,407 
See you, sir.

1949
01:43:18,490 --> 01:43:19,491 
See you.

1950
01:43:24,830 --> 01:43:26,206 
I'm officially your fan, Prabha!

1951
01:43:26,248 --> 01:43:27,499 
How do you play so well?

1952
01:43:27,541 --> 01:43:29,751 
Well, that's just how talented I am!

1953
01:43:30,586 --> 01:43:31,628 
Ugh!

1954
01:43:31,628 --> 01:43:33,505 
Rupa has scheduled a puja
for tomorrow evening!

1955
01:43:33,839 --> 01:43:34,840 
What do we do?

1956
01:43:36,842 --> 01:43:40,012 
I've sent you the door password
for the service apartment.

1957
01:43:40,137 --> 01:43:41,221 
The location too.

1958
01:43:41,388 --> 01:43:42,890 
- It's close by.
- Got it.

1959
01:43:43,015 --> 01:43:44,475 
Are you okay with the
evening flight tomorrow?

1960
01:43:44,475 --> 01:43:47,978 
Err... is it possible to get a flight
that lands before noon tomorrow?

1961
01:43:48,187 --> 01:43:49,938 
Ah... there's one at 6:30 AM.

1962
01:43:49,980 --> 01:43:50,981 
Will that do?

1963
01:43:51,064 --> 01:43:52,274 
I'm on that flight too.

1964
01:43:52,441 --> 01:43:53,901 
Yeah, that's fine.

1965
01:43:55,110 --> 01:43:56,111 
Okay.

1966
01:43:56,403 --> 01:43:57,404 
Yes, it's okay.

1967
01:44:00,282 --> 01:44:01,283 
Okay.

1968
01:44:01,658 --> 01:44:02,784 
You had dinner?

1969
01:44:02,951 --> 01:44:03,994 
No.

1970
01:44:04,036 --> 01:44:05,621 
Come on.
You can leave your bag here.

1971
01:44:05,746 --> 01:44:06,747 
Okay.

1972
01:44:07,831 --> 01:44:08,874 
Let's go.

1973
01:44:09,249 --> 01:44:11,335 
We need to leave
for the airport at 4:30 AM.

1974
01:44:11,376 --> 01:44:13,086 
- Okay.
- It'll be busy since it's the morning.

1975
01:44:14,254 --> 01:44:17,549 
I brought my bags, thinking the
recording would go on all night.

1976
01:44:18,175 --> 01:44:19,468 
You're amazing, Prabhendu!

1977
01:44:19,551 --> 01:44:21,011 
You finished it so fast!

1978
01:44:27,726 --> 01:44:29,436 
Pretty cool breeze, huh?
[mimicking Nivin Pauly]

1979
01:44:33,065 --> 01:44:34,107 
Sorry.

1980
01:44:37,694 --> 01:44:39,154 
She seems to be in
some kind of trouble.

1981
01:44:39,988 --> 01:44:41,031 
I'll check.

1982
01:44:45,160 --> 01:44:47,454 
Ugh! Classic heartbreak!

1983
01:44:47,704 --> 01:44:49,164 
- Poor thing!
- Oh.

1984
01:44:52,543 --> 01:44:53,710 
Aren't you eating?

1985
01:44:54,169 --> 01:44:55,212 
Huh?

1986
01:44:55,212 --> 01:44:56,839 
I asked...
aren't you eating?

1987
01:44:58,882 --> 01:45:01,426 
Her boyfriend dumped her, Prabha.

1988
01:45:01,593 --> 01:45:02,803 
Commitment issues.

1989
01:45:03,679 --> 01:45:04,930 
Stop it, Delulu!

1990
01:45:05,681 --> 01:45:08,767 
Poor girl. Still, she's handling
the situation so maturely.

1991
01:45:09,184 --> 01:45:10,269 
Yeah.

1992
01:45:10,310 --> 01:45:12,146 
Prabha, just ask her
if she's fine, no?

1993
01:45:12,729 --> 01:45:13,939 
Uh... uh... uh...

1994
01:45:13,981 --> 01:45:15,399 
What uh, uh, uh?

1995
01:45:15,566 --> 01:45:17,234 
Don't just keep staring!
Say something!

1996
01:45:18,443 --> 01:45:19,570 
Saadhya...

1997
01:45:19,903 --> 01:45:21,405 
Aren't you eating
the bun and gravy?

1998
01:45:26,243 --> 01:45:27,411 
Pav Bhaji.

1999
01:45:28,871 --> 01:45:30,455 
Ah, Pav Bhaji.

2000
01:45:47,681 --> 01:45:51,602 
Even though
I'm really angry with him...

2001
01:45:54,229 --> 01:45:55,856 
he is actually a good guy.

2002
01:46:05,157 --> 01:46:07,784 
My first instinct was to block him,
just like anyone would.

2003
01:46:10,037 --> 01:46:11,914 
But then,
I decided to go through with it,

2004
01:46:12,623 --> 01:46:14,124 
even though
it's a painful process.

2005
01:46:15,918 --> 01:46:17,711 
It's better for getting
a proper closure.

2006
01:46:19,463 --> 01:46:20,464 
Sometimes,

2007
01:46:20,464 --> 01:46:22,800 
we can only blame the situation,
not the person.

2008
01:46:26,887 --> 01:46:29,056 
If someone walks out of your life,

2009
01:46:29,223 --> 01:46:31,517 
it's important to keep
your heart clear.

2010
01:46:32,935 --> 01:46:35,229 
No anger, no grudges...

2011
01:46:36,021 --> 01:46:37,272 
wishing only the best for them.

2012
01:46:40,859 --> 01:46:41,860 
It's not easy.

2013
01:46:43,195 --> 01:46:44,404 
But...

2014
01:46:44,446 --> 01:46:46,323 
we get healed
just by being nice to them.

2015
01:46:59,837 --> 01:47:00,838 
Prabha...

2016
01:47:02,214 --> 01:47:03,465 
Are you able to see me?

2017
01:47:07,594 --> 01:47:08,595 
Yeah.

2018
01:47:09,555 --> 01:47:10,806 
I think I was in love.

2019
01:47:13,433 --> 01:47:14,935 
I was in love with someone.

2020
01:47:25,904 --> 01:47:27,447 
Do you remember his name?

2021
01:47:31,910 --> 01:47:33,203 
So...

2022
01:47:33,245 --> 01:47:34,705 
could he be the one
who said 'Yes'?

2023
01:47:37,332 --> 01:47:39,168 
Then I should've been happy, right?

2024
01:47:39,585 --> 01:47:40,836 
I didn't have to die!

2025
01:47:46,800 --> 01:47:47,843 
Hello, sir.

2026
01:47:47,843 --> 01:47:50,053 
Your friend has upgraded
you to an XL seat.

2027
01:47:50,387 --> 01:47:52,764 
You can shift there
and sit more comfortably.

2028
01:47:53,015 --> 01:47:54,057 
Thank you, sir.

2029
01:47:57,227 --> 01:47:58,228 
Come.

2030
01:48:02,065 --> 01:48:03,150 
Go on.

2031
01:48:29,468 --> 01:48:30,761 
Won't this run?

2032
01:48:30,803 --> 01:48:32,179 
It ran out of charge.

2033
01:48:35,599 --> 01:48:37,392 
Uncle, you must've received an OTP.

2034
01:48:37,476 --> 01:48:38,811 
Who are you calling "Uncle"?

2035
01:48:38,894 --> 01:48:40,020 
Oh... sorry, bro.

2036
01:48:40,062 --> 01:48:41,939 
An OTP must have come.
Could you tell me?

2037
01:48:41,980 --> 01:48:43,816 
I've been sitting here for an hour.

2038
01:48:44,024 --> 01:48:45,192 
I haven't seen anyone.

2039
01:48:45,442 --> 01:48:46,777 
Prabhendu N. Namboothiri?

2040
01:48:46,777 --> 01:48:48,403 
- Don't you have his number?
- I do.

2041
01:48:48,445 --> 01:48:49,655 
Then just call and ask him.

2042
01:48:49,696 --> 01:48:50,697 
Okay.

2043
01:48:57,287 --> 01:49:00,040 
I thought you didn't believe
in ghosts and stuff.

2044
01:49:00,082 --> 01:49:02,334 
- I don't believe in them, but I'm scared.
- Oh!

2045
01:49:02,459 --> 01:49:04,128 
Aren't your mantras strong, sir?

2046
01:49:04,211 --> 01:49:07,005 
Absolutely! A mantra saves
the one who chants it.

2047
01:49:07,005 --> 01:49:08,632 
What was that line, Indu?

2048
01:49:08,632 --> 01:49:10,968 
- A lie?
- Not a lie! A line!

2049
01:49:11,426 --> 01:49:14,096 
Ah, it's
"Manana thraayathe ithi mantrah"

2050
01:49:16,306 --> 01:49:17,307 
A doll!

2051
01:49:20,018 --> 01:49:21,061 
Take the sacred ash.

2052
01:49:27,901 --> 01:49:29,611 
Clean.
Let's go, let's go.

2053
01:49:29,611 --> 01:49:31,572 
Wait, there's a guest room too.

2054
01:49:31,613 --> 01:49:33,240 
- That's not really necess--
- Come on!

2055
01:49:41,081 --> 01:49:42,332 
Clean!
Can we go now?

2056
01:49:42,833 --> 01:49:45,335 
Close the window, Sashiyetta.
We don't want pigeons getting in.

2057
01:49:45,711 --> 01:49:47,379 
Sir, next is the grandmother's room.

2058
01:49:47,504 --> 01:49:48,505 
That's the main one.

2059
01:49:51,675 --> 01:49:52,676 
You're not scared?

2060
01:49:53,635 --> 01:49:54,636 
Of what?

2061
01:49:54,761 --> 01:49:56,513 
You know plenty of mantras, right?
Chant them.

2062
01:49:58,724 --> 01:49:59,725 
Come.

2063
01:50:00,559 --> 01:50:01,560 
You too.

2064
01:50:02,519 --> 01:50:03,520 
Who is he talking to?!

2065
01:50:07,399 --> 01:50:08,859 
This is the grandmother's room.

2066
01:50:11,153 --> 01:50:13,864 
After what happened,
not even the staff will enter here.

2067
01:50:15,782 --> 01:50:17,701 
- She'd be in here all the time.
- Even now?

2068
01:50:17,743 --> 01:50:19,453 
No, I mean before she died.

2069
01:50:19,536 --> 01:50:20,537 
Okay.

2070
01:50:21,205 --> 01:50:22,915 
She hardly slept.

2071
01:50:22,956 --> 01:50:24,541 
Why are you telling me all this?

2072
01:50:25,667 --> 01:50:27,085 
She really loved the balcony.

2073
01:50:27,127 --> 01:50:28,504 
Why? Was she a smoker?

2074
01:50:28,504 --> 01:50:29,963 
No, no.
To enjoy the breeze.

2075
01:50:30,798 --> 01:50:32,049 
Shall we cleanse that area too?

2076
01:50:32,090 --> 01:50:33,842 
Yeah! The balcony's safe.
There will be sunlight.

2077
01:50:33,884 --> 01:50:35,010 
Open it! Open it!

2078
01:50:47,606 --> 01:50:48,732 
Prabha!

2079
01:50:50,275 --> 01:50:51,276 
What is it?

2080
01:50:52,069 --> 01:50:53,070 
There...

2081
01:50:54,112 --> 01:50:55,113 
Where?

2082
01:50:56,073 --> 01:50:57,282 
- It's...
- What?

2083
01:50:57,908 --> 01:50:58,909 
What?

2084
01:51:15,634 --> 01:51:16,718 
What is it?

2085
01:51:16,885 --> 01:51:18,178 
Don't kill us, sir!

2086
01:51:18,971 --> 01:51:20,347 
We're not thieves, sir.

2087
01:51:20,472 --> 01:51:22,266 
We were staying here
since it's an empty room.

2088
01:51:22,558 --> 01:51:23,934 
- What?
- Is this the grandma?

2089
01:51:25,936 --> 01:51:26,895 
Get out, you!

2090
01:51:29,148 --> 01:51:30,232 
Oh no!

2091
01:51:30,315 --> 01:51:31,483 
Don't call the police, Chetta!

2092
01:51:32,442 --> 01:51:33,569 
Is the spirit gone?

2093
01:51:33,986 --> 01:51:34,987 
Yes!

2094
01:51:35,195 --> 01:51:36,196 
Clean!

2095
01:51:45,789 --> 01:51:49,251 
Hey, did you decide to stop doing pujas
because of what happened today?

2096
01:51:49,585 --> 01:51:51,378 
Not all all!
Today's puja worked, right?

2097
01:51:51,420 --> 01:51:53,005 
We got rid of the spirit,
didn't we?

2098
01:51:54,548 --> 01:51:55,924 
It's just that...

2099
01:51:56,258 --> 01:51:58,051 
The thought of you not
being here with me anymore...

2100
01:51:58,218 --> 01:51:59,761 
I'll be in Bombay from next week...

2101
01:51:59,845 --> 01:52:01,430 
busy with stage shows
and practice sessions.

2102
01:52:02,014 --> 01:52:04,558 
I can't commit to pujas
in the middle of all that.

2103
01:52:04,933 --> 01:52:05,976 
It'll be a hassle for you too.

2104
01:52:08,020 --> 01:52:09,021 
Hey!

2105
01:52:09,396 --> 01:52:11,106 
Just leave the sacred
thread on for now.

2106
01:52:11,356 --> 01:52:12,399 
Drop by when you're free.

2107
01:52:13,066 --> 01:52:14,526 
I don't feel as scared
when you're with me.

2108
01:52:15,694 --> 01:52:16,695 
Here, take this.

2109
01:52:17,946 --> 01:52:18,947 
It's 50K.

2110
01:52:19,406 --> 01:52:21,116 
50K? Wasn't our deal 60-40?

2111
01:52:21,200 --> 01:52:22,201 
You take the whole thing.

2112
01:52:22,534 --> 01:52:23,785 
Consider it your
provident fund!

2113
01:52:24,369 --> 01:52:26,914 
Also, if you get any puja work
in Bombay, don't say no.

2114
01:52:27,039 --> 01:52:28,207 
I've never been on a flight.

2115
01:52:29,541 --> 01:52:30,751 
Get up! Let's go!

2116
01:52:34,421 --> 01:52:35,422 
What?

2117
01:52:36,924 --> 01:52:37,925 
Huh!

2118
01:52:38,717 --> 01:52:39,718 
Hmm?

2119
01:52:39,968 --> 01:52:40,969 
What?

2120
01:52:43,722 --> 01:52:44,973 
- Oh no!
- What is it?

2121
01:52:45,015 --> 01:52:45,891 
- Snake?
- A snake?

2122
01:52:45,974 --> 01:52:47,434 
Get inside!
It's not safe, not safe!

2123
01:52:47,476 --> 01:52:48,477 
Let's go.

2124
01:52:51,104 --> 01:52:53,565 
Wow! Such a brave ghost!

2125
01:52:57,778 --> 01:53:00,322 
One, two...
Three and four...

2126
01:53:00,489 --> 01:53:01,698 
Guys, guys, guys!

2127
01:53:02,074 --> 01:53:03,992 
I have to give the final count
for food tomorrow.

2128
01:53:03,992 --> 01:53:05,369 
- Is anyone else coming?
- Yes.

2129
01:53:05,911 --> 01:53:06,995 
There's one more person.

2130
01:53:08,163 --> 01:53:09,164 
Veg.

2131
01:53:10,541 --> 01:53:11,583 
- Hi, Prabhendu...

2132
01:53:11,750 --> 01:53:14,711 
- Shall I book our tickets to Bombay
together for next week?

2133
01:53:14,962 --> 01:53:17,339 
- With you on the flight,
I barely noticed we'd reached Kochi.

2134
01:53:17,631 --> 01:53:18,841 
- Thanks for the company.

2135
01:53:20,425 --> 01:53:21,426 
There's one more.

2136
01:53:21,468 --> 01:53:22,469 
Play, play, play!

2137
01:53:23,554 --> 01:53:26,181 
- Tomorrow evening is my
cousin's pre-wedding party.

2138
01:53:26,473 --> 01:53:29,309 
- Just reminding you, since you said
you might come if you're free.

2139
01:53:29,518 --> 01:53:30,727 
- I've sent the location.

2140
01:53:31,645 --> 01:53:33,438 
What? Pookie Prabha
is feeling shy?

2141
01:53:33,522 --> 01:53:34,523 
Why don't we go?

2142
01:53:34,982 --> 01:53:35,983 
No, no, no.

2143
01:53:36,233 --> 01:53:38,402 
You've got to play a little hard
to get, to be taken seriously.

2144
01:53:38,443 --> 01:53:39,653 
Ugh!

2145
01:53:39,945 --> 01:53:41,530 
When someone's being this frank,

2146
01:53:41,530 --> 01:53:43,031 
don't put on
these stupid airs, okay?

2147
01:53:43,699 --> 01:53:45,075 
I'm not putting on airs, Delulu.

2148
01:53:45,576 --> 01:53:47,619 
I just feel weird when someone
gets close to me too quickly.

2149
01:53:47,828 --> 01:53:51,331 
See... she just met us...
No, actually... sorry... met you.

2150
01:53:51,331 --> 01:53:54,376 
Did she really have to tell you
her whole break-up story right away?

2151
01:53:54,418 --> 01:53:55,294 
No.

2152
01:53:55,335 --> 01:53:56,336 
I think she's into you.

2153
01:53:57,004 --> 01:53:58,589 
No! It's...

2154
01:53:59,423 --> 01:54:01,258 
Maybe it's just because
she cried in front of us.

2155
01:54:02,426 --> 01:54:03,802 
Not just that!

2156
01:54:03,969 --> 01:54:07,181 
Any other guy would have
used this chance to make a move.

2157
01:54:07,639 --> 01:54:10,267 
And... don't think I'm saying this
to flatter you. But...

2158
01:54:11,643 --> 01:54:13,145 
I think you are actually a nice guy.

2159
01:54:13,312 --> 01:54:14,271 
Really?

2160
01:54:14,813 --> 01:54:15,814 
Yeah!

2161
01:54:18,650 --> 01:54:20,944 
In that case,
if I ask you something...

2162
01:54:22,696 --> 01:54:23,739 
will you tell me the truth?

2163
01:54:23,780 --> 01:54:25,866 
This is such a classic guy move!

2164
01:54:25,908 --> 01:54:28,911 
When you're circling around for parking
and spot someone leaving a good space,

2165
01:54:28,911 --> 01:54:30,245 
you just swoop straight in!

2166
01:54:30,829 --> 01:54:32,039 
Love-sick fools!

2167
01:54:36,293 --> 01:54:37,419 
Love?

2168
01:54:38,545 --> 01:54:39,630 
And me?

2169
01:54:45,511 --> 01:54:47,137 
Music is my only love!

2170
01:54:47,179 --> 01:54:48,180 
Oh, spare me the drama!

2171
01:54:48,222 --> 01:54:49,598 
Just leave music out of this.

2172
01:54:50,057 --> 01:54:52,559 
And it's always the single guys
who are the most romantic!

2173
01:54:52,559 --> 01:54:53,602 
Ugh!

2174
01:54:53,602 --> 01:54:54,770 
What do you mean, "Ugh"?

2175
01:54:54,978 --> 01:54:56,063 
Come here, Prabha.

2176
01:54:56,897 --> 01:54:58,315 
Come here.
Sit down.

2177
01:55:02,027 --> 01:55:05,364 
Prabha, a good relationship
just makes life better.

2178
01:55:05,656 --> 01:55:09,243 
See... Someone who can understand
what's in your mind with a single glance...

2179
01:55:09,409 --> 01:55:13,288 
And someone who can understand
the meaning of your silences.

2180
01:55:13,747 --> 01:55:16,125 
Wouldn't it be great
to have that kind of support?

2181
01:55:18,210 --> 01:55:20,462 
You're absolutely hell-bent on
making me park there, aren't you?

2182
01:55:21,088 --> 01:55:23,090 
- Look, afterwards--
- That's not it.

2183
01:55:23,257 --> 01:55:26,510 
Look, you'll be seeing
her again anyway.

2184
01:55:26,593 --> 01:55:28,178 
So you'll have a good
friend in Mumbai.

2185
01:55:28,220 --> 01:55:29,304 
We should go, Prabha.

2186
01:55:29,304 --> 01:55:30,347 
It will be fun.

2187
01:55:31,098 --> 01:55:32,391 
That place is on the outskirts.

2188
01:55:32,641 --> 01:55:33,934 
Going by bike could be risky.

2189
01:55:34,768 --> 01:55:35,978 
Why don't you take your dad's car?

2190
01:55:36,979 --> 01:55:38,188 
Nah, that's not a good idea.

2191
01:55:38,981 --> 01:55:40,357 
Why so much ego, Prabha?

2192
01:55:41,567 --> 01:55:43,235 
It's not ego. It's just--

2193
01:55:44,695 --> 01:55:45,737 
Is that Pappu?

2194
01:55:46,155 --> 01:55:47,156 
Yes.

2195
01:55:47,823 --> 01:55:49,074 
How did he get in?

2196
01:55:49,283 --> 01:55:50,325 
No idea.

2197
01:55:53,662 --> 01:55:54,913 
All done, Pappu.

2198
01:55:55,497 --> 01:55:57,416 
If we don't let this wound heal,

2199
01:55:57,791 --> 01:56:00,085 
the doctor will have to operate
on you again, just like last time.

2200
01:56:01,795 --> 01:56:03,046 
Sleep now, okay?

2201
01:56:03,088 --> 01:56:04,590 
Just call me
if you need anything.

2202
01:56:04,715 --> 01:56:06,133 
Dad is right here, okay?

2203
01:56:12,931 --> 01:56:14,057 
You haven't slept?

2204
01:56:15,350 --> 01:56:16,393 
No.

2205
01:56:16,894 --> 01:56:18,896 
Pappu has a wound on him.

2206
01:56:19,521 --> 01:56:20,647 
If he remains outside,

2207
01:56:20,647 --> 01:56:23,066 
flies will land on the wound,
and it'll end up getting infected.

2208
01:56:24,485 --> 01:56:27,446 
I feel at peace
when he's in here.

2209
01:56:53,555 --> 01:56:55,224 
When did you start this?

2210
01:56:55,974 --> 01:56:57,184 
Two years ago.

2211
01:56:57,226 --> 01:56:58,685 
It used to be a big cylinder.

2212
01:56:58,894 --> 01:57:00,270 
Deepu brought this one.

2213
01:57:00,646 --> 01:57:01,688 
It's comfortable.

2214
01:57:05,317 --> 01:57:07,820 
Please put that spray bottle
in the cupboard.

2215
01:57:08,654 --> 01:57:10,322 
Pappu might chew on it.

2216
01:57:22,835 --> 01:57:24,628 
I haven't moved
any of your mom's belongings.

2217
01:57:25,379 --> 01:57:27,131 
Thulasi washes them every week.

2218
01:57:27,714 --> 01:57:29,091 
I press them
and put them back.

2219
01:57:40,435 --> 01:57:42,938 
When I open that cupboard,
I feel like Sujatha is here,

2220
01:57:42,980 --> 01:57:44,481 
even if just for a little while.

2221
01:57:44,898 --> 01:57:46,525 
It gives me strength.

2222
01:57:58,370 --> 01:57:59,705 
You can go to bed, Indu.

2223
01:58:00,330 --> 01:58:01,665 
We are okay.

2224
01:58:19,141 --> 01:58:20,142 
Dad...

2225
01:58:25,606 --> 01:58:26,732 
Can I...

2226
01:58:26,773 --> 01:58:28,025 
take our car tomorrow?

2227
01:59:06,563 --> 01:59:08,941 
~ I saw you on the floor
In the crowd yet alone ~

2228
01:59:09,149 --> 01:59:11,652 
~ The music in my heart
Rings the lub-dub tone ~

2229
01:59:11,652 --> 01:59:14,071 
~ Would you let me
sing my love? ~

2230
01:59:17,115 --> 01:59:19,743 
~ I drifted through the night
You're the star in my sight ~

2231
01:59:19,785 --> 01:59:22,454 
~ The moment makes it right
For me and you ~

2232
01:59:22,454 --> 01:59:24,665 
~ Would you let me
sing my love? ~

2233
01:59:27,543 --> 01:59:32,464 
~ My heart snaps in two
Oh baby, looking at you ~

2234
01:59:38,595 --> 01:59:43,559 
~ The music slows down
My sweetheart, dancing with you ~

2235
01:59:48,939 --> 01:59:51,441 
~ As the new groom
arrives in splendid array ~

2236
01:59:51,608 --> 01:59:54,319 
~ The whole place suddenly
glows in a lovely way ~

2237
01:59:54,403 --> 01:59:56,864 
~ Like an ocean where
foaming waves lift and play ~

2238
01:59:56,864 --> 01:59:59,783 
~ In this canopy decked
with garlands and bells ~

2239
01:59:59,825 --> 02:00:01,994 
~ The colours now blossom
as beauty swells ~

2240
02:00:02,327 --> 02:00:04,663 
~ Never to separate again ~

2241
02:00:04,913 --> 02:00:07,499 
~ They must flow
through life's terrain ~

2242
02:00:07,624 --> 02:00:12,713 
~ With one shared mind under the sun,
together... forever... as one ~

2243
02:00:34,610 --> 02:00:37,279 
~ Smile and step where rhythms deploy,
ankle bells chiming in light convoy ~

2244
02:00:37,321 --> 02:00:39,615 
~ O sparrows looping
in ecstatic ploy ~

2245
02:00:39,656 --> 02:00:41,909 
~ Who is ready to dissolve
in that whirling joy? ~

2246
02:00:45,329 --> 02:00:47,706 
~ In eyes lit bright where feelings beam,
there flickers softly a tender gleam ~

2247
02:00:47,956 --> 02:00:50,292 
~ There's a tiny rattle
of naughty dreams that tattle ~

2248
02:00:50,334 --> 02:00:54,046 
~ Yet no words can capture
such a dream ~

2249
02:01:17,528 --> 02:01:22,491 
~ Without saying anything
to each other aloud ~

2250
02:01:22,950 --> 02:01:27,830 
~ Through the sharpness of glances
their hearts have avowed ~

2251
02:01:27,955 --> 02:01:33,293 
~ Will not all that's written
on life's turning page ~

2252
02:01:33,335 --> 02:01:38,298 
~ Blossom forth as moonlight
that will never age? ~

2253
02:01:38,298 --> 02:01:40,801 
~ Won't even their silence,
like a drifting cloud ~

2254
02:01:41,009 --> 02:01:46,098 
~ Melt into honeyed words,
soft-falling, unbowed? ~

2255
02:01:46,140 --> 02:01:48,767 
~ The umbrella is unfurling,
its shelter well dealt ~

2256
02:01:48,934 --> 02:01:51,562 
~ And beneath its shade,
a calm is felt ~

2257
02:01:51,603 --> 02:01:54,148 
~ Weaving a love as vast
as the ocean we span ~

2258
02:01:54,273 --> 02:01:56,608 
~ Won't you and I rise
together like dawn... ~

2259
02:01:56,733 --> 02:02:01,530 
~ Forever... as one? ~

2260
02:02:23,886 --> 02:02:26,472 
~ I saw you on the floor
In the crowd yet alone ~

2261
02:02:26,555 --> 02:02:29,057 
~ The music in my heart
Rings the lub-dub tone ~

2262
02:02:29,099 --> 02:02:31,226 
~ Would you let me
sing my love? ~

2263
02:02:34,605 --> 02:02:37,024 
~ In eyes lit bright where feelings beam,
there flickers softly a tender gleam ~

2264
02:02:37,274 --> 02:02:39,610 
~ There's a tiny rattle
of naughty dreams that tattle ~

2265
02:02:39,651 --> 02:02:43,363 
~ Yet no words can capture
such a dream ~

2266
02:03:13,018 --> 02:03:14,770 
I need to tell you something, Prabha.

2267
02:03:17,689 --> 02:03:18,774 
What is it?

2268
02:03:19,441 --> 02:03:20,776 
I like you, Prabha.

2269
02:03:26,949 --> 02:03:28,200 
Well...

2270
02:03:28,784 --> 02:03:29,993 
I like you too, Delulu.

2271
02:03:31,370 --> 02:03:32,538 
That's not what I meant.

2272
02:03:34,873 --> 02:03:36,041 
I'm in love with you.

2273
02:03:39,503 --> 02:03:40,671 
Thank you.

2274
02:03:40,921 --> 02:03:42,005 
I love you too.

2275
02:03:42,172 --> 02:03:44,424 
When I am speaking so frankly
without any ego,

2276
02:03:44,424 --> 02:03:45,968 
why are you behaving like this?

2277
02:03:46,718 --> 02:03:48,971 
When someone else showed up suddenly,
did I become nothing to you?

2278
02:03:50,180 --> 02:03:51,723 
What's gotten into you, Delulu?

2279
02:03:52,683 --> 02:03:54,476 
Weren't you the one who told me
to go meet Saadhya?

2280
02:03:55,435 --> 02:03:57,855 
You're the one who set us up,
even after I said no.

2281
02:03:58,689 --> 02:04:00,274 
Where did this love come from
all of a sudden,

2282
02:04:00,315 --> 02:04:01,358 
like flipping a switch?

2283
02:04:01,900 --> 02:04:02,943 
I don't know.

2284
02:04:03,235 --> 02:04:04,403 
I don't know!

2285
02:04:04,570 --> 02:04:07,656 
I can't hide things from the people
I care about the most.

2286
02:04:08,115 --> 02:04:09,783 
I won't have any peace of mind.

2287
02:04:11,452 --> 02:04:12,911 
And you're the only one I have!

2288
02:04:13,537 --> 02:04:14,788 
I have no one else.

2289
02:04:19,209 --> 02:04:20,461 
This is...

2290
02:04:21,420 --> 02:04:23,213 
This is just a kind
of possessiveness.

2291
02:04:25,549 --> 02:04:26,800 
You'll get over it.

2292
02:04:31,680 --> 02:04:32,890 
Also,

2293
02:04:32,931 --> 02:04:34,475 
even though you're a ghost,

2294
02:04:34,516 --> 02:04:36,101 
you're not old enough
to get married.

2295
02:04:36,477 --> 02:04:37,811 
And I'm almost past that age.

2296
02:04:37,895 --> 02:04:39,521 
Prabha, stop calling me a "ghost"!

2297
02:04:39,688 --> 02:04:41,315 
I've told you this many times.

2298
02:04:42,941 --> 02:04:44,193 
Then what should I call you?

2299
02:04:44,776 --> 02:04:46,320 
You don't know your name.

2300
02:04:46,361 --> 02:04:47,529 
I can't even touch--

2301
02:04:47,571 --> 02:04:49,239 
Prabha, love is not physical!

2302
02:04:49,364 --> 02:04:51,241 
People love each other
from great distances.

2303
02:04:51,575 --> 02:04:53,660 
People fall in love
even when they're much older.

2304
02:04:53,869 --> 02:04:56,288 
It's about the deep
emotional connect we share.

2305
02:04:58,373 --> 02:05:00,000 
We have that between us.

2306
02:05:01,627 --> 02:05:03,337 
Can you honestly say
we don't have that?

2307
02:05:07,424 --> 02:05:08,967 
That's not what I meant.

2308
02:05:10,177 --> 02:05:11,386 
See...

2309
02:05:11,512 --> 02:05:12,888 
I'm trying to be practical here.

2310
02:05:13,680 --> 02:05:15,098 
When Saadhya hugged me today,

2311
02:05:15,933 --> 02:05:17,184 
I felt my heart fill up.

2312
02:05:17,559 --> 02:05:19,520 
It's the first time I've ever felt
something like that.

2313
02:05:21,855 --> 02:05:23,565 
Today was the happiest
day of my life.

2314
02:05:24,066 --> 02:05:25,776 
And you were the first person
I shared it with.

2315
02:05:26,109 --> 02:05:27,194 
And now you've spoiled it!

2316
02:05:27,778 --> 02:05:29,196 
You're so selfish!

2317
02:05:29,655 --> 02:05:31,073 
You've changed so much, Prabha!

2318
02:05:31,532 --> 02:05:33,784 
Your life has only gotten better
since I showed up, right?

2319
02:05:34,284 --> 02:05:36,120 
I'm the reason
you even met Saadhya!

2320
02:05:36,870 --> 02:05:38,330 
You are all the same!

2321
02:05:38,664 --> 02:05:39,832 
All men are the same!

2322
02:05:47,214 --> 02:05:48,215 
Answer the call.

2323
02:06:02,146 --> 02:06:03,105 
I'm sorry.

2324
02:06:03,480 --> 02:06:04,481 
Talk to her.

2325
02:06:11,488 --> 02:06:12,739 
I need some privacy!

2326
02:06:20,831 --> 02:06:22,958 
I'm the one who needs salvation...
from you!

2327
02:06:27,004 --> 02:06:28,464 
What the hell, man?

2328
02:06:28,589 --> 02:06:30,174 
Don't you have anything
better to do, you jerk?

2329
02:07:41,203 --> 02:07:42,204 
Annie...

2330
02:07:43,122 --> 02:07:45,040 
Our daughter has something to tell you.

2331
02:07:46,542 --> 02:07:47,543 
I know what it is.

2332
02:07:47,668 --> 02:07:48,669 
Not happening, Vinod.

2333
02:07:50,045 --> 02:07:51,046 
Huh!

2334
02:07:51,713 --> 02:07:53,257 
She wants a new iPhone, right?

2335
02:07:53,799 --> 02:07:55,634 
She's making a habit of this.

2336
02:07:55,634 --> 02:07:57,636 
No, Mom.
It's not about an iPhone!

2337
02:07:57,803 --> 02:08:00,180 
- Then what?
- It's... well...

2338
02:08:00,639 --> 02:08:01,807 
Papa, just tell her!

2339
02:08:01,807 --> 02:08:02,808 
Mummy...

2340
02:08:02,975 --> 02:08:05,102 
Chechi wants to
dye her hair blue.

2341
02:08:05,102 --> 02:08:06,687 
Not blue, Chacko!
Lavender!

2342
02:08:06,728 --> 02:08:08,856 
- Oh, so I have to say that too?
- Ugh!

2343
02:08:09,022 --> 02:08:11,191 
Oh, Papa, just tell her
the main matter now!

2344
02:08:11,441 --> 02:08:12,442 
What is it?

2345
02:08:12,734 --> 02:08:14,027 
Well, Annie...

2346
02:08:14,111 --> 02:08:15,863 
We're not just their parents.

2347
02:08:15,988 --> 02:08:17,531 
We're their best friends too, right?

2348
02:08:17,781 --> 02:08:19,032 
Skip the intro.

2349
02:08:19,032 --> 02:08:20,033 
Get to the point.

2350
02:08:20,534 --> 02:08:22,411 
Our daughter likes someone.

2351
02:08:22,995 --> 02:08:25,247 
Oh, it's that Joe from Kottayam,
isn't it?

2352
02:08:25,414 --> 02:08:27,541 
The moment I saw his gaze,
I knew it.

2353
02:08:27,791 --> 02:08:30,752 
Eww! Joe and Aishu are already
in a relationship.

2354
02:08:30,794 --> 02:08:32,379 
Huh! Since when?

2355
02:08:33,005 --> 02:08:34,006 
Papa!

2356
02:08:34,047 --> 02:08:35,841 
Okay. Straight to the point.

2357
02:08:36,258 --> 02:08:37,885 
It's someone she met in Bangalore.

2358
02:08:37,885 --> 02:08:40,137 
Not from college,
but through a mutual friend.

2359
02:08:40,345 --> 02:08:42,347 
I warned you before,

2360
02:08:42,764 --> 02:08:44,933 
many guys will come after you,
so watch out.

2361
02:08:44,975 --> 02:08:46,560 
Annie, let me complete.

2362
02:08:46,602 --> 02:08:48,770 
She's the one
who's going to propose!

2363
02:08:50,314 --> 02:08:51,315 
Yes.

2364
02:08:52,274 --> 02:08:54,443 
See, we're the first ones
she's telling this to.

2365
02:08:54,693 --> 02:08:56,111 
I think we should appreciate that.

2366
02:08:56,278 --> 02:08:57,905 
Yeah, we should.

2367
02:08:58,822 --> 02:09:00,282 
He's coming tomorrow.

2368
02:09:00,324 --> 02:09:03,118 
We'll just meet him, grab a coffee,
and head back.

2369
02:09:03,202 --> 02:09:04,203 
That's it.

2370
02:09:04,411 --> 02:09:05,871 
Does he like you?

2371
02:09:06,705 --> 02:09:08,624 
He hasn't said so yet...

2372
02:09:09,082 --> 02:09:11,794 
But I'm so sure... we have
a deep emotional connect.

2373
02:09:12,669 --> 02:09:13,712 
Show me his photo.

2374
02:09:14,421 --> 02:09:15,964 
See, Papa?
What did I say?

2375
02:09:16,006 --> 02:09:17,299 
This is the problem with Mummy.

2376
02:09:17,299 --> 02:09:18,717 
She judges instantly by looks!

2377
02:09:19,343 --> 02:09:22,221 
Ha! We're meeting him tomorrow,
aren't we, Annie?

2378
02:09:22,554 --> 02:09:24,348 
What's the harm in
showing a picture?

2379
02:09:25,182 --> 02:09:26,850 
You don't like beards, Mummy.

2380
02:09:26,975 --> 02:09:28,227 
He has a beard.

2381
02:09:28,477 --> 02:09:29,520 
Also...

2382
02:09:29,895 --> 02:09:30,854 
He is a Hindu.

2383
02:09:31,355 --> 02:09:33,315 
And he's a little older than me.

2384
02:09:33,524 --> 02:09:34,650 
Jesus!

2385
02:09:34,650 --> 02:09:35,984 
Hey, relax!

2386
02:09:36,193 --> 02:09:38,862 
Her prediction is that you'll be
the first one to like him, Annie!

2387
02:09:39,905 --> 02:09:41,073 
Let us go, Mummy.

2388
02:09:41,115 --> 02:09:42,324 
Chechi will be happy.

2389
02:09:42,324 --> 02:09:44,076 
- "Us"? No way!
- Huh?

2390
02:09:44,326 --> 02:09:45,953 
You've got school tomorrow morning!

2391
02:09:47,121 --> 02:09:48,872 
Your Papa and I
will meet him first.

2392
02:09:50,040 --> 02:09:51,959 
- Yeah! Yaay!!
- Success!

2393
02:09:55,170 --> 02:09:56,171 
I'll show you, okay?

2394
02:09:56,213 --> 02:09:57,506 
I'm sure you'll be happy.

2395
02:09:57,548 --> 02:09:58,549 
Promise?

2396
02:09:58,882 --> 02:09:59,883 
Promise.

2397
02:10:02,511 --> 02:10:05,097 
You know Varkey, right?
He runs the coffee shop here.

2398
02:10:05,848 --> 02:10:08,433 
His cold coffee is
already famous, Annie.

2399
02:10:11,270 --> 02:10:12,521 
Where is he?

2400
02:10:12,563 --> 02:10:13,897 
He's late.

2401
02:10:14,606 --> 02:10:16,150 
He needs time to get here, Mummy.

2402
02:10:25,576 --> 02:10:26,618 
What is it?

2403
02:10:34,001 --> 02:10:35,002 
Dear...

2404
02:10:35,002 --> 02:10:36,044 
Papa, one sec.

2405
02:10:42,259 --> 02:10:43,719 
He's not coming, right?

2406
02:10:44,845 --> 02:10:46,054 
Yeah, he's not coming.

2407
02:10:46,096 --> 02:10:47,097 
Are you happy now, Mummy?

2408
02:10:53,061 --> 02:10:54,021 
Sorry, Papa.

2409
02:10:54,188 --> 02:10:55,397 
I think he guessed it.

2410
02:10:57,107 --> 02:10:58,817 
He guessed
why I asked him to come.

2411
02:11:00,360 --> 02:11:01,653 
That's okay, dear.

2412
02:11:02,780 --> 02:11:03,781 
It's alright.

2413
02:11:04,406 --> 02:11:06,492 
We shouldn't expect anything
from anyone.

2414
02:11:06,742 --> 02:11:09,203 
Your generation generally has a hesitation
to become committed.

2415
02:11:10,037 --> 02:11:11,330 
It's quite natural, dear.

2416
02:11:11,955 --> 02:11:14,625 
How can you judge someone
you don't even know, Mummy?

2417
02:11:22,341 --> 02:11:23,801 
Papa, I think he is just confused.

2418
02:11:23,801 --> 02:11:25,511 
Maybe it'll be fine
if I just talk to him.

2419
02:11:27,596 --> 02:11:28,597 
Dear!

2420
02:11:29,056 --> 02:11:30,098 
Dear!

2421
02:11:34,686 --> 02:11:36,939 
Rakhi, please ask the Head Boy
to come to my office.

2422
02:11:42,986 --> 02:11:44,029 
Good afternoon, Ma'am.

2423
02:11:44,321 --> 02:11:45,322 
Good afternoon.

2424
02:11:45,364 --> 02:11:48,242 
Jacob V. Manjooran from 8-C...
His sister had an accident.

2425
02:11:48,283 --> 02:11:49,409 
She's in critical condition.

2426
02:11:49,493 --> 02:11:51,870 
Avinash, I need you to go with him
to the hospital.

2427
02:11:51,912 --> 02:11:53,580 
I'll have a staff member
go with you.

2428
02:11:53,789 --> 02:11:56,250 
- Okay, Ma'am.
- Jacob's parents will be there.

2429
02:11:56,458 --> 02:11:57,876 
Till then, make sure that he's fine.

2430
02:11:58,210 --> 02:11:59,211 
Sure, Ma'am.

2431
02:12:06,009 --> 02:12:07,719 
She's in the ICU.
Third floor.

2432
02:12:41,545 --> 02:12:42,546 
Papa...

2433
02:12:43,338 --> 02:12:44,339 
Where is Chechi?

2434
02:13:05,319 --> 02:13:06,320 
Chacko...

2435
02:13:07,112 --> 02:13:09,281 
Do you know when your sister
was her happiest?

2436
02:13:10,908 --> 02:13:13,869 
When you were born,
on the floor right below us.

2437
02:13:18,457 --> 02:13:20,334 
To make your Chechi happy now,

2438
02:13:21,668 --> 02:13:24,254 
Papa needs your help
with something.

2439
02:13:27,382 --> 02:13:28,759 
The doctors are saying...

2440
02:13:29,426 --> 02:13:30,803 
that your sister is gone.

2441
02:13:32,554 --> 02:13:33,889 
Her brain is dead.

2442
02:13:38,519 --> 02:13:40,521 
To stop the machine support...

2443
02:13:41,355 --> 02:13:43,023 
and set her free...

2444
02:13:44,441 --> 02:13:47,110 
they need my permission.

2445
02:13:50,114 --> 02:13:52,866 
They need a... "Yes" from me.

2446
02:13:56,203 --> 02:13:57,204 
But...

2447
02:13:59,289 --> 02:14:01,500 
unless... unless you also say "Yes"...

2448
02:14:03,669 --> 02:14:04,962 
I won't say "Yes."

2449
02:14:10,551 --> 02:14:12,010 
If I say "Yes"...

2450
02:14:13,303 --> 02:14:14,888 
will Chechi be happy?

2451
02:14:16,181 --> 02:14:17,182 
Yes.

2452
02:14:21,103 --> 02:14:22,104 
Promise?

2453
02:14:25,190 --> 02:14:26,233 
Promise.

2454
02:14:34,408 --> 02:14:35,409 
Yes!

2455
02:15:11,653 --> 02:15:13,822 
My Papa's name is
Vinod Mathew Manjooran.

2456
02:15:14,656 --> 02:15:16,074 
We have a plantation.

2457
02:15:16,450 --> 02:15:18,076 
Magic Hills Plantation.

2458
02:15:18,118 --> 02:15:19,119 
It's in Kuttikkanam.

2459
02:15:19,703 --> 02:15:21,163 
My Mummy's name is Annie.

2460
02:15:21,789 --> 02:15:23,415 
Chacko's real name is Jacob.

2461
02:15:24,291 --> 02:15:25,918 
Same name as my grandfather.

2462
02:15:26,335 --> 02:15:27,336 
What's your name?

2463
02:15:30,214 --> 02:15:31,215 
Delulu.

2464
02:15:31,840 --> 02:15:33,258 
That's just the name
we gave you, right?

2465
02:15:34,510 --> 02:15:35,511 
What's your real name?

2466
02:15:37,346 --> 02:15:38,472 
Delulu...

2467
02:15:39,890 --> 02:15:41,016 
means delusion...

2468
02:15:43,268 --> 02:15:44,353 
means Maya.

2469
02:15:46,605 --> 02:15:47,648 
Maya Mathew.

2470
02:16:06,667 --> 02:16:14,633 
~ Don't leave; don't make my eyes
turn to tears ~

2471
02:16:17,344 --> 02:16:25,352 
~ Don't disappear and fill my heart
with painful spears ~

2472
02:16:27,646 --> 02:16:33,152 
~ Wasn't it in your eyes
that I saw myself clearer ~

2473
02:16:33,318 --> 02:16:37,823 
~ As though I stood
before a living mirror? ~

2474
02:16:38,282 --> 02:16:41,285 
~ When I stood all alone
in silent plea ~

2475
02:16:41,368 --> 02:16:47,958 
~ Didn't you arrive
and breathe life into me? ~

2476
02:16:49,376 --> 02:16:51,962 
~ As I climbed the steps
where darkness spread ~

2477
02:16:51,962 --> 02:16:54,673 
~ To sparkle and shine
in the path ahead ~

2478
02:16:54,673 --> 02:16:59,303 
~ You appeared as a star in golden frame,
you rose as a lamp with a steady flame ~

2479
02:16:59,970 --> 02:17:02,598 
~ You flew from the sky
and landed with art ~

2480
02:17:02,681 --> 02:17:05,350 
~ Resting gently
on the branch of my heart ~

2481
02:17:05,392 --> 02:17:09,521 
~ O petal, O angel,
sweet counterpart ~

2482
02:17:10,647 --> 02:17:14,985 
~ O magic unending,
eternally rare ~

2483
02:17:16,028 --> 02:17:19,740 
~ May you never
disappear anywhere ~

2484
02:17:21,325 --> 02:17:24,995 
~ O magic unending,
eternally rare ~

2485
02:17:26,705 --> 02:17:30,709 
~ May you never
disappear anywhere ~

2486
02:17:32,044 --> 02:17:40,052 
~ Don't leave; don't make my eyes
turn to tears ~

2487
02:17:42,721 --> 02:17:50,687 
~ Don't disappear and fill my heart
with painful spears ~

2488
02:18:25,764 --> 02:18:30,144 
~ The memories simply soak
in the rain of sorrow's tears ~

2489
02:18:30,144 --> 02:18:35,899 
~ And in that rain your face appears,
whispering its stories to my ears ~

2490
02:18:35,941 --> 02:18:40,654 
~ The summer of separation
scorches everything in sight ~

2491
02:18:40,654 --> 02:18:45,784 
~ And in that heat, thoughts of you
smoulder like an ember bright ~

2492
02:18:46,702 --> 02:18:51,832 
~ O smile that enfolds me
in wings of feathered gleam ~

2493
02:18:52,040 --> 02:18:55,961 
~ Do not fade like an unseen wind
lost in a dream ~

2494
02:18:57,337 --> 02:18:59,965 
~ You flew from the sky
and landed with art ~

2495
02:19:00,007 --> 02:19:02,676 
~ Resting gently
on the branch of my heart ~

2496
02:19:02,676 --> 02:19:06,889 
~ O petal, O angel,
sweet counterpart ~

2497
02:19:07,973 --> 02:19:12,352 
~ O magic unending,
eternally rare ~

2498
02:19:13,437 --> 02:19:17,107 
~ May you never
disappear anywhere ~

2499
02:19:18,692 --> 02:19:22,362 
~ O magic unending,
eternally rare ~

2500
02:19:23,989 --> 02:19:28,035 
~ May you never
disappear anywhere ~

2501
02:19:31,330 --> 02:19:32,372 
Indu...

2502
02:19:32,414 --> 02:19:35,083 
Everything you said
could be your imagination,

2503
02:19:35,542 --> 02:19:36,752 
or it could be true.

2504
02:19:37,085 --> 02:19:40,172 
I'd like to believe
that it's true.

2505
02:19:42,925 --> 02:19:46,762 
Her parents haven't seen
the person she loved, till date.

2506
02:19:50,808 --> 02:19:52,976 
A soul can find
peace and salvation

2507
02:19:53,519 --> 02:19:55,813 
only by freeing itself
from sorrow!

2508
02:20:16,875 --> 02:20:18,293 
Lakshmy, the guest room first.

2509
02:20:18,335 --> 02:20:19,336 
Okay, Madam.

2510
02:20:20,254 --> 02:20:21,255 
- Would this do?
- Yes.

2511
02:20:26,927 --> 02:20:27,928 
Yes?

2512
02:20:28,178 --> 02:20:29,596 
I'm a friend of Maya's.

2513
02:20:30,389 --> 02:20:32,182 
I was in the area
and thought I'd drop by.

2514
02:20:33,392 --> 02:20:34,393 
Oh.

2515
02:20:34,768 --> 02:20:35,769 
Come in.

2516
02:20:43,902 --> 02:20:45,237 
Maya always used to say...

2517
02:20:46,238 --> 02:20:47,781 
that regardless of how much
you both fought,

2518
02:20:48,115 --> 02:20:49,867 
when she was away,
the one she missed the most...

2519
02:20:51,118 --> 02:20:52,244 
was her mom.

2520
02:20:52,828 --> 02:20:54,163 
She's a big liar.

2521
02:20:54,246 --> 02:20:56,748 
She'd say the exact same thing
about her Papa.

2522
02:20:59,501 --> 02:21:02,004 
We still haven't been able
to accept that reality

2523
02:21:02,337 --> 02:21:05,174 
So, we don't really...
miss her, as such.

2524
02:21:08,760 --> 02:21:11,138 
Her Papa has turned
into a complete workaholic.

2525
02:21:11,221 --> 02:21:13,056 
And Chacko keeps studying
all the time.

2526
02:21:13,265 --> 02:21:14,850 
He's even the class topper now.

2527
02:21:18,645 --> 02:21:21,523 
But there are two things
that really trouble me.

2528
02:21:22,107 --> 02:21:24,443 
I miss her whenever I open
the fridge in the kitchen.

2529
02:21:25,277 --> 02:21:27,362 
She always used to walk over
and open the fridge,

2530
02:21:27,738 --> 02:21:29,156 
ever since she was a little girl.

2531
02:21:31,533 --> 02:21:34,244 
And then, when I see clothes
lying all over the bed.

2532
02:21:34,828 --> 02:21:37,372 
No matter how many times I told her,
she always left her clothes on the bed.

2533
02:21:38,540 --> 02:21:40,459 
Clothes were her weakness.

2534
02:21:40,876 --> 02:21:43,420 
She was always on her phone,
browsing for them.

2535
02:21:49,468 --> 02:21:51,094 
Let me get you
something to drink.

2536
02:22:27,673 --> 02:22:29,258 
"You don't like beards, Mummy."

2537
02:22:29,466 --> 02:22:30,467 
"He has a beard."

2538
02:22:30,926 --> 02:22:31,927 
"And..."

2539
02:22:32,427 --> 02:22:33,428 
"He is a Hindu."

2540
02:22:33,887 --> 02:22:35,722 
"And he's a little older than me."

2541
02:22:39,643 --> 02:22:40,644 
What's your name?

2542
02:22:47,776 --> 02:22:48,777 
Prabhendu.

2543
02:22:51,989 --> 02:22:54,366 
You were the one she was in love with...
Isn't that right, Prabhendu?

2544
02:23:07,796 --> 02:23:08,797 
Yes.

2545
02:25:51,043 --> 02:25:57,800 
~ When someone sat close to me at night,
like new-fallen rain in cool delight ~

2546
02:25:57,925 --> 02:26:03,514 
~ My heart shifted, lighter than ever,
turning at once to a moonlit river ~

2547
02:26:04,598 --> 02:26:08,060 
~ Slowly unfolding its wings
in tender delight ~

2548
02:26:08,185 --> 02:26:11,563 
~ Weaving a chain of laughter
pure and bright ~

2549
02:26:11,605 --> 02:26:17,194 
~ My mind fills up
on its own tonight ~

2550
02:26:18,403 --> 02:26:24,034 
~ Come, let's go to distances
we've never seen ~

2551
02:26:24,409 --> 02:26:30,415 
~ Becoming two lovely,
colourful clouds serene ~

2552
02:26:30,457 --> 02:26:32,084 
~ In this new birth
where our paths convene ~

2553
02:26:32,126 --> 02:26:37,923 
~ Let's find our shelter on a blossom
branch kissed by morning dew ~

2554
02:26:37,923 --> 02:26:41,385 
~ Becoming the breath
that rises soft and true ~

2555
02:26:41,510 --> 02:26:45,597 
~ Till every painful memory 
softens and bids adieu ~